{"title_page": "Martin Zandvliet", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Martin Zandvliet\n| image         = Applause delegation Martin Zandvliet KVIFF (cropped).jpg\n| alt           = \n| caption       = Martin Zandvliet at KVIFF, 2009\n| birth_name    = Martin Pieter Zandvliet\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1971|01|07|df=y}} \n| birth_place   = [[Fredericia]], Denmark\n| death_date    =  <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = Danish\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = [[Film director]], [[Screenwriter]]\n| years_active  = 2002\u2013present\n| known_for     = \n| spouse        = Camilla Hjelm Knudsen<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cheshire|first1=Godfrey|title=Land of Mine|url=http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/land-of-mine-2017|website=RobertEbert.com|publisher=Ebert Digital LLC|accessdate=27 February 2017|date=10 February 2017}}</ref>\n| notable_works = [[Land of Mine]]\n}}\n\n'''Martin Pieter Zandvliet'''  (born 7 January 1971 in [[Fredericia]]) is a [[Denmark|Danish]] [[film director]] and [[screenwriter]].<ref name=\"DFI\">{{cite web|author1=Danish Film Institute|title=Martin Pieter Zandvliet|url=http://www.dfi.dk/faktaomfilm/person/da/149734.aspx?id=149734|website=DFI|publisher=Danish Film Institute|accessdate=24 January 2017|language=Danish}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n[[File:Applause delegation KVIFF.jpg|thumb|[[Paprika Steen]], Zandvliet and [[Anders August]] in Karlovy Vary]]\nZandvliet originally began as an [[Film editing|editor]], before writing and directing the documentary ''Angels of Brooklyn'' in 2002.<ref name=\"DFI\" /><ref name=\"BT\">{{cite web|author1=/ritzau/|title=Martin Zandvliet, the Man Behind Land of Mine|url=http://www.bt.dk/danmark/blaa-bog-martin-zandvliet-staar-bag-under-sandet?referrer=RSS|website=BT|publisher=Berlingske Media|accessdate=24 January 2017|language=Danish|date=24 January 2017}}</ref> His first major picture was ''[[Applause (2009 film)|Applause]]'' in 2009, which received wide praise.<ref name=\"BT\" /> He then wrote and directed ''[[A Funny Man]]'', based on the life of Danish actor and comedian [[Dirch Passer]]. In 2015 he wrote and directed ''[[Land of Mine]]'', which received almost universal acclaim at home, with many calling it the best Danish film that year,<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Land of Mine|url=http://www.ekkofilm.dk/anmeldelser/under-sandet/|accessdate=11 December 2015|language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Olsen|first1=Jesper|title=Review|url=http://soundvenue.com/film/2015/12/under-sandet-174023|accessdate=11 December 2015|language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Carlsen|first1=Per Juul|title=A Kick in the Head for National Feeling|url=http://www.dr.dk/nyheder/kultur/film/anmeldelse-et-spark-i-skridtet-paa-den-danske-nationalfoelelse|accessdate=11 December 2015|language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kastrup|first1=Kim|title=Land of Mine is Number 1|url=http://ekstrabladet.dk/filmmagasinet/Filmnyheder/under-sandet-ligger-nummer-1/5863594|accessdate=11 December 2015|language=Danish}}</ref> the film was furthermore nominated for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[89th Academy Awards]].<ref name=\"Oscar\">{{cite news|last1=Samuelson|first1=Kate|title=Here Are the 2017 Oscar Nominations|url=http://time.com/4635815/2017-oscars-nominations-list/|accessdate=24 January 2017|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=24 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" \n! width=\"15%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Title !! width=\"4%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Year!! colspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Credited as !! width=\"10%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| Notes !! width=\"1%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |{{abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! width=6% |[[Film director|Director]]!! width=6% |[[Screenwriter|Writer]]!! width=6% | [[Actor]]\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Applause (2009 film)|Applause]]''\n|2009\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| \n| \n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[A Funny Man]]''\n|2011\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|Portrays ''Mus & M\u00e6nd'' director\n| \n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Teddy Bear (2012 film)|Teddy Bear]]''\n|2012\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n|\n| \n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[Land of Mine]]''\n|2015\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| \n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[The Model (film)|The Model]]''\n|2016\n| {{no}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| \n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''[[The Outsider (2018 film)|The Outsider]]''\n|2018\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| {{no}}\n| \n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|''The Marco Effect''\n|2020\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n| {{no}}\n| Co-written with [[Jussi Adler-Olsen]]\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n|-\n|2003\n|Robert Festival Awards\n|Best Documentary\n|''Angels of Brooklyn''\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2009\n|Bombay International Film Festival\n|Golden Gateway\n|rowspan=11|''[[Applause (2009 film)|Applause]]''\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2009\n|[[Ghent International Film Festival]]\n|Best Film\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2009\n|rowspan=2|[[Karlovy Vary International Film Festival]]\n|[[Crystal Globe]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2009\n|Label Europa Cinemas\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2009\n|rowspan=2|[[Zurich Film Festival]]\n|Critics' Choice Award\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2009\n|Best International Feature Film\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|[[63rd Bodil Awards|2010]]\n|[[Bodil Awards]]\n|[[Bodil Award for Best Danish Film]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2010\n|Lecce Festival of European Cinema\n|Golden Olive Tree\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2010\n|Robert Festival Awards\n|Best Film\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2010\n|[[Rouen Nordic Film Festival]]\n|\"Deuxi\u00e8me Souffle\" Award\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2011\n|[[Alliance of Women Film Journalists]]\n|Best Non-English Language Film\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2012\n|rowspan=2|[[Bodil Awards]]\n|Best Film\n|rowspan=6|''[[A Funny Man]]''\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2012\n|Blockbuster Audience Award\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2