|publisher=Berlingske Media|accessdate=24 January 2017|language=Danish|date=24 January 2017}}</ref> His first major picture was ''[[Applause (2009 film)|Applause]]'' in 2009, which received wide praise.<ref name=\"BT\" /> He then wrote and directed ''[[A Funny Man]]'', based on the life of Danish actor and comedian [[Dirch Passer]]. In 2015 he wrote and directed ''[[Land of Mine]]'', which received almost universal acclaim at home, with many calling it the best Danish film that year,<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Land of Mine|url=http://www.ekkofilm.dk/anmeldelser/under-sandet/|accessdate=11 December 2015|language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Olsen|first1=Jesper|title=Review|url=http://soundvenue.com/film/2015/12/under-sandet-174023|accessdate=11 December 2015|language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Carlsen|first1=Per Juul|title=A Kick in the Head for National Feeling|url=http://www.dr.dk/nyheder/kultur/film/anmeldelse-et-spark-i-skridtet-paa-den-danske-nationalfoelelse|accessdate=11 December 2015|language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Kastrup|first1=Kim|title=Land of Mine is Number 1|url=http://ekstrabladet.dk/filmmagasinet/Filmnyheder/under-sandet-ligger-nummer-1/5863594|accessdate=11 December 2015|language=Danish}}</ref> the film was furthermore nominated for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[89th Academy Awards]].<ref name=\"Oscar\">{{cite news|last1=Samuelson|first1=Kate|title=Here Are the 2017 Oscar Nominations|url=http://time.com/4635815/2017-oscars-nominations-list/|accessdate=24 January 2017|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=24 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" \n! width=\"15%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Title !! width=\"4%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" | Year!! colspan=\"3\" scope=\"col\" | Credited as !! width=\"10%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| Notes !! width=\"1%\" rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" |{{abbr|Ref(s)|