]]\n|[[Russia]]\n|[[Military helicopter#Observation helicopters|scout]] / [[Anti-tank warfare#Helicopters|anti-armor]]\n|\n|35<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|11 on order\n|-\n| [[Mil Mi-24]]\n| [[Russia]]\n| [[Attack aircraft|Attack]]\n|\n|unknown{{citation needed|date=January 2020}} \n|First Appear in 4 January 2020\n|-\n| [[Mil Mi-17]]\n| [[Russia]]\n| [[Utility helicopter|utility]]\n|[[Mil Mi-17#Variants|Mi-8/17]]\n|62<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|\n|-\n|[[Sikorsky UH-60 Black Hawk|Sikorsky UH-60]]\n| [[United States]]\n|utility \n||[[Sikorsky UH-60 Black Hawk#Utility variants|UH-60M]]\n|2<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing CH-47 Chinook|CH-47 Chinook]]\n|[[United States]]\n|transport / [[Combat search and rescue|CSAR]]\n|[[Boeing CH-47 Chinook#CH-47D|CH-47D]]\n|19<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n| \n|-\n|[[Westland Sea King]]\n| [[United Kingdom]]\n|transport / utility  \n|[[Westland Sea King#Variant|Commando Mk.2/1]]\n|23<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|\n|-\n|[[Kaman SH-2G Super Seasprite|SH-2G Super Seasprite]]\n|[[United States]]\n| [[Anti-submarine warfare|ASW]] / [[Maritime patrol aircraft|maritime patrol]]\n|\n|10<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|\n|-\n|[[A\u00e9rospatiale Gazelle]]\n|[[France]]\n|scout / [[Anti-tank warfare#Helicopters|anti-armor]]\n|[[A\u00e9rospatiale Gazelle#Variants|SA342]]\n|89<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|\n|-\n|[[Eurocopter AS350 \u00c9cureuil|Eurocopter AS350]]\n|[[France]]\n|liaison \n|\n|3<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n| \n|-\n| [[AgustaWestland AW109]]\n| Italy\n| light utility / [[Air transports of heads of state and government|VIP]]\n|\n|3<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|\n|-\n| [[AgustaWestland AW139]]\n| Italy\n| light utility / [[Air transports of heads of state and government|VIP]]\n|\n|2<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | [[Trainer (aircraft)|Trainer aircraft]]\n|-\n|  [[Aero L-59 Albatros|Aero L-59]]\n| [[Czech Republic]]\n| primary trainer\n|\n| 48<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|\n|-\n| [[Grob G 115]]\n| [[Germany]]\n|basic trainer\n| \n|74<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|\n|-\n| [[Hongdu JL-8]]\n| [[China]] / [[Pakistan]]\n|jet trainer\n|[[Hongdu JL-8#Variants|K-8]]\n| 119\n| \n|-\n| [[Embraer EMB 312 Tucano|Embraer EMB-312]]\n| [[Brazil]]\n| trainer\n|\n|54<ref name=\"flight2020\" />\n|-\n! style=\"align: center; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | [[Unmanned aerial vehicle|UAV]]\n|-\n|[[ASN-209]]\n|[[China]]\n|surveillance \n|\n|\n|locally produced under license<ref>{{cite news|url=https://phys.org/news/2013-05-china-emerging-drone-warfare.html|first=Christopher|last=Bodeen|title=China emerging as new force in drone warfare|website=[[Phys.org]]|date=3 May 2013|accessdate=2 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[CASC Rainbow]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.xcnnews.com/js/2745387.html|title=\u4e2d\u570b\u7121\u4eba\u6a5f\u5230\u5e95\u6709\u591a\u725b\uff1f\u4e00\u6b21\u9f4a\u5c04\u59a5\u59a5\u5e79\u6389\u4e00\u500b\u5766\u514b\u9023|date=3 January 2018|website=xcnnews.com|accessdate=2 April 2018}}</ref>\n|[[China]]\n|surveillance \n|[[CASC Rainbow#CH-5|CH-5]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[CAIG Wing Loong]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2015/03/20/chinas-weapons-of-mass-consumption/|first=Joseph E.|last=Lin|title=China\u2019s Weapons of Mass Consumption|date=20 March 2015|website=Foreign Policy|accessdate=2 April 2018}}</ref>  \n|[[China]]\n| reconnaissance\n|\n|108<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.sohu.com/a/382780569_120126853/?pvid=000115_3w_a&fbclid=IwAR1v65snZLw1qxLqex0nxZ1eQk7B2ykGI6MP5UPqkbWmmaB56Wj7s_PKusE|title=\u7ffc\u9f99\u7ff1\u7fd4\u4e1c\u5317\u975e\uff01\u57c3\u53ca\u4e24\u6b21\u5171\u5f15\u8fdb108\u67b6\uff0c\u53ef\u6302\u8f7d8\u679a\u7a7a\u5730\u5bfc\u5f39|lang=zh|date=30 March 2020|access-date=20 April 2020|website=sohu.com}}</ref>\n|76 Wing Loong & 32 Wing Loong II\n|-\n|[[AeroVironment RQ-20 Puma|RQ-20 Puma]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.defense.gov/News/Contracts/Contract-View/Article/1468905/|title=Contracts|publisher=US Department of Defense|date=16 March 2018|accessdate=2 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180318120429/https://www.defense.gov/News/Contracts/Contract-View/Article/1468905/|archive-date=18 March 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite pr|url=https://www.avinc.com/resources/press-releases/view/aerovironment-awarded-44.5-million-puma-ae-uas-contract-from-a-major-countr|title=AeroVironment Awarded $44.5 Million Puma AE UAS Contract from a Major Country in the Middle East|publisher=AeroVironment|date=6 March 2018|accessdate=2 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180318055054/https://www.avinc.com/resources/press-releases/view/aerovironment-awarded-44.5-million-puma-ae-uas-contract-from-a-major-countr|archive-date=18 March 2018 }}</ref>\n |[[United States]]\n|surveillance \n|\n|\n| hand launched system \n|-\n|[[Teledyne Ryan Scarab|324 Scarab]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/egypt-resumes-scarab-uav-upgrade-talks-215351/|title=Egypt resumes Scarab UAV upgrade talks|author=Peter La Franchi|publisher=Flight Global|date=5 July 2007|accessdate=2 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180309182732/https://www.flightglobal.com/news/articles/egypt-resumes-scarab-uav-upgrade-talks-215351/|archive-date=9 March 2018 }}</ref>\n| United States\n|surveillance \n|\n|\n| \n|-\n|[[Lip\u00e1n M3]]<ref>[https://dragonsdrones.com/drones/lipan-m3/ Dragondrones] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180309120442/https://dragonsdrones.com/drones/lipan-m3/ |date=9 March 2018 }} Retrieved 2 April 2018.</ref>\n| [[Argentina]]  \n|surveillance \n|\n|\n| \n|-\n|[[Meggitt Banshee]] -<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.meggitt.com/news/aerial-targetry-and-scoring-wins-for-meggitt-defence-systems/|title=Aerial targetry and scoring wins for Meggitt Defence Systems|accessdate=2 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170702185221/https://www.meggitt.com/news/aerial-targetry-and-scoring-wins-for-meggitt-defence-systems/|archive-date=2 July 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> \n| [[United Kingdom]]\n| [[target drone]] \n|\n|\n| \n|}\n\n===Future===\n[[File:MAKS Airshow 2015 (20615630784).jpg|thumb|[[Sukhoi Su-35]]]]\nEgypt is in an advanced stage of negotiations for the purchase of the Russian strategic air lifter [[Ilyushin Il-76|Il-76MD-90A]]. The first export contracts of the aircraft were to be signed within 4\u20136 months after the [[MAKS (air show)|MAKS]]-2015 air show.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://tass.ru/armiya-i-opk/2212298|agency=TASS|script-title=ru:\u041e\u0410\u041a \u043e\u0436\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0435 \u044d\u043a\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0442\u044b \u043d\u0430 \u0418\u043b-76\u041c\u0414-90\u0410 \u0447\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0437 4\u20136 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0446\u0435\u0432 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435 \u041c\u0410\u041a\u0421-2015.|date=26 August 2015|language=ru|accessdate=2 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180403234519/http://tass.ru/armiya-i-opk/2212298|archive-date=3 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Egypt planned to sign a large arms deal with Russia for the purchase of 24 MiG-35 fighter jets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://defense-update.com/20140422_egypt-interested-buying-24-mig-35s-russia.html|title=Egypt interested in buying 24 MiG-35s from Russia|author=News Desk|publisher=defense-update.com|accessdate=14 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141030095133/http://defense-update.com/20140422_egypt-interested-buying-24-mig-35s-russia.html|archive-date=30 October 2014|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/egypt-russia-said-close-to-deal-for-advanced-jets/|title=Russia said set to sell its top fighter jets to Egypt|work=The Times of Israel|accessdate=14 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626112607/http://www.timesofisrael.com/egypt-russia-said-close-to-deal-for-advanced-jets/|archive-date=26 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://in.rbth.com/blogs/2014/05/30/mig-35_the_plane_that_wont_die_35625|title=MiG-35: The plane that won't die|work=in.rbth.com|accessdate=30 May 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170408114322/http://in.rbth.com/blogs/2014/05/30/mig-35_the_plane_that_wont_die_35625|archive-date=8 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2015, MiG Director General Sergei Korotkov announced that the company was ready to supply the MiG-35 jets to Egypt should the country request them.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sputniknews.com/business/201502201018545949/|title=Russia Ready to Supply MiG-35 Jets to Egypt \u2013 Manufacturer|last=Sputnik|website=sputniknews.com|access-date=8 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401163634/https://sputniknews.com/business/201502201018545949/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, in April 2015, Egypt signed a $2&nbsp;billion contract for the purchase of 46 MiG-29M/M2 multi-role fighters instead.<ref name=\"migavia.ru\">{{cite news|url=http://www.migavia.ru/index.php/ru/novosti/smi-o-nas/543-my-obezopasilis-ot-katastroficheskikh-posledstvij|title=\u041c\u044b \u043e\u0431\u0435\u0437\u043e\u043f\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0441\u044c \u043e\u0442 \u043a\u0430\u0442\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0440\u043e\u0444\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0438\u0439|language=Russian|website=migavia.ru|access-date=6 February 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160207000510/http://www.migavia.ru/index.php/ru/novosti/smi-o-nas/543-my-obezopasilis-ot-katastroficheskikh-posledstvij|archive-date=7 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vedomosti.ru/politics/articles/2015/05/25/593348-soglasovan-kontrakt-na-postavku-46-istrebitelei-mig-29-v-egipet|title=\u0421\u043e\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0443 46 \u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0435\u0431\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0439 \u041c\u0438\u0413-29 \u0432 \u0415\u0433\u0438\u043f\u0435\u0442|website=vedomosti.ru|date=24 May 2015|accessdate=28 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626164540/https://www.vedomosti.ru/politics/articles/2015/05/25/593348-soglasovan-kontrakt-na-postavku-46-istrebitelei-mig-29-v-egipet|archive-date=26 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Airbus Defence and Space]] received from Egypt its first order of [[Airbus A400M Atlas|A400M]]. Egypt asked the company to have the [[Airbus A400M Atlas|A400M]] as soon as possible.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://andaluciainformacion.es/andalucia/537976/airbus-recibe-de-egipto-el-primer-pedido-de-un-a400m-tras-el-accidente/|title=Airbus recibe de Egipto el primer pedido de un A400M tras el accidente.|date=5 October 2015|language=es|accessdate=2 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151009040627/http://andaluciainformacion.es/andalucia/537976/airbus-recibe-de-egipto-el-primer-pedido-de-un-a400m-tras-el-accidente/|archive-date=9 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://andaluciainformacion.es/andalucia/551083/egipto-comprara-hasta-doce-a400m-a-airbus-por-1800-millones/|title=Egipto comprar\u00e1 hasta doce A400M a Airbus por 1.800 millones|date=23 November 2015|language=es|accessdate=2 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151125030220/http://andaluciainformacion.es/andalucia/551083/egipto-comprara-hasta-doce-a400m-a-airbus-por-1800-millones/|archive-date=25 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Rosoboronexport]] and the Russian Helicopters holding are engaged in consultations with their Egyptian partners concerning a possible acquisition of [[Kamov]] [[Kamov Ka-50|Ka-52K]] ship-based helicopters for the 2 [[Mistral-class amphibious assault ship|Mistral]]-class helicopter carriers that Egypt has agreed to buy from France.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://rbth.co.uk/news/2015/09/24/egypt_may_buy_some_30_ka-52k_helicopters_from_russia_for_over_1_billion_49514.html|title=Egypt may buy some 30 Ka-52K helicopters from Russia for over $1 billion|date=24 September 2015|accessdate=2 April 2018}}</ref> An Egyptian Air Force delegation had access to the helicopter before the official opening of the [[MAKS (air show)|MAKS]]-2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vedomosti.ru/politics/articles/2015/08/27/606428-novinkami-rossiiskogo-aviaproma-interesuyutsya-klienti-rosoboroneksporta-i-egipet|title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u043d\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0448\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0430\u0432\u0438\u0430\u043f\u0440\u043e\u043c\u0430 \u0438\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0443\u044e\u0442\u0441\u044f \u043a\u043b\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442\u044b \"\u0420\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u044d\u043a\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\u0430\" \u0438 \u0415\u0433\u0438\u043f\u0435\u0442|date=26 August 2015|language=ru|accessdate=2 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180403112926/https://www.vedomosti.ru/politics/articles/2015/08/27/606428-novinkami-rossiiskogo-aviaproma-interesuyutsya-klienti-rosoboroneksporta-i-egipet|archive-date=3 April 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, it was reported that [[Egypt]] would procure \"over two dozen\" Su-35 aircraft from Russia in a deal valued about $US 2 billion, finalized in late 2018. Deliveries are expected to begin as early as 2020 or 2021.<ref name=\"EgyptJanes\">{{cite web |last1=Binnie |first1=Jeremy |title=Egypt reportedly orders Su-35 fighters |url=https://www.janes.com/article/87282/egypt-reportedly-orders-su-35-fighters |website=Jane's 360 |access-date=18 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190318224216/https://www.janes.com/article/87282/egypt-reportedly-orders-su-35-fighters |archive-date=18 March 2019 |location=London |date=18 March 2019 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref name=\"EgyptRT\">{{cite web |title=Russia & Egypt seal $2 billion deal for supply of Su-35 fighter jets |url=https://www.rt.com/business/454106-russia-egypt-su-35-deal/ |access-date=20 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190319154719/https://www.rt.com/business/454106-russia-egypt-su-35-deal/ |archive-date=19 March 2019 |date=18 March 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"EgyptKommersant\">{{cite web |last1=\u0421\u0430\u0444\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0432 |first1=\u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d |last2=\u0414\u0436\u043e\u0440\u0434\u0436\u0435\u0432\u0438\u0447 |first2=\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u0430 |title=\u0421\u0443-35 \u0443\u043a\u0440\u0435\u043f\u044f\u0442 \u0435\u0433\u0438\u043f\u0435\u0442\u0441\u043a\u0443\u044e \u0441\u0438\u043b\u0443 |url=https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/3915483 |website=Kommersant |access-date=18 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190318131445/https://www.kommersant.ru/doc/3915483 |archive-date=18 March 2019 |date=18 March 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref> However, deputy head of the [[Rosoboronexport]] Sergei Kornev denied any contract regarding to the supply of Su-35 fighters to Egypt has been signed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/655788|title=\"\u0420\u043e\u0441\u043e\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u044d\u043a\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0442\" \u043e\u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0433 \u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0438\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043a\u0443 \u0421\u0443-35 \u0415\u0433\u0438\u043f\u0442\u0443|website=[[Interfax]]|date=26 March 2019|access-date=17 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190605020831/https://www.interfax.ru/russia/655788|archive-date=5 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Munitions===\n{{Main|List of munitions used by the Egyptian Air Force}}\n\n==Aircraft insignia==\nThe Roundel of the EAF consists of three circles, with the outside one being red, the middle one white, and the inner one being black, matching the Egyptian flag. Former roundels of the EAF included a similar variant with two green stars used from 1961 to 1973, and one with the old Egyptian crescent and three stars on a green background. Changes in markings reflect political changes.\n\n===Roundels===\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%; text-align:center\"\n![[File:Royal Egyptian Air Force roundel (1932).svg|110px|]]\n![[File:Roundel of Egypt 02.gif|120px|]]\n![[File:Royal Egyptian Air Force roundel (1939-1945).svg|130px|]]\n![[File:Egyptian Air Force roundel (1945-1958).svg|130px|]]\n![[File:Roundel of Egypt (1958\u20131972).svg|130px]]\n![[File:Roundel of Egypt.svg|130px|]]\n|-\n!1932\u20131932\n!1932\u20131932\n!1932\u20131945\n!1945\u20131958\n!1958\u20131972\n!1972\u2013present\n|}\n\n===Tail marking===\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:100%; text-align:center\"\n![[File:Fin flash of Egypt.gif|80px|]]\n![[File:Egypt fin flash.svg|150px|]]\n![[File:Flag of Syria.svg|150px|]]\n![[File:Flag of Egypt (1972-1984).svg|150px|]]\n![[File:Flag of Egypt.svg|150px|]]\n|-\n!1932\u20131945\n!1945\u20131958\n!1958\u20131972\n!1972\u20131984\n!1984\u2013present\n|}\n\n==Egyptian Air Force ranks==\n{{Main|Egyptian Air Force ranks}}\n;Officers\n{| style=\"border:1px solid #8888aa; background-color:#f7f8ff; padding:5px; font-size:95%; margin: 0px 12px 12px 0px;\"\n{{Ranks and Insignia of Non NATO Air Forces/OF/Blank}}\n{{Ranks and Insignia of Non NATO Air Forces/OF/Egypt}}\n|}\n\n;Enlisted\n{| style=\"border:1px solid #8888aa; background-color:#f7f8ff; padding:5px; font-size:95%; margin: 0px 12px 12px 0px;\"\n{{Ranks and Insignia of Non NATO Air Forces/OR/Blank}}\n{{Ranks and Insignia of Non NATO Air Forces/OR/Egypt}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of air forces]]\n*[[Egyptian Air Force ranks]]\n*[[National Authority for Remote Sensing and Space Sciences]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Air force of Egypt}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20031216161315/http://www.scramble.nl/eg.htm Egyptian Air Force Overview] from [[Scramble (magazine)|Scramble]]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20141220060601/http://www.egyptdailynews.com/egyptian%20airforce.htm Pictures of the Egyptian Air Force]\n*[http://www.country-data.com/cgi-bin/query/r-4163.html War of Attrition and the October 1973 War]\n*[http://www.f-16.net/f-16_users_article4.html Al Quwwat al Jawwiya Ilmisriya Egyptian Air Force \u2013 EAF]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20071029092340/http://defence-data.com/f2002/pagefa1042.htm Boeing Chinook modernisation programme for Egyptian Air Force is on track]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20120121121431/http://www.mmc.gov.eg/Academies/AFA/default.htm Site of Egyptian Air Force Academy]\n\n{{Military of Egypt}}\n{{air forces}}\n\n[[Category:Egyptian Air Force| ]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations established in 1937]]\n[[Category:Military aviation in Africa]]\n\n[[hu:Egyiptom hadereje#L\u00e9gier\u0151]]\n", "name_user": "LilHelpa", "label": "safe", "comment": "it's \u2192 its; mos", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egyptian_Air_Force"}
{"title_page": "Bina Sheth Lashkari", "text_new": "{{Infobox Person\n| name        = Bina Sheth Lashkari\n| image       = Bina Sheth Lashkari (Maharashtra), at the presentation of Stree Shakti Puraskar 2013 on International Women\u2019s Day, at Rashtrapati Bhavan (cropped).jpg\n| image_size  =\n| caption     = in 2013\n| birth_name  =\n| birth_date  =\n| birth_place =\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| death_cause =\n| residence   =\n| other_names =\n| known_for   = starting a Doorstep School\n| education   =\n| employer    =\n| occupation  =\n| spouse      =\n| partner     =\n| children    =\n| parents     =\n| relatives   =\n| signature   =\n| website     =\n| footnotes   =\n| nationality = [[India]]\n}}\n'''Bina Sheth Lashkari''' (born ) is an [[India]]n Doorstep school founder in India. Over 30 years she has helped to organise the education of 100,000 children in Mumbai. In 2013 she was awarded the [[Stree Shakti Puraskar]] \n\n==Life==\nLaskari took her first degree in [[child psychology]].\n\nShe started her work when she founded her first school in Cuffe Parade in [[Colaba]] in 1988. At the time children from the slums could only look on as richer children went off to posh schools. She originally had 25 children and their [[Banjara]] parents were working for low wages gutting fish.<ref name=mmi/> She had been inspired to the idea while she was taking her masters degree in social work. She had visited the local school and she was surprised to find that children were leaving after her three or four years. Visiting the children's parent she found that the children were all ready an essential part of their families wage earning. They could not be spared if the family was to survive. With the assistance of Rajani Paranjape she started a school that could be on their doorstep.<ref name=better/>\n\n[[File:Pranab Mukherjee presenting the \u201cMata Jijabai Award\u201d to Smt. Bina Sheth Lashkari (Maharashtra), at the presentation of Stree Shakti Puraskar 2013 on the occasion of International Women\u2019s Day, at Rashtrapati Bhavan.jpg|thumb|left|Pranab Mukherjee presenting the \u201cMata Jijabai Award\u201d to Smt. Bina Sheth Lashkari (Maharashtra), at the presentation of Stree Shakti Puraskar 2013 on the occasion of International Women\u2019s Day, at Rashtrapati Bhavan]]\nOn  [[International Women\u2019s Day]] in 2013 the President of India [[Pranab Mukherjee]] presented her with the [[Stree Shakti Puraskar]]. The award was one of six made in New Delhi at the Presidential Palace - [[Rashtrapati Bhavan]]. She was nominated by the state of [[Maharashtra]] for her work in education and training.<ref name=six>{{Cite web|url=https://pib.gov.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=104539|title=President Confers Stree Shakti Puruskar on International Women\u2019s Day|website=pib.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge visited her in [[Mumbai]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MqVIOEzSBhA|title=Duke and Duchess visit|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> That year the school's campaign had led to the naming of streets after their pupils. Previously unnamed streets in three areas of Mumbai were named after their students. The objective is to inspire other students to gain an education and have ambition.<ref name=better>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/55594/slum-kids-road-naming-doorstep-school-mumbai-rajani-paranjpe-bina-lashkari/|title=This NGO is Motivating Slum Kids to Stay in School By Naming Alleys and Streets After Them|date=2016-05-19|website=The Better India|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019 it was estimated that over the 31 years she has helped to organise the education of 100,000 children in Mumbai. By that time the school had seven yellow school buses with school equipment inside them. Each of them stops four times each day for two and a half hours, so each bus is teaching 100 children each day.<ref name=\"mmi\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/202767/mumbai-free-school-for-poor-slum-kids-school-on-wheels-students-hero/|title=From Doorstep to On Wheels: How This Woman Taught Over 1 Lakh Slum Kids in 30 Yrs|date=2019-11-12|website=The Better India|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Nari Shakti Puraskar}}{{Improve categories|date=April 2020}}{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lashkari, Bina Sheth}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:People from Mumbai]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Person\n| name        = Bina Sheth Lashkari\n| image       = Bina Sheth Lashkari (Maharashtra), at the presentation of Stree Shakti Puraskar 2013 on International Women\u2019s Day, at Rashtrapati Bhavan (cropped).jpg\n| image_size  =\n| caption     = in 2013\n| birth_name  =\n| birth_date  =\n| birth_place =\n| death_date  =\n| death_place =\n| death_cause =\n| residence   =\n| other_names =\n| known_for   = starting a Doorstep School\n| education   =\n| employer    =\n| occupation  =\n| spouse      =\n| partner     =\n| children    =\n| parents     =\n| relatives   =\n| signature   =\n| website     =\n| footnotes   =\n| nationality = [[India]]\n}}\n'''Bina Sheth Lashkari''' (born ) is an [[India]]n Doorstep school founder in India. Over 30 years she has helped to organise the education of 100,000 children in Mumbai. In 2013 she was awarded the [[Stree Shakti Puraskar]] \n\n==Life==\nLaskari took her first degree in [[child psychology]].\n\nShe started her work when she founded her first school in Cuffe Parade in [[Colaba]] in 1988. At the time children from the slums could only look on as richer children went off to posh schools. She originally had 25 children and their [[Banjara]] parents were working for low wages gutting fish.<ref name=mmi/> She had been inspired to the idea while she was taking her masters degree in social work. She had visited the local school and she was surprised to find that children were leaving after her three or four years. Visiting the children's parent she found that the children were all ready an essential part of their families wage earning. They could not be spared if the family was to survive. With the assistance of Rajani Paranjape she started a school that could be on their doorstep.<ref name=better/>\n\n[[File:Pranab Mukherjee presenting the \u201cMata Jijabai Award\u201d to Smt. Bina Sheth Lashkari (Maharashtra), at the presentation of Stree Shakti Puraskar 2013 on the occasion of International Women\u2019s Day, at Rashtrapati Bhavan.jpg|thumb|left|Pranab Mukherjee presenting the \u201cMata Jijabai Award\u201d to Smt. Bina Sheth Lashkari (Maharashtra), at the presentation of Stree Shakti Puraskar 2013 on the occasion of International Women\u2019s Day, at Rashtrapati Bhavan]]\nOn  [[International Women\u2019s Day]] in 2013 the President of India [[Pranab Mukherjee]] presented her with the [[Stree Shakti Puraskar]]. The award was one of six made in New Delhi at the Presidential Palace - [[Rashtrapati Bhavan]]. She was nominated by the state of [[Maharashtra]] for her work in education and training.<ref name=six>{{Cite web|url=https://pib.gov.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=104539|title=President Confers Stree Shakti Puruskar on International Women\u2019s Day|website=pib.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016 the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge visited her in [[Mumbai]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MqVIOEzSBhA|title=Duke and Duchess visit|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> That year the school's campaign had led to the naming of streets after their pupils. Previously unnamed streets in three areas of Mumbai were named after their students. The objective is to inspire other students to gain an education and have ambition.<ref name=better>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/55594/slum-kids-road-naming-doorstep-school-mumbai-rajani-paranjpe-bina-lashkari/|title=This NGO is Motivating Slum Kids to Stay in School By Naming Alleys and Streets After Them|date=2016-05-19|website=The Better India|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019 it was estimated that over the 31 years she has helped to organise the education of 100,000 children in Mumbai. By that time the school had seven yellow school buses with school equipment inside them. Each of them stops four times each day for two and a half hours, so each bus is teaching 100 children each day.<ref name=\"mmi\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebetterindia.com/202767/mumbai-free-school-for-poor-slum-kids-school-on-wheels-students-hero/|title=From Doorstep to On Wheels: How This Woman Taught Over 1 Lakh Slum Kids in 30 Yrs|date=2019-11-12|website=The Better India|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Nari Shakti Puraskar}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lashkari, Bina Sheth}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:People from Mumbai]]\n", "name_user": "Oronsay", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:added more cat template", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bina_Sheth_Lashkari"}
