{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil", "text_new": "{{currentevent|date=April 2020}}\n{{Cleanup translation|Portuguese}}\n{{Cleanup rewrite|[[WP:NOTNEWS|Wikipedia is not a newspaper]]|date=April 2020}}\n{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use American English|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Brazil}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Brazil.svg\n| legend1         = Map of states with confirmed coronavirus cases (as of 16 April)\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Brazil]]\n| first_case      = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| arrival_date    = 26 February 2020<br/>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=2|day1=25|year1=2020}})\n| origin          = [[Lombardy]], Italy<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/02/25/ministerio-da-saude-investiga-possivel-paciente-com-coronavirus-em-sp-caso-foi-para-contraprova.ghtml|title=Painel Coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n| recovery_cases  = \n| deaths          = 2,575<ref name=Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade/>\n| confirmed_cases = 40,581<ref name=\"Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade\">{{cite web |url=https://covid.saude.gov.br/ |title=Painel Coronav\u00edrus |language=Portuguese |work=Ministry of Health |access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n| total_ili       =  <!-- P.s: Several states in the country confirmed cases after the closure of the Ministry of Health. Brazil is a Federative Republic, divided into 27 federative units, of which confirm results before the federal government. -->\n| website         = {{URL|https://coronavirus.saude.gov.br/}}\n}}\n\nThe ongoing [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|pandemic]] of [[COVID-19|coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19) was confirmed to have spread to [[Brazil]] on 25 February 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46435-brasil-confirma-primeiro-caso-de-novo-coronavirus|title=Brasil confirma primeiro caso da doen\u00e7a|date=26 February 2020|website=Ministerio da Saude|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306155723/https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46435-brasil-confirma-primeiro-caso-de-novo-coronavirus|archive-date=6 March 2020|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref> after a 61-year-old man from [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] who had returned from [[Lombardy]], Italy tested positive for the virus. As of 19 April 2020, 38,654 cases have been confirmed in the country, causing 2,462 deaths.<ref name=\"Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade\"/>\n\nThe pandemic has triggered a variety of responses from federal, state and local governments, with an impact on politics, education and the economy. On 27 March Brazil announced a temporary ban on foreign air travelers,<ref>{{cite web |author1=Pedro Fonseca |author2=Jamie McGeever |title=Coronavirus: Brazil bans foreign air travelers |url=https://www.mercurynews.com/2020/03/27/coronavirus-brazil-bans-foreign-air-travelers/ |website=The Mercury News |accessdate=13 April 2020 |date=28 March 2020}}</ref> and most state governors have imposed [[Quarantine|quarantines]] to prevent the spread of the [[SARS-CoV-2|virus]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Brazil reports more than 1,000 coronavirus deaths |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-52251342 |website=BBC News |publisher=BBC |accessdate=13 April 2020 |date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=\"Elsevier\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center|last=Elsevier|date=|website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Matt|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic?|date=4 March 2020|work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|issn=1357-0978}}</ref>\n\nUnlike [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]], the [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 <ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus|website=Imperial News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England|last=|first=|date=|website=GOV.UK|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> has been much lower, but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=\"WFSA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" />\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Brazil medical cases chart}}\n\n=== January ===\n* January 28, the [[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Ministry of Health]] (''Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade'') raised the emergency alert to level 2 of 3, considering an \"imminent threat\" for Brazil, as a suspected case was being investigated in [[Belo Horizonte]], Minas Gerais.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-caso-suspeito-de-coronavirus-em-mg.ghtml |title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade investiga caso suspeito de coronav\u00edrus em MG |last= Cruz |first= Carolina |date= 28 January 2020 |accessdate=28 January 2020 | work = G1 |language= pt-br |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200128142750/https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-caso-suspeito-de-coronavirus-em-mg.ghtml |archive-date=28 January 2020 |url-status= live}}</ref> \n\n* January 29, the Ministry announced it was investigating two other suspected cases, in [[Porto Alegre]] and [[Curitiba]]. No further information was given about the patients in Porto Alegre and Curitiba. However, it was informed that the Belo Horizonte patient was a student that had recently visited [[Wuhan]], China, point of origin of the outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-3-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil/|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade confirma 3 casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil|date=28 January 2020|publisher=Exame Abril|accessdate=29 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129042253/https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-3-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil/|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== February ===\n* February 3, the Minister of Health [[Luiz Henrique Mandetta]] said that the Brazilian government would declare a [[Public Health Emergency of International Concern]], even without confirmed cases in the country. He also said the government would assist on the return of Brazilians from Wuhan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/03/nao-gosto-de-trabalhar-com-prazo-diz-ministro-da-saude-sobre-repatriacao-de-brasileiros-de-wuhan.ghtml|title=Pa\u00eds adotar\u00e1 emerg\u00eancia para retirar cidad\u00e3os de \u00e1rea de surto de coronav\u00edrus, diz ministro|date=3 February 2020|publisher=G1|accessdate=3 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203161354/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/03/nao-gosto-de-trabalhar-com-prazo-diz-ministro-da-saude-sobre-repatriacao-de-brasileiros-de-wuhan.ghtml|archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n* February 4, the Ministry confirmed that around 30 Brazilians were in Wuhan, and that they would return to the country on 8 February. It was also announced that they would be [[quarantine]]d for 18 days in [[An\u00e1polis]], Goi\u00e1s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/04/coronavirus-brasileiros-na-china-devem-chegar-ao-pais-no-sabado-e-cumprir-quarentena-em-anapolis.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: brasileiros na China devem chegar ao pa\u00eds no s\u00e1bado e cumprir quarentena em An\u00e1polis|date=4 February 2020|publisher=G1|accessdate=4 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205010554/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/04/coronavirus-brasileiros-na-china-devem-chegar-ao-pais-no-sabado-e-cumprir-quarentena-em-anapolis.ghtml|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* February 5, the Brazilian government sent two planes to evacuate 34 Brazilians from [[Wuhan]]. They and the flight crew were quarantined at a [[Brazilian Air Force]] base in An\u00e1polis,<ref>{{cite news|first1=Pedro Henrique|last1=Gomes|date=5 February 2020 |url= https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/05/coronavirus-avioes-da-fab-decolam-em-viagem-para-buscar-brasileiros-na-china.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: avi\u00f5es da FAB decolam de Bras\u00edlia para buscar brasileiros na China |work=G1|accessdate=5 February 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200205214039/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/05/coronavirus-avioes-da-fab-decolam-em-viagem-para-buscar-brasileiros-na-china.ghtml |archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and discharged, along with the doctors and health professionals who had contact with them, on 23 February, four days earlier than predicted, as routine tests repeatedly showed negative results for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news|date=23 February 2020|url= https://www.bbc.com/portuguese/geral-51605693 |title=Coronav\u00edrus: Brasileiros s\u00e3o liberados da quarentena e deixam An\u00e1polis|work= BBC News Brasil |accessdate= 23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n* February 25,  the '''first case of COVID-19 in Brazil''' and in South America, was reported by the Health Department of S\u00e3o Paulo. <ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/02/25/ministerio-da-saude-investiga-possivel-paciente-com-coronavirus-em-sp-caso-foi-para-contraprova.ghtml |title= Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade investiga poss\u00edvel paciente com coronav\u00edrus em SP; caso foi para contraprova| work =G1|date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/equilibrioesaude/2020/02/brasil-confirma-primeiro-caso-do-novo-coronavirus.shtml|title= Brasil confirma primeiro caso do novo coronav\u00edrus|website=Folha de S. Paulo|date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n* February 28, Brazilian scientists from Adolfo Lutz Institute and the [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo]]'s Tropical Medicine Institute\u2014part of the Centre for Arbovirus Discovery, Diagnostics, Genomics & Epidemiology\u2014announced the sequencing of the COVID-19 [[genome]] of the first case reported in Brazil, in a record time of just two days.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409|title= Projecto CADDE \u2013 Primeiro genoma de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil|website= R7|date= 29 February 2020|access-date= 4 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200305042115/http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409|archive-date= 5 March 2020|url-status= live}}</ref> This discovery will assist in improving the diagnosis and control measures to curb the spread of the disease.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/28/cientistas-do-brasil-e-de-oxford-sequenciam-genoma-do-novo-coronavirus-detectado-em-sp.ghtml|title=Cientistas do Brasil e de Oxford sequenciam genoma do novo coronav\u00edrus detectado em SP|website=G1 Bem Estar|date=28 February 2020|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228213521/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/28/cientistas-do-brasil-e-de-oxford-sequenciam-genoma-do-novo-coronavirus-detectado-em-sp.ghtml|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* February 29, a second case was confirmed in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://noticias.r7.com/saude/segundo-caso-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-e-confirmado-em-sp-29022020|title= Segundo caso de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil \u00e9 confirmado em SP|website= R7|date= 29 February 2020|access-date= 29 February 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200229203856/https://noticias.r7.com/saude/segundo-caso-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-e-confirmado-em-sp-29022020|archive-date= 29 February 2020|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n=== March ===\n* March 3, the genome of COVID-19 samples from the second Brazilian case were released on the [[GISAID]] database. The analysis shows two independent introductions of the virus in Brazil from [[Northern Italy]] and have direct implications in understanding the outbreak in Italy.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409 |title= Projeto Cadde \u2013 Segundo genoma de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil |website= Virological |date= 29 February 2020 |access-date= 4 March 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200305042115/http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409 |archive-date= 5 March 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref> \n\n[[File:Pronunciamento oficial do Presidente Jair Bolsonaro sobre COVID-19.webm|thumb|right|upright=1.25|right|start=00:00|thumbtime=00:39|President [[Jair Bolsonaro]]'s official announcement about COVID-19 on March 6.]]\n\n* March 6, Brazilian scientists announced the cultivation of COVID-19 in a laboratory, with the purpose of contributing to the diagnosis and vaccines against the disease. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/pesquisadores-brasileiros-produzem-novo-coronavirus-em-laboratorio.ghtml|title=Pesquisadores brasileiros desenvolvem 'novo coronav\u00edrus' em laborat\u00f3rio; material vai ajudar no diagn\u00f3stico da doen\u00e7a|website=Bem Estar|date=6 March 2020|access-date=6 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323140422/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/pesquisadores-brasileiros-produzem-novo-coronavirus-em-laboratorio.ghtml|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: President [[Jair Bolsonaro]], said during an official announcement on television that \"there is no reason to panic\" and that people \"must strictly follow the experts recommendations as the best protective measure\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/ainda-que-o-problema-possa-se-agravar-nao-ha-motivo-para-panico-diz-bolsonaro-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Bolsonaro diz na TV que n\u00e3o h\u00e1 raz\u00e3o para p\u00e2nico ainda que problema se agrave|website=G1|date=6 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307124400/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/ainda-que-o-problema-possa-se-agravar-nao-ha-motivo-para-panico-diz-bolsonaro-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=7 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* March 12, F\u00e1bio Wajngarten, Press Secretary to President Bolsonaro, tested positive for COVID-19. As such, the president and his cabinet were being monitored. Wajngarten had also interacted with U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] and Vice President [[Mike Pence]], during Bolsonaro's visit to Miami on March 7, raising concerns that he might have infected them. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/sociedade/exame-de-fabio-wajngarten-para-coronavirus-da-positivo-24300536|title=Exame de Fabio Wajngarten para coronav\u00edrus d\u00e1 positivo|website=O Globo|date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312220550/https://oglobo.globo.com/sociedade/exame-de-fabio-wajngarten-para-coronavirus-da-positivo-24300536|archive-date=12 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: The Ministry of Health requests the approval of an additional R$10&nbsp;billion (US$2.1&nbsp;billion) in the federal budget to reinforce its fight against the disease in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.infomoney.com.br/economia/guedes-diz-que-governo-negocia-r-10-bi-para-combate-ao-coronavirus-ha-espaco-para-medidas-emergenciais/|title=Guedes diz que governo negocia R$10 bi para combate ao coronav\u00edrus: h\u00e1 espa\u00e7o para medidas emergenciais|website=Infomoney|date=12 March 2020}}</ref> It also estimated that 2,000 intensive care units will be needed to treat patients in the coming weeks.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/12/sus-preve-2-mil-leitos-de-uti-para-tratar-pacientes-com-covid-19.ghtml|title=SUS prev\u00ea 2 mil leitos de UTI para tratar pacientes com Covid-19|website=Infomoney|date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322095100/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/12/sus-preve-2-mil-leitos-de-uti-para-tratar-pacientes-com-covid-19.ghtml|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: The cruise ship ''[[Silver Shadow (ship)|Silver Shadow]]'' from [[the Bahamas]] with 318 passengers and 291 crew members, docked in [[Recife]], Pernambuco, with a suspected case of COVID-19. The ship was isolated by health authorities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/nahorah/cruzeiro-fica-em-quarentena-em-recife-apos-idoso-ser-suspeito-de-contrair-coronavirus|title=Cruzeiro fica em quarentena em Recife ap\u00f3s idoso ser suspeito de contrair coronav\u00edrus|website=Jornal de Bras\u00edlia|date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n* March 13, President Jair Bolsonaro tested negative for COVID-19. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/13/coronavirus-bolsonaro-testa-negativo-diz-perfil-do-presidente-no-facebook.htm|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Bolsonaro testa negativo para covid-19|website=UOL|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314140808/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/13/coronavirus-bolsonaro-testa-negativo-diz-perfil-do-presidente-no-facebook.htm|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://time.com/5802494/jair-bolsonaro-brazil-coronavirus|title=Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro Tests Negative for Coronavirus|website=Time|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313191155/https://time.com/5802494/jair-bolsonaro-brazil-coronavirus/|archive-date=13 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: The Ministry of Health issued a warning recommending Brazilians and foreigners arriving in Brazil to stay in isolation for at least 7 days. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/13/ministerio-da-saude-divulga-orientacoes-para-estados-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade recomenda que viajante internacional fique em casa por 7 dias ao chegar ao Brasil|website=G1|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314134057/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/13/ministerio-da-saude-divulga-orientacoes-para-estados-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: The first patient of COVID-19 in the country finally recovered. <ref>{{cite web|title=Governo anuncia que primeiro paciente com coronav\u00edrus no Brasil est\u00e1 curado|url=https://istoe.com.br/governo-anuncia-que-primeiro-paciente-com-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-curado/|date=13 March 2020|language=pt-BR|accessdate=14 March 2020|publisher=Isto\u00e9|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316063738/https://istoe.com.br/governo-anuncia-que-primeiro-paciente-com-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-curado/|archive-date=16 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> <!-- was he the first confirmed recovery ? -->\n\n* March 15, President Jair Bolsonaro, still being monitored by doctors, was heavily criticized for meeting his supporters in a public parade in Bras\u00edlia without wearing a mask. <ref name=\"auto11\">{{cite web|url=https://www.canalrural.com.br/radar/bolsonaro-tira-selfies-com-manifestantes-em-frente-ao-palacio-do-planalto-2/|title=Bolsonaro tira selfies com manifestantes em frente ao Pal\u00e1cio do Planalto|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322033033/https://www.canalrural.com.br/radar/bolsonaro-tira-selfies-com-manifestantes-em-frente-ao-palacio-do-planalto-2/|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>  <!-- should we move this to another section ? -->\n\n* March 17, the '''first coronavirus-related death was confirmed in the country''' .<ref name=\"first death\">{{cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/sao-paulo-registra-primeira-morte-por-coronavirus.shtml|title=S\u00e3o Paulo registra primeira morte por coronav\u00edrus|website=Folha de S.Paulo|date=17 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318140829/https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/sao-paulo-registra-primeira-morte-por-coronavirus.shtml|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The State of Santa Catarina declares state of emergency and starts preventive measures, including closures of non-essential shops and services (shopping malls, gyms, restaurants, hotels) and suspension of public transit, inter-city and inter-state buses, public meetings, concerts, theatres, sport events and religious services. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sc/santa-catarina/noticia/2020/03/17/governo-de-sc-decreta-situacao-de-emergencia-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml |title=Governo de SC decreta situa\u00e7\u00e3o de emerg\u00eancia por causa do coronav\u00edrus|website=G1 Santa Catarina|date=17 March 2020|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318183649/https://g1.globo.com/sc/santa-catarina/noticia/2020/03/17/governo-de-sc-decreta-situacao-de-emergencia-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that day, the [[Ministry of Health]] reported 291 confirmed cases in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus/|title=Notifica\u00e7\u00e3o de casos de doen\u00e7a pelo coronav\u00edrus 2019 (COVID-19) \u2013 Plataforma Integrada de Vigil\u00e2ncia em Sa\u00fade \u2013 Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318192904/http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus/|archive-date=18 March 2020|access-date=4 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* March 20, the health departments of the Brazilian states had reported almost a thousand confirmed cases. COVID-19 cases were confirmed in 23 states (of 26) and the Federal District. <ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/casos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-em-20-de-marco.ghtml|title=Casos de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil em 20 de mar\u00e7o|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321010341/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/casos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-em-20-de-marco.ghtml|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* March 21, the local government of the State of S\u00e3o Paulo declares a state-wide quarantine starting on March 24. The measure determined the closure of all commerce and non-essential services from that date until April 7.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n: All Brazilian states reports at least one confirmed case of COVID-19, with the last being Roraima. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gazetadopovo.com.br/republica/breves/governo-de-roraima-confirma-dois-primeiros-casos-e-todos-os-estados-do-brasil-tem-coronavirus/|title=Governo de Roraima confirma dois primeiros casos e todos os estados do Brasil t\u00eam coronav\u00edrus}}</ref>\n\n* March 24, President Jair Bolsonaro makes a third public announcement, criticizing the local governments for issuing quarantines over \"a small flu\", and blaming the media for scaring the population. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2020/03/em-pronunciamento-bolsonaro-critica-fechamento-de-escolas-ataca-governadores-e-culpa-midia.shtml|title=Em pronunciamento, Bolsonaro critica fechamento de escolas, ataca governadores e culpa m\u00eddia}}</ref>\n\n* March 26, a month after the first confirmed case in February 26, the Ministry of Health reports that Brazil has 2,915 confirmed cases and 77 deaths. <ref>{{cite web | url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/numero-infectados-coronavirus-brasil/ |title = Mortes no Brasil por coronav\u00edrus sobem 19% em um dia e chegam a 92}}</ref>\n\n* March 28, Brazil totals more than 100 confirmed deaths from COVID-19. The Ministry of Health reported on Saturday (28) that Brazil has so far registered 114 deaths and 3,904 confirmed cases of coronavirus. The mortality of COVID-19 in the country is 2.9%, according to the balance released by the folder. The survey also points out that, in the country, men die more from coronavirus than women\u201461.4% for men to 38.6% for women. Approximately 90% of deaths are people over 60 years of age. In 84% of deaths, patients had at least one risk factor. The most common, according to the Ministry, is heart disease, followed by diabetes and [[pneumopathy]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/saude/brasil-tem-114-mortes-e-3904-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-28032020|title=Brasil tem 114 mortes e 3.904 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus|date=28 March 2020|website=R7.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/28/brasil-tem-111-mortes-e-3904-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 114 mortes e 3.904 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|website=G1}}</ref>\n\n=== April ===\n* April 6, clashes between President Jair Bolsonaro and the Minister of Health, [[Luiz Henrique Mandetta]], shake the government and society. The President threatened to fire the Minister<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/blog/gerson-camarotti/post/2020/04/06/ameaca-nao-da-desabafa-mandetta-a-interlocutores.ghtml|title='Amea\u00e7a n\u00e3o d\u00e1', desabafa Mandetta em telefonemas a ministros|date=6 April 2020|website=g1.globo.com}}</ref>, but reverted it after the political opposition. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/04/06/mandetta-diz-que-continua-e-que-governo-se-reposiciona-para-enfrentar-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Mandetta diz que continua e que governo 'se reposiciona' para enfrentar coronav\u00edrus|date=6 April 2020|website=g1.globo.com}}</ref>\n\n* April 9, the federal government rolls out a project that provides financial help to those in need. On this first day, more than 2.5 million people received R$&nbsp;600 ($&nbsp;116) to cover essential needs. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/economia/noticia/2020/04/09/6-milhoes-comecam-a-receber-auxilio-emergencial-de-r-600-nesta-quinta.ghtml|title=2,5 milh\u00f5es receberam aux\u00edlio emergencial de R$ 600 nesta quinta|date=9 April 2020|website=g1.globo.com }}</ref>\n\n* April 10, Brazil confirms '''the thousandth coronavirus-related death''', as the number of confirmed cases nears 20,000. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/04/10/brasil-tem-1057-mortes-e-19638-casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 1.056 mortes e 19.638 casos confirmados de novo coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n: The virus reaches even the most remote locations, as a [[Yanomani]] teen dies in [[Roraima]] from COVID-19. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rr/roraima/noticia/2020/04/10/morre-adolescente-yanomami-infectado-pelo-coronavirus-em-roraima.ghtml|title=\u00cdndio yanomami de 15 anos morre em Roraima ap\u00f3s 6 dias na UTI|date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* April 14, '''more than 14 thousand recoveries''' are reported by the Ministry of Health, with 25,262 confirmed cases and 1,532 confirmed deaths since the beginning of the pandemic. This totals fewer than 10 thousand active cases of COVID-19 in Brazil. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/04/14/brasil-tem-1532-mortes-e-25262-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 1.532 mortes e 25.262 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* April 15, it was reported that eleven COVID-19 patients taking part in a study died after being given high doses of the anti-malarial drug [[chloroquine]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/12/health/chloroquine-coronavirus-trump.html|title=Small Chloroquine Study Halted Over Risk of Fatal Heart Complications|website= New York Times|language=en|date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* April 16, President Jair Bolsonaro fires the Minister of Health, [[Luiz Henrique Mandetta]], over disagreements on his social isolation guidelines <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/04/16/mandetta-anuncia-em-rede-social-que-foi-demitido-do-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|title=Mandetta anuncia em rede social que foi demitido por Bolsonaro do Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|date=16 April 2020}}</ref>. Shortly afterwards, [[Nelson Teich]] was appointed to replace him. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/04/16/nelson-teich-novo-ministro-da-saude-perfil.ghtml|title=Saiba quem \u00e9 Nelson Teich, novo ministro da Sa\u00fade|date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Response==\nPolicy responses and prevention announced in the country amid the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\n[[File:Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade - Livreto Plano de Contingencia Covid-19 Coronavirus 2020.pdf|thumb|Contingency plan booklet of the pandemic]]\n\n===Scientific research and forecast===\n\nOn 19 March, scientists predicted up to 2 million deaths in Brazil in the worst-case scenario without measures to contain the virus. They pointed out that a policy of [[social distancing]] is one of the most effective measures given the lack of a [[vaccine]].<ref name=\"auto10\">{{cite web|url=https://www.opovo.com.br/coronavirus/2020/03/19/cientistas-prevem-ate-2-milhoes-de-mortes-no-brasil-no-pior-cenario-sem-medidas-para-conter-o-virus.html|title=Cientistas prevem at\u00e9 2 milh\u00f5es de mortes no Brasil no pior cen\u00e1rio sem medidas para conter o v\u00edrus|first=O.|last=Povo|date=21 March 2020|website=Coronavirus|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320142716/https://www.opovo.com.br/coronavirus/2020/03/19/cientistas-prevem-ate-2-milhoes-de-mortes-no-brasil-no-pior-cenario-sem-medidas-para-conter-o-virus.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, experts from Italy warned that the coronavirus growth curve in Brazil would repeat that of European countries. An observatory with physicists from [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo|USP]], [[Unicamp]], [[Unesp]], [[UnB]], [[UFABC]], [[UC Berkeley]] and the [[University of Oldenburg]] showed that the number of infected people, considering data from March 19, had been doubling every 54 hours, and that the case total would exceed 3,000 on the 24th.<ref name=\"auto13\">{{cite web|url=https://epocanegocios.globo.com/Mundo/noticia/2020/03/curva-de-crescimento-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-repete-de-paises-europeus-alertam-especialistas-da-italia.html|title=Curva de crescimento do coronav\u00edrus no Brasil repete a de pa\u00edses europeus, alertam especialistas da It\u00e1lia|website=\u00c9poca Neg\u00f3cios|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320183307/https://epocanegocios.globo.com/Mundo/noticia/2020/03/curva-de-crescimento-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-repete-de-paises-europeus-alertam-especialistas-da-italia.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/ritmo-de-contagio-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-igual-ao-registrado-na-italia-e-acelerando-aponta-unesp.ghtml|title=Ritmo de cont\u00e1gio do coronav\u00edrus no Brasil est\u00e1 igual ao registrado na It\u00e1lia e acelerando, apontam universidades|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320173906/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/ritmo-de-contagio-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-igual-ao-registrado-na-italia-e-acelerando-aponta-unesp.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, researchers were mobilizing to increase test availability in Brazil. The [[Federal University of Rio de Janeiro]] is currently attempting to create a [[serology test]], as opposed to the more common [[PCR test]], to detect infections through a patient's blood drop.<ref name=\"auto6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/pesquisadores-se-mobilizam-para-aumentar-oferta-de-testes-no-brasil,d6a76c837c86a20c120e5d733d51a3ebrddc3q94.html|title=Pesquisadores se mobilizam para aumentar oferta de testes no Brasil|website=Terra|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321163919/https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/pesquisadores-se-mobilizam-para-aumentar-oferta-de-testes-no-brasil,d6a76c837c86a20c120e5d733d51a3ebrddc3q94.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n[[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Minister of Health]] [[Luiz Henrique Mandetta]] has said the number of cases will increase exponentially until the end of June.<ref name=\"exame\">{{cite web|url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/numero-infectados-coronavirus-brasil/|title=Brasil tem 1546 casos e 25 mortes pelo coronav\u00edrus|website=EXAME|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319232448/https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/numero-infectados-coronavirus-brasil/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, a report from [[Funda\u00e7\u00e3o Get\u00falio Vargas|FGV]] economist Emerson Mar\u00e7al predicted a negative 2020 GDP of up to 4.4% with the effect of the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://noticias.r7.com/economia/pesquisa-preve-pib-negativo-de-ate-44-com-efeito-do-coronavirus-23032020 |title=Pesquisa prev\u00ea PIB negativo de at\u00e9 4,4% com efeito do coronav\u00edrus |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324095828/https://noticias.r7.com/economia/pesquisa-preve-pib-negativo-de-ate-44-com-efeito-do-coronavirus-23032020 |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Preventive measures===\n[[File:Corpo de Bombeiros vai atuar na detec\u00e7\u00e3o de casos suspeitos - 49658924053.jpg|thumb|Brazilian firefighters will be helping in the detection of suspected cases]]\n\nOn 17 March, Brazilian authorities partially closed [[Brazil\u2013Venezuela border|their border]] with Venezuela. Health Minister Luiz Henrique Mandetta had urged closure of the border due to Venezuela's collapsing health system.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-venezuela-idUSKBN2143ZS|title=Brazil partially closing Venezuela border, allowing trucks|date=18 March 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318100317/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-venezuela-idUSKBN2143ZS|archive-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, Rio de Janeiro and five other municipalities\u2014[[S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo, Rio de Janeiro|S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo]], [[Guapimirim]], [[Niter\u00f3i]], [[Nova Igua\u00e7u]], and [[Mesquita, Rio de Janeiro|Mesquita]]\u2014in the state of Rio de Janeiro have declared an [[State of emergency|emergency state]] to help contain the coronavirus. declared emergency situations in the area of public health.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/18/prefeitura-do-rio-declara-situacao-de-emergencia.ghtml|title=Rio e outros 5 munic\u00edpios do estado declaram situa\u00e7\u00e3o de emerg\u00eancia para conter o coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319214110/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/18/prefeitura-do-rio-declara-situacao-de-emergencia.ghtml|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe following day, the government of Rio Grande do Sul declared a public calamity situation. Among the measures adopted are the prohibition of interstate travel and the restriction of items purchased in the markets.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rs/rio-grande-do-sul/noticia/2020/03/19/governo-decreta-situacao-de-calamidade-publica-no-rs-devido-ao-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Governo do RS decreta situa\u00e7\u00e3o de calamidade p\u00fablica devido ao coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175803/https://g1.globo.com/rs/rio-grande-do-sul/noticia/2020/03/19/governo-decreta-situacao-de-calamidade-publica-no-rs-devido-ao-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, it was the government of Rio Grande do Norte that declared a public calamity situation.<ref name=\"auto12\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rn/rio-grande-do-norte/noticia/2020/03/20/governo-do-rn-decreta-calamidade-publica-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Governo do RN decreta calamidade p\u00fablica por causa do coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182944/https://g1.globo.com/rn/rio-grande-do-norte/noticia/2020/03/20/governo-do-rn-decreta-calamidade-publica-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Declara\u00e7\u00f5es \u00e0 Imprensa referentes ao Corona v\u00edrus em 18 de mar\u00e7o de 2020 - Pal\u00e1cio do Planalto 44.jpg|thumb|Government declarations about the disease on the [[Pal\u00e1cio do Planalto]] ]]\n\nGovernment of Rio Grande do Norte decrees public calamity because of the coronavirus. The measure becomes effective on Friday (20), after being published in the Official Gazette of the State.<ref name=\"auto12\"/>\n\nOn 21 March, In SP, cases of coronavirus rise almost 40% in two hours. Deaths also increased in the period. Cities in the Campinas region declared an emergency situation due to the pandemic of the new coronavirus. In addition to the metropolis, Hortol\u00e2ndia, Holambra, Indaiatuba, Itapira, Jaguari\u00fana, Mogi Gua\u00e7u, Mogi Mirim, Paul\u00ednia, Sumar\u00e9 and \u00c1guas de Lindoia issued decrees with special measures to contain the progress of COVID-19 cases. Valinhos and Vinhedo determined a state of public calamity. Americana is in a state of attention.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.diariodolitoral.com.br/saude/em-sp-casos-de-coronavirus-sobem-quase-40-em-duas-horas/133224/|title=Em SP, casos de coronav\u00edrus sobem quase 40% em duas horas|website=diariodolitoral.com.br|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321170926/https://www.diariodolitoral.com.br/saude/em-sp-casos-de-coronavirus-sobem-quase-40-em-duas-horas/133224/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/campinas-regiao/noticia/2020/03/21/coronavirus-veja-lista-de-cidades-em-estado-de-emergencia-ou-calamidade-publica-e-o-que-muda-com-decretos-na-regiao-de-campinas.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: veja lista de cidades em estado de emerg\u00eancia ou calamidade p\u00fablica e o que muda com decretos na regi\u00e3o de Campinas|website=G1|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321163920/https://g1.globo.com/sp/campinas-regiao/noticia/2020/03/21/coronavirus-veja-lista-de-cidades-em-estado-de-emergencia-ou-calamidade-publica-e-o-que-muda-com-decretos-na-regiao-de-campinas.ghtml|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Prefeitura de Petr\u00f3polis - Sirenes m\u00f3veis s\u00e3o usadas para alertar popula\u00e7\u00e3o sobre perigo do Coronav\u00edrus.webm|thumb|Sirens used to warn people about the dangers of the pandemic]]\n\n===Internal policy===\n\nPresident [[Jair Bolsonaro]] has been criticized for his handling of the coronavirus crisis.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/03/coronavirus-bolsonaro-brazil-panelaco.html|title=Could the Coronavirus Topple Jair Bolsonaro?|last=Dias|first=Isabela|date=20 March 2020|website=Slate|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322031616/https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/03/coronavirus-bolsonaro-brazil-panelaco.html|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 10 March, he referred to the pandemic as a \"fantasy\" created by the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/10/bolsonaro-diz-que-questao-do-coronavirus-e-muito-mais-fantasia.ghtml|title=Bolsonaro diz que 'pequena crise' do coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 'mais fantasia' e n\u00e3o 'isso tudo' que m\u00eddia propaga|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322031617/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/10/bolsonaro-diz-que-questao-do-coronavirus-e-muito-mais-fantasia.ghtml|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, Bolsonaro, who was being monitored by doctors after his Press Secretary tested positive for COVID-19, was heavily criticized for meeting his supporters in a public parade in [[Bras\u00edlia]] without wearing a [[mask]].<ref name=\"auto11\"/> Later, impeachment cases were brought up against the [[President (government title)|President]] for his participation in the parade, which some viewed as anti-democratic, and also for posing a threat to public health.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/intervozes/coronavirus-desmascara-a-politica-de-morte-de-bolsonaro/|title=Coronav\u00edrus desmascara a pol\u00edtica de morte de Bolsonaro|date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321194634/https://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/intervozes/coronavirus-desmascara-a-politica-de-morte-de-bolsonaro/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, Bolsonaro criticized the governor of [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Wilson Witzel]] ([[Social Christian Party (Brazil)|PSC]]), for asking for the suspension of the arrival of [[flights]] from [[state (polity)|state]]s where [[contamination]] by the new coronavirus is [[confirmed]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/bolsonaro-critica-witzel-por-fechar-aeroporto-parece-que-rj-e-outro-pais.htm|title=Bolsonaro critica Witzel por querer impedir voos para o Rio de Janeiro|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320195055/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/bolsonaro-critica-witzel-por-fechar-aeroporto-parece-que-rj-e-outro-pais.htm|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBolsonaro says that closing shopping malls and commerce hurts the economy. In the midst of the COVID-19 pandemic, experts from around the world have suggested measures to restrict the circulation of individuals as one of the most efficient ways to contain the spread of the virus. However, then-president Jair Bolsonaro said on Friday (March 20th) that he was against closing of trade and market places decreed by most state governors as a measure to combat the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bnews.com.br/noticias/economia/coronavirus/262603,bolsonaro-diz-que-fechar-shoppings-e-comercio-prejudica-a-economia.html|title=Bolsonaro diz que fechar shoppings e com\u00e9rcio prejudica a economia|website=BNews|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320195057/https://www.bnews.com.br/noticias/economia/coronavirus/262603,bolsonaro-diz-que-fechar-shoppings-e-comercio-prejudica-a-economia.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe governor of [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]], Jo\u00e3o Doria, countered president Bolsonaro's supposed lack of action, by saying that state's governors are playing the role that should've be his, which is to lead [the people] amidst the pandemic of the new coronavirus. Earlier in [[Bras\u00edlia]], Bolsonaro criticized what he called \"extreme measures\", such as \"closing shopping malls and weekly outdoor markets\". He did not specifically mentioned Doria by name, but the governor of S\u00e3o Paulo defended his policies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/doria-rebate-bolsonaro-estamos-fazendo-o-que-ele-nao-faz-liderar.htm|title=Doria rebate Bolsonaro: 'estamos fazendo o que ele n\u00e3o faz, liderar'|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175802/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/doria-rebate-bolsonaro-estamos-fazendo-o-que-ele-nao-faz-liderar.htm|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBrazil is the second country with most cases of coronavirus at the executive cabinet. Just behind Iran and followed by France, the Brazilian government had at least thirteen prominent politicians contaminated. The confirmation on Thursday 18th that the Minister of Mines and Energy, Bento Albuquerque, and the [[President of the Senate]], [[Davi Alcolumbre]], contracted the new coronavirus made Brazil the second country with more cases of the disease by politicians in leading positions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://veja.abril.com.br/mundo/brasil-e-2o-pais-com-mais-casos-de-coronavirus-na-alta-cupula-do-governo/|title=Brasil \u00e9 2\u00ba pa\u00eds com mais casos de coronav\u00edrus na alta c\u00fapula do governo|website=VEJA|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320132618/https://veja.abril.com.br/mundo/brasil-e-2o-pais-com-mais-casos-de-coronavirus-na-alta-cupula-do-governo/|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, talking about Congress, Bolsonaro said they wanted to impeach him to have a confrontation.{{Clarify|date=April 2020}} The president of the Chamber of Deputies, Rodrigo Maia (DEM-RJ), and of the Senate, Davi Alcolumbre (DEM-AP), as well as the leaders of the main parties in Congress no longer believe in the possibility of productive dialogue with President Jair Bolsonaro.<ref name=\"auto9\"/>\n\nOn 23 March, Rodrigo Maia stated that Brazil might need between $78.1&nbsp;billion to combat coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-budget-idUSKBN21A3GJ|title=Brazil needs up to $78&nbsp;billion to fight coronavirus crisis \u2013 Congress leader|date=23 March 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324095115/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-budget-idUSKBN21A3GJ|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, president Bolsonaro declared that the routine in the country must return to reality and that the Brazilian press spread the panic around the coronavirus, which he called again \"little flu\". Speaking on radio and television, Bolsonaro also criticized governors for determining quarantine\u2014with trade and border closures\u2014and questioned why schools were closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/24/covid-19-bolsonaro-culpa-imprensa-por-panico-e-volta-a-falar-gripezinha.htm|title=Bolsonaro critica imprensa e fechamento de escolas e diz que crise passar\u00e1|website=noticias.uol.com.br|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/regiao-dos-lagos/noticia/2020/03/25/autoridades-no-rj-reagem-a-pronunciamento-de-bolsonaro-que-critica-confinamento-em-massa.ghtml|title=Autoridades no RJ reagem a pronunciamento de Bolsonaro que pede fim do 'confinamento em massa'|website=G1|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nPoliticians and authorities reacted to President Jair Bolsonaro's pronouncement about the coronavirus pandemic on Tuesday night (24). The president called for \"a return to normalcy\", an end to \"mass confinement\" and said that the media had spread \"dread\". Senate President Davi Alcolumbre (DEM-AP) released a note in which he classified Bolsonaro's speech as \"serious\" and said the country needs \"serious leadership\". The president of the Chamber of Deputies, Rodrigo Maia (DEM-RJ), affirmed that the statement \"was wrong when attacking the press, the governors and specialists in public health\".{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nA large number of the Brazilian politicians spoke out against this statement by the President of the Republic.{{efn|They include: [[Davi Alcolumbre]] (DEM-AP) President of the Senate, [[Rodrigo Maia]] (DEM-RJ) President of the Chamber, [[Felipe Santa Cruz]] President of the OAB, [[Gilmar Mendes]] Minister of the STF, [[Wilson Witzel]] (PSC) governor of Rio de Janeiro, [[Helder Barbalho]] (MDB) governor of Par\u00e1, [[Alexandre Frota]] (PSDB-SP) federal deputy, [[Joice Hasselmann]] (PSL-SP) federal deputy, [[Janaina Paschoal]] (PSL-SP) state deputy, [[Rodrigo Pacheco (politician)|Rodrigo Pacheco]] (DEM-MG) senator, [[Kim Kataguiri]] (DEM-SP) federal deputy, [[Jos\u00e9 Serra]] (PSDB) former Minister of Health, Jos\u00e9 Ricardo Roriz vice president of Fiesp, [[Leila Barros|Leila do V\u00f4lei]] (PSB-DF) senator, [[Renato Casagrande]] (PSB) governor of Esp\u00edrito Santo, [[Wellington Dias]] (PT), governor of Piau\u00ed, [[F\u00e1tima Bezerra]] (PT) governor of Rio Grande do Norte, [[Antonio Anastasia]] (PSD-MG) senator, [[Fernando Henrique Cardoso]] former president, [[Jo\u00e3o Amo\u00eado]] ex-president of the New Party, [[Enio Verri]] (PT-PR) federal deputy, [[Eduardo Braga]] (MDB-AM) senator, [[Humberto Costa]] (PT-PE) senator, [[Randolfe Rodrigues]] (Rede-AP) senator, [[Alessandro Molon]] (PSB-RJ) federal deputy, [[Fl\u00e1vio Dino]] (PCdoB) governor of Maranh\u00e3o, [[Jos\u00e9 Nobre Guimar\u00e3es]] (PT-CE) federal deputy, [[Rog\u00e9rio Carvalho Santos|Rog\u00e9rio Carvalho]] (PT-SE) senator, [[Fernanda Melchionna]] (PSOL-RS) federal deputy, [[Weverton Rocha]] (PDT-MA) senator, [[Marcelo Freixo]] (PSOL-RJ) federal deputy, [[Paulo Pimenta (politician)|Paulo Pimenta]] (PT -RS) federal deputy, [[Jean-Paul Prates]] (PT-RN) senator, [[Eliziane Gama]] (Cidadania-MA) senator, [[Marcelo Ramos Rodrigues|Marcelo Ramos]] (PL-AM) federal deputy, [[Arnaldo Jardim]] (Cidadania-SP) federal deputy, [[Reinaldo Azambuja]] (PSDB) governor of Mato Grosso do Sul, [[Wilson Lima]] (PSC) governor of Amazonas.<ref name=\"24globo\"/>}} The [[PSDB]], the Brazilian Press Association (ABI), the Secretaries of Health of the Northeast, the Brazilian Society of Infectology, also spoke against the president's speech. In favor of the president's speech, his two sons [[Eduardo Bolsonaro]] (no party) federal deputy and [[Fl\u00e1vio Bolsonaro]] (no party) senator, along with Vitor Hugo (PSL-GO), federal deputy, spoke.<ref name=24globo>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/24/veja-repercussao-ao-pronunciamento-de-bolsonaro-em-que-ele-pediu-volta-a-normalidade-fim-do-confinamento-e-disse-que-meios-de-comunicacao-espalharam-pavor.ghtml |title=Veja repercuss\u00e3o do pronunciamento de Bolsonaro sobre o coronav\u00edrus em que ele contrariou especialistas e pediu fim do 'confinamento em massa' |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325024638/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/24/veja-repercussao-ao-pronunciamento-de-bolsonaro-em-que-ele-pediu-volta-a-normalidade-fim-do-confinamento-e-disse-que-meios-de-comunicacao-espalharam-pavor.ghtml |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBrazilian cities register pots against Bolsonaro for the eighth consecutive day. [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Rio de Janeiro, [[Bras\u00edlia]], [[Belo Horizonte]] and [[Recife]] were some of the cities in which people threw pots during the president's speech last Tuesday (24). Brasilienses protested, against the pronouncement of the President of the Republic, Jair Bolsonaro (without party). \"Pots\" were recorded in \u00c1guas Claras, in the Southwest, in Cruzeiro, in Asa Norte, in Asa Sul and in Taguatinga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/24/cidades-brasileiras-registram-panelacos-contra-bolsonaro.ghtml |title=Cidades brasileiras registram panela\u0102\u00a7os contra Bolsonaro pelo oitavo dia seguido &#124; Pol\u0102tica &#124; G1 |publisher=G1.globo.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metropoles.com/distrito-federal/df-tem-panelaco-contra-bolsonaro-durante-pronunciamento-na-tv|title=DF tem panela\u00e7o contra Bolsonaro durante pronunciamento na TV|date=24 March 2020|website=Metr\u00f3poles}}</ref>\n\n===Foreign policy===\n\nOn 19 March, [[Eduardo Bolsonaro]], son of President Jair Bolsonaro, set off a diplomatic dispute with China, Brazil's largest trading partner, when he retweeted a message blaming the [[Communist Party of China|Chinese Communist Party]] for the virus.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/rio-reports-first-coronavirus-deaths-163812406.html Brazil coronavirus cases top 600, diplomatic spat with China bubbles] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320192215/https://news.yahoo.com/rio-reports-first-coronavirus-deaths-163812406.html |date=20 March 2020 }} By Pedro Fonseca, Reuters, 19 March 2020</ref> Yang Wanming, China's top diplomat in Brazil, later retweeted a message saying \"The Bolsonaro family is the great poison of this country.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Bolsonaro's son enrages Beijing by blaming China for coronavirus crisis |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/coronavirus-bolsonaro-son-china-row |work=The Guardian |date=19 March 2020 |access-date=22 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320190353/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/coronavirus-bolsonaro-son-china-row |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\nBolsonaro made a televised speech about the pandemic, during which both pro and anti-Bolsonaro ''[[Cacerolazo|panela\u00e7os]]'' broke out in the largest cities of Brazil.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51955679|title=Brazil coronavirus protesters urge 'Bolsonaro out'|date=19 March 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322135850/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51955679|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nAccording to one poll, 64% of Brazilians reject the way Bolsonaro has been handling the pandemic, while 44.8% support his [[impeachment]], an all-time high.<ref>[https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-19/gestao-de-bolsonaro-do-coronavirus-e-reprovada-por-64-e-45-se-dizem-a-favor-de-impeachment.html \"Gest\u00e3o de Bolsonaro do coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 reprovada por 64%, e 45% se dizem a favor de impeachment\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323021820/https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-19/gestao-de-bolsonaro-do-coronavirus-e-reprovada-por-64-e-45-se-dizem-a-favor-de-impeachment.html |date=23 March 2020 }}. ''El Pa\u00eds''. 19 March 2020.</ref>\nAccording to some sources in the Congress, Bolsonaro is shutting down political dialogue on purpose. They claim he is forcing his impeachment as a way to mobilize his supporters.<ref name=\"auto9\">{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/colunas/tales-faria/2020/03/21/para-o-congresso-bolsonaro-quer-que-tentem-impeachment-para-ter-confronto.htm|title=Para o Congresso, Bolsonaro quer que tentem impeachment para ter confronto|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321172504/https://noticias.uol.com.br/colunas/tales-faria/2020/03/21/para-o-congresso-bolsonaro-quer-que-tentem-impeachment-para-ter-confronto.htm|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Impact==\n===Economy===\nEconomists expect an [[economic stagnation]] for the country in 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://diariodocomercio.com.br/exclusivo/economia-brasileira-sofrera-forte-impacto-com-o-novo-coronavirus/|title=Economia brasileira sofrer\u00e1 forte impacto com o novo coronav\u00edrus|first=Mara|last=Bianchetti|date=21 March 2020|website=Di\u00e1rio do Com\u00e9rcio|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322062357/https://diariodocomercio.com.br/exclusivo/economia-brasileira-sofrera-forte-impacto-com-o-novo-coronavirus/|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> As such, on 16 March, the [[Ministry of Economy (Brazil)|Ministry of Economy]] announced a stimulus package of R$147.3&nbsp;billion (US$29&nbsp;billion) to help the economy against the effects of the pandemic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.poder360.com.br/economia/guedes-anuncia-pacote-de-r-147-bilhoes-para-combater-pandemia-de-covid-19/|title=Guedes anuncia pacote de R$147 bilh\u00f5es para combater pandemia de covid-19|website=Poder 360|date=16 March 2020}}</ref> The Brazilian government is also in negotiations with the [[New Development Bank]] to receive an aid package for its COVID-19 efforts; China received one billion USD from the same institution.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/banco-de-desenvolvimento-do-brics-libera-ajuda-de-r-5-bilhoes-a-china,9bc26d72a411019e55adb6bdd0a3094asut8ttyw.html|title=Banco de Desenvolvimento do BRICS libera ajuda de R$5 bilh\u00f5es \u00e0 China|website=Terra|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321195758/https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/banco-de-desenvolvimento-do-brics-libera-ajuda-de-r-5-bilhoes-a-china,9bc26d72a411019e55adb6bdd0a3094asut8ttyw.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, Economy Minister [[Paulo Guedes]] announced a series of aid measures to reduce the impact on the economy that will be caused by COVID-19. A scholarship for self-employed professionals, in the amount of R$200, is being prepared, in addition to the payment guarantee for workers who have reduced working hours.<ref name=\"exame\"/>\n\nOn 23 March, government announces package of R$85.8 billion for states and municipalities. Amount involves transfers to the health area, recomposition of transfers of constitutional funds and suspension of the maturity of debts of the states with the Union.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/economia/noticia/2020/03/23/coronavirus-governo-anuncia-pacote-de-r-858-bilhoes-para-estados-e-municipios.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: governo anuncia pacote de R$ 85,8 bilh\u00f5es para estados e munic\u00edpios|website=G1}}</ref>\n\n===Education===\nOn 20 March, The pandemic has [[impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education|impacted education all over the world]]. In over a hundred countries, there were nationwide school closures. However, President Jair Bolsonaro has issued few country-wide measures to slow the spread of the virus,<ref name=\":17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200316-as-latin-america-takes-steps-to-counter-coronavirus-brazil-s-bolsonaro-snubs-warnings|title=Latin America takes steps to counter coronavirus, Brazil's Bolsonaro snubs warnings|date=16 March 2020|publisher=France 24|access-date=16 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320165406/https://www.france24.com/en/20200316-as-latin-america-takes-steps-to-counter-coronavirus-brazil-s-bolsonaro-snubs-warnings|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-panama-idUSKBN20Y3FA|title=Latin American countries order school closures over coronavirus fears|date=12 March 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=16 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320165410/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-panama-idUSKBN20Y3FA|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and because the federal government decided not to cancel classes in the whole country, lower levels of government have done so on independently. As such, municipal, state, and private schools and universities had different reactions regarding the suspension of classes. Classes were suspended at once, gradually or not at all. Some of them were replaced with [[distance education]] or simply postponed. Because of that, there are only \"localized\" (as opposed to \"national\") school closures, according to [[UNESCO]].<ref name=\"UNESCO\">{{cite web|url=https://en.unesco.org/themes/education-emergencies/coronavirus-school-closures|title=COVID-19 Educational Disruption and Response|publisher=UNESCO|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321000612/https://en.unesco.org/themes/education-emergencies/coronavirus-school-closures|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Favelas===\n\nOn 17 March, Residents of [[favelas]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]] suffer from a lack of water amid the coronavirus pandemic. [[Cariocas]] and fluminenses are much more exposed to the proliferation of coronavirus without having water for cleaning, says a specialist. In parts of the [[Baixada Fluminense]] and the [[North]] Zone of [[Rio de Janeiro]] the water does not reach. Among the affected areas are: Chatuba de [[Mesquita, Rio de Janeiro|Mesquita]], Camarista, [[M\u00e9ier]] and [[Complexo do Alem\u00e3o]] communities. The infectious disease doctor and pediatrician Cristiana Meirelles says that without clean running water, the situation of fighting the epidemic becomes catastrophic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/17/moradores-de-comunidades-do-rj-sofrem-com-falta-de-agua-em-meio-a-pandemia-de-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Moradores de comunidades do RJ sofrem com falta de \u00e1gua em meio \u00e0 pandemia de coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319211134/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/17/moradores-de-comunidades-do-rj-sofrem-com-falta-de-agua-em-meio-a-pandemia-de-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nCufa calls for measures to contain coronavirus in favelas. Government actions do not include the economically fragile, a contingent that totals more than 70 million people, says the organization.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/cufa-pede-medidas-para-conter-o-coronavirus-nas-favelas/|title=Cufa pede medidas para conter o coronav\u00edrus nas favelas|website=EXAME|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321203956/https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/cufa-pede-medidas-para-conter-o-coronavirus-nas-favelas/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSome areas of Mar\u00e9 had been without water for two days, and other areas reported have been without water for two weeks.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://s2.glbimg.com/_pbfQW3RR8K11JBZvO2u590X8FM=/0x41:720x861/1600x0/smart/filters:strip_icc()/i.s3.glbimg.com/v1/AUTH_59edd422c0c84a879bd37670ae4f538a/internal_photos/bs/2020/v/O/AA9BvNRQSiodWbwzkd2w/jacarezinho.jfif |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324094915/https://s2.glbimg.com/_pbfQW3RR8K11JBZvO2u590X8FM%3D/0x41:720x861/1600x0/smart/filters:strip_icc()/i.s3.glbimg.com/v1/AUTH_59edd422c0c84a879bd37670ae4f538a/internal_photos/bs/2020/v/O/AA9BvNRQSiodWbwzkd2w/jacarezinho.jfif |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-tem-63-casos-suspeitos-do-novo-coronavirus.ghtml |title=Favelas do Rio t\u00eam 61 casos suspeitos do novo coronav\u00edrus, segundo Secretaria de Sa\u00fade |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324154450/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-tem-63-casos-suspeitos-do-novo-coronavirus.ghtml |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brasildefato.com.br/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-sofrem-com-falta-d-agua-e-populacao-fica-mais-vulneravel-a-coronavirus |title=Favelas do Rio sofrem com falta d'\u00e1gua e popula\u00e7\u00e3o fica mais vulner\u00e1vel a coronav\u00edrus |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324094920/https://www.brasildefato.com.br/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-sofrem-com-falta-d-agua-e-populacao-fica-mais-vulneravel-a-coronavirus |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Healthcare===\n\n[[File:Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade -01- Boletim Infec\u00e7\u00e3o Humana pelo Novo Coronav\u00edrus 2019-nCoV.pdf|thumb|Ministry of Health -01- Bulletin of Human infection for the Noval Coronavirus 2019-nCoV]]\n\nSince the first cases were reported in the country, there were concerns if its [[Sistema \u00danico de Sa\u00fade|healthcare system]] would be able to deal with the pandemic.\n\nOn 18 March, hospitals in [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]] denounced a lack of health materials, such as masks, gloves and [[hand sanitizer]], caused by an in an increase in prices.<ref name=\"auto8\">{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/saude/ultimas-noticias/redacao/2020/03/19/funcionarios-relatam-falta-de-alcool-gel-e-luvas-em-hospitais-de-sao-paulo.htm|title=Funcion\u00e1rios relatam falta de \u00e1lcool gel e luvas em hospitais de S\u00e3o Paulo|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175759/https://noticias.uol.com.br/saude/ultimas-noticias/redacao/2020/03/19/funcionarios-relatam-falta-de-alcool-gel-e-luvas-em-hospitais-de-sao-paulo.htm|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto7\">{{cite web|url=https://brasil.elpais.com/sociedade/2020-03-20/profissionais-relatam-precariedade-contra-coronavirus-no-sus-paciente-fica-exposto-e-nos-tambem.html|title=Profissionais relatam precariedade contra coronav\u00edrus no SUS: \"Paciente fica exposto, e n\u00f3s tamb\u00e9m\"|first=Joana|last=Oliveira|date=20 March 2020|website=EL PA\u00cdS|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182411/https://brasil.elpais.com/sociedade/2020-03-20/profissionais-relatam-precariedade-contra-coronavirus-no-sus-paciente-fica-exposto-e-nos-tambem.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> According to them, packages of masks went from R$4.50 in January to R$140 on 17 March. The government said it will negotiate with the industry to meet the demand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/coronavirus-hospitais-de-sp-denunciam-falta-de-materiais-e-aumento-de-ate-30-vezes-nos-precos.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Hospitais de SP denunciam falta de materiais e aumento de at\u00e9 30 vezes nos pre\u00e7os|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175759/https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/coronavirus-hospitais-de-sp-denunciam-falta-de-materiais-e-aumento-de-ate-30-vezes-nos-precos.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/brasil/coronavirus-caixa-de-mascara-sobe-de-r-450-para-r-140-denunciam-hospitais/|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Caixa de m\u00e1scara sobe de R$ 4,50 para R$ 140, denunciam Hospitais|first=Reda\u00e7\u00e3o Jornal de|last=Bras\u00edlia|date=18 March 2020|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175758/https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/brasil/coronavirus-caixa-de-mascara-sobe-de-r-450-para-r-140-denunciam-hospitais/|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]], there was an outage of masks and hand sanitizer in the local commerce.<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bahianoticias.com.br/noticia/245528-mascaras-para-profissionais-de-saude-esgotam-em-salvador-e-ambulantes-aproveitam.html|title=M\u00e1scaras para profissionais de sa\u00fade esgotam em Salvador e ambulantes 'aproveitam'|website=bahianoticias.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182417/https://www.bahianoticias.com.br/noticia/245528-mascaras-para-profissionais-de-saude-esgotam-em-salvador-e-ambulantes-aproveitam.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nRio and five other municipalities in the state declare an emergency to contain the coronavirus. Municipalities of [[S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo, Rio de Janeiro|S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo]] and [[Guapimirim]] also declared a state of emergency and [[Niter\u00f3i]], [[Nova Igua\u00e7u]] and Mesquita declared an emergency situation in the area of public health.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nOn 19 March, scientists predicted up to 2&nbsp;million deaths in Brazil in the worst scenario without measures to contain the coronavirus. They point out that maintaining social distance is one of the most effective measures without a vaccine.<ref name=\"auto10\"/> Their conclusion came after analyzing the [[Growth curve (statistics)|growth curve]] of COVID-19 cases in Brazil. The contagion rate is the same as that registered in Italy, as the number of infected people has been doubling every 54 hours. According to estimates, the number of confirmed cases might reach 3,000 by 24 March.<ref name=\"auto13\"/> According to the Ministry of Health, the number of infected patients will grow [[Exponential growth|exponentially]] by the end of June.<ref name=\"exame\"/> The mayor of [[Belo Horizonte]], [[Alexandre Kalil]] (PSD), asked General Altair Jos\u00e9 Polsin, commander of the 4th Army Region, for the temporary assignment of 51 professionals from the army garrison to assist in the demands of fighting the coronavirus. The Brazilian Army has not yet said whether it will meet this demand. Peak cases of COVID-19 in BH will be in the first week of April. In an interview, the health secretary announced the creation of two more Respiratory Disease centers and is studying placing PMs to serve the population.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/minas-gerais/pico-de-casos-de-covid-19-em-bh-sera-na-1-semana-de-abril-19032020|title=Pico de casos de Covid-19 em BH ser\u00e1 na 1\u00aa semana de abril|date=19 March 2020|website=R7.com|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322190809/https://noticias.r7.com/minas-gerais/pico-de-casos-de-covid-19-em-bh-sera-na-1-semana-de-abril-19032020|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/mg/minas-gerais/noticia/2020/03/19/coronavirus-prefeitura-de-bh-pede-reforco-de-medicos-ao-exercito.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Prefeitura de BH pede refor\u00e7o do Ex\u00e9rcito para o atendimento da sa\u00fade|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320173852/https://g1.globo.com/mg/minas-gerais/noticia/2020/03/19/coronavirus-prefeitura-de-bh-pede-reforco-de-medicos-ao-exercito.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n\nThe Government of [[Rio Grande do Sul]] decreed a public calamity situation, with measures including the prohibition of interstate travel and the restriction of items purchased in the markets, with the decree in force from 19 March.<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\nEmployees at four public hospitals in the city of S\u00e3o Paulo reported a shortage of materials such as alcohol gel, masks and gloves when caring for patients with suspected coronavirus. Professionals in the [[Sistema \u00danico de Sa\u00fade]] (SUS) reported a shortage of masks and rationing of gel alcohol, though the situation of public service workers is different from{{how|date=April 2020}} that of private hospitals in S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref name=\"auto8\"/><ref name=\"auto7\"/>\nStores specializing in medical supplies no longer had alcohol gels and masks, including [[N95 mask]]s used by health professionals. Street vendors were reported to be taking advantage of the demand for equipment and trying to profit from it.<ref name=\"auto4\"/>\n\n[[File:Capacita\u00e7\u00e3o dos profissionais da Sa\u00fade que atuar\u00e3o nos terminais de \u00f4nibus - 49667698972.jpg|thumb|Health professionals clean up public transport to prevent spread]]\n\nOn 20 March, it was reported by the press that Brazil was contradicting the recommendation of the [[World Health Organization]] by only testing patients in severe condition. Jo\u00e3o Gabbardo, executive secretary at the Ministry of Health, said that the criteria adopted would not change, and people with serious cases will be tested for COVID-19.<ref name=\"auto2\"/> The following day, a group of scientists announced they were developing new COVID-19 tests in Brazil. They expect to elaborate a test which will work with a single drop of blood from the patient. They expect it to be ready for the current outbreak of COVID-19, and hope to engage some of the main Brazilian universities in its development.<ref name=\"auto6\"/>\nWithout protective items, health workers improvise caps like masks in hospitals. In addition to the first cases of coronavirus in Acre, health professionals in the state have to deal with the lack of Personal Protective Equipment (PPE). Some agents are improvising caps like masks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://istoe.com.br/sem-itens-de-protecao-agentes-de-saude-improvisam-toucas-como-mascaras-em-hospitais/|title=Sem itens de prote\u00e7\u00e3o, agentes de sa\u00fade improvisam toucas como m\u00e1scaras em hospitais|date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nHealth professionals in RJ complain about the lack of conditions to work with patients in COVID-19. Doctor says there are no N95 masks, with more efficient filter, at Hospital Salgado Filho. Unions say there is a shortage of personal protective equipment in hospitals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/20/profissionais-de-saude-do-rj-reclamam-da-falta-de-condicoes-para-trabalhar-com-pacientes-de-covid-19.ghtml|title=Profissionais de sa\u00fade do RJ reclamam da falta de condi\u00e7\u00f5es para trabalhar com pacientes de Covid-19|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182757/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/20/profissionais-de-saude-do-rj-reclamam-da-falta-de-condicoes-para-trabalhar-com-pacientes-de-covid-19.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Religious services===\n[[Odilo Scherer|Dom Odilo Scherer]], [[archdiocese of S\u00e3o Paulo|Archbishop of S\u00e3o Paulo]] had initially defended that churches should not be closed, arguing that there should be more daily services to diffuse large gatherings. Later, he determined the suspension of celebrations with the people.<ref name=igrejas/><ref>{{cite web|title=Comunicado sobre a suspens\u00e3o tempor\u00e1ria de Celebra\u00e7\u00f5es Religiosas|url=http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-sobre-a-suspensao-temporaria-de-celebracoes-religiosas|date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326200303/http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-sobre-a-suspensao-temporaria-de-celebracoes-religiosas|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Comunicado n\u00b02 da Arquidiocese de S\u00e3o Paulo sobre Celebra\u00e7\u00f5es e outras A\u00e7\u00f5es Pastorais nas igrejas durante a pandemia do Coronav\u00edrus|url=http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-ndeg2-da-arquidiocese-de-sao-paulo-sobre-celebracoes-e-outras-acoes-pastorais-nas-igrejas-durante-a-pandemia-do-coronavirus|date=26 March 2020|access-date=28 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331203026/http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-ndeg2-da-arquidiocese-de-sao-paulo-sobre-celebracoes-e-outras-acoes-pastorais-nas-igrejas-durante-a-pandemia-do-coronavirus|archive-date=31 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Bishop [[Edir Macedo]], founder of the [[Universal Church of the Kingdom of God]] has also defended that services should not be suspended, as well as [[Silas Malafaia]], leader of [[Assembleias de Deus|Assembleia de Deus Vit\u00f3ria em Cristo]].<ref name=igrejas>{{cite web|url=https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-20/igrejas-desafiam-recomendacao-de-suspender-missas-e-cultos-diante-da-pandemia-do-coronavirus.html|title=Igrejas desafiam recomenda\u00e7\u00e3o de suspender missas e cultos diante da pandemia do coronav\u00edrus|first=Breiller|last=Pires|date=20 March 2020|website=EL PA\u00cdS|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321155318/https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-20/igrejas-desafiam-recomendacao-de-suspender-missas-e-cultos-diante-da-pandemia-do-coronavirus.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Malafaia said he would only close his churches if mandated by a court order. Macedo has caused greater controversy after he dismissed coronavirus as a creation of the media.<ref>{{cite web|title=M\u00f4nica Bergamo: V\u00eddeo mostra Edir Macedo dizendo que coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 inofensivo e que Satan\u00e1s e m\u00eddia promovem medo|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/video-mostra-edir-macedo-dizendo-que-coronavirus-e-inofensivo-e-que-satanas-e-midia-promovem-medo.shtml|date=15 March 2020|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064430/https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/video-mostra-edir-macedo-dizendo-que-coronavirus-e-inofensivo-e-que-satanas-e-midia-promovem-medo.shtml|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Television programming===\nBrazilian networks started airing prevention tips during their programming. [[Rede Globo|Globo]], [[Sistema Brasileiro de Televis\u00e3o|SBT]], [[RecordTV]], [[Rede Bandeirantes|Band]], and [[RedeTV!]] announced they would stop production of all of their ''[[telenovelas]]'', and would record their [[talk shows]] without a live audience, while expanding journalism in their programming.<ref>{{cite web | last=Padiglione | first=Cristina | title=Em razao do coronavirus, Domingao do Faustao vai ao ar sem plateia pela 1 vez em 31 anos | publisher=[[Folha de S.Paulo]] | date=12 March 2020 | url=https://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/em-razao-coronavirus-domingao-faustao-vai-ao-ar-sem-plateia-pela-1a-vez-em-31-anos | accessdate=13 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064434/https://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/em-razao-coronavirus-domingao-faustao-vai-ao-ar-sem-plateia-pela-1a-vez-em-31-anos | archive-date=22 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Oliveira | first=Fernando | title=Com medo do coronavirus, Raul Gil cancela grava\u00c7ao e se isola em sitio | publisher=[[Universo Online|UOL]] | date=13 March 2020 | url=https://tvefamosos.uol.com.br/colunas/fefito/2020/03/13/com-medo-do-coronavirus-raul-gil-se-isola-em-sitio.html | accessdate=13 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064431/https://tvefamosos.uol.com.br/colunas/fefito/2020/03/13/com-medo-do-coronavirus-raul-gil-se-isola-em-sitio.html | archive-date=22 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=RedeTV! cancela plateia do Encrenca com medo do surto de coronavirus | publisher=[[Universo Online|Noticias da TV \u2013 UOL]] | date=12 March 2020 | url=https://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/televisao/redetv-cancela-plateia-do-encrenca-com-medo-do-surto-de-coronavirus-34432 | accessdate=13 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064431/https://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/televisao/redetv-cancela-plateia-do-encrenca-com-medo-do-surto-de-coronavirus-34432 | archive-date=22 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n \n\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil/Statistics}}\n{{:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil/Statistics}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.saude.gov.br/saude-de-a-z/coronavirus COVID-19 in Brazil] \u2013 Ministry of Health\n* {{cite web |url=https://coronavirus-global.com/brazil |title=Coronavirus Brazil updates and news |trans-title=Latest news and statistics of coronavirus in Brazil. |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=English, French, Spanish, Portuguese, German, Italian, Swedish, Norwegian, Finnish, Estonian, Russian}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Brazil|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Brazil]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in South America|Brazil]]\n[[Category:2020 in Brazil|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health disasters in Brazil|Coronavirus]]\n", "text_old": "{{currentevent|date=April 2020}}\n{{Cleanup translation|Portuguese}}\n{{Cleanup rewrite|[[WP:NOTNEWS|Wikipedia is not a newspaper]]|date=April 2020}}\n{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use American English|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Brazil}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Brazil.svg\n| legend1         = Map of states with confirmed coronavirus cases (as of 16 April)\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Brazil]]\n| first_case      = [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| arrival_date    = 26 February 2020<br/>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=2|day1=25|year1=2020}})\n| origin          = [[Lombardy]], Italy<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/02/25/ministerio-da-saude-investiga-possivel-paciente-com-coronavirus-em-sp-caso-foi-para-contraprova.ghtml|title=Painel Coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n| recovery_cases  = \n| deaths          = 2,507<ref name=Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade/>\n| confirmed_cases = 39,548<ref name=\"Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade\">{{cite web |url=https://covid.saude.gov.br/ |title=Painel Coronav\u00edrus |language=Portuguese |work=Ministry of Health |access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n| total_ili       =  <!-- P.s: Several states in the country confirmed cases after the closure of the Ministry of Health. Brazil is a Federative Republic, divided into 27 federative units, of which confirm results before the federal government. -->\n| website         = {{URL|https://coronavirus.saude.gov.br/}}\n}}\n\nThe ongoing [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|pandemic]] of [[COVID-19|coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19) was confirmed to have spread to [[Brazil]] on 25 February 2020,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46435-brasil-confirma-primeiro-caso-de-novo-coronavirus|title=Brasil confirma primeiro caso da doen\u00e7a|date=26 February 2020|website=Ministerio da Saude|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306155723/https://www.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/46435-brasil-confirma-primeiro-caso-de-novo-coronavirus|archive-date=6 March 2020|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref> after a 61-year-old man from [[S\u00e3o Paulo]] who had returned from [[Lombardy]], Italy tested positive for the virus. As of 19 April 2020, 38,654 cases have been confirmed in the country, causing 2,462 deaths.<ref name=\"Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade\"/>\n\nThe pandemic has triggered a variety of responses from federal, state and local governments, with an impact on politics, education and the economy. On 27 March Brazil announced a temporary ban on foreign air travelers,<ref>{{cite web |author1=Pedro Fonseca |author2=Jamie McGeever |title=Coronavirus: Brazil bans foreign air travelers |url=https://www.mercurynews.com/2020/03/27/coronavirus-brazil-bans-foreign-air-travelers/ |website=The Mercury News |accessdate=13 April 2020 |date=28 March 2020}}</ref> and most state governors have imposed [[Quarantine|quarantines]] to prevent the spread of the [[SARS-CoV-2|virus]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Brazil reports more than 1,000 coronavirus deaths |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-52251342 |website=BBC News |publisher=BBC |accessdate=13 April 2020 |date=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=\"Elsevier\">{{cite web|url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center|last=Elsevier|date=|website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Reynolds4March2020\">{{Cite news|last=Reynolds|first=Matt|url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic?|date=4 March 2020|work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|issn=1357-0978}}</ref>\n\nUnlike [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]], the [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 <ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\">{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus|website=Imperial News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Gov.ukHCIDDef\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England|last=|first=|date=|website=GOV.UK|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> has been much lower, but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=\"WFSA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus|last=|first=|date=|website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Imperial13March2020\" />\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Brazil medical cases chart}}\n\n=== January ===\n* January 28, the [[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Ministry of Health]] (''Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade'') raised the emergency alert to level 2 of 3, considering an \"imminent threat\" for Brazil, as a suspected case was being investigated in [[Belo Horizonte]], Minas Gerais.<ref>{{Cite news |url= https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-caso-suspeito-de-coronavirus-em-mg.ghtml |title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade investiga caso suspeito de coronav\u00edrus em MG |last= Cruz |first= Carolina |date= 28 January 2020 |accessdate=28 January 2020 | work = G1 |language= pt-br |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200128142750/https://g1.globo.com/ciencia-e-saude/noticia/2020/01/28/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-caso-suspeito-de-coronavirus-em-mg.ghtml |archive-date=28 January 2020 |url-status= live}}</ref> \n\n* January 29, the Ministry announced it was investigating two other suspected cases, in [[Porto Alegre]] and [[Curitiba]]. No further information was given about the patients in Porto Alegre and Curitiba. However, it was informed that the Belo Horizonte patient was a student that had recently visited [[Wuhan]], China, point of origin of the outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-3-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil/|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade confirma 3 casos suspeitos de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil|date=28 January 2020|publisher=Exame Abril|accessdate=29 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200129042253/https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/ministerio-da-saude-confirma-3-casos-suspeitos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil/|archive-date=29 January 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== February ===\n* February 3, the Minister of Health [[Luiz Henrique Mandetta]] said that the Brazilian government would declare a [[Public Health Emergency of International Concern]], even without confirmed cases in the country. He also said the government would assist on the return of Brazilians from Wuhan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/03/nao-gosto-de-trabalhar-com-prazo-diz-ministro-da-saude-sobre-repatriacao-de-brasileiros-de-wuhan.ghtml|title=Pa\u00eds adotar\u00e1 emerg\u00eancia para retirar cidad\u00e3os de \u00e1rea de surto de coronav\u00edrus, diz ministro|date=3 February 2020|publisher=G1|accessdate=3 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203161354/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/03/nao-gosto-de-trabalhar-com-prazo-diz-ministro-da-saude-sobre-repatriacao-de-brasileiros-de-wuhan.ghtml|archive-date=3 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n* February 4, the Ministry confirmed that around 30 Brazilians were in Wuhan, and that they would return to the country on 8 February. It was also announced that they would be [[quarantine]]d for 18 days in [[An\u00e1polis]], Goi\u00e1s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/04/coronavirus-brasileiros-na-china-devem-chegar-ao-pais-no-sabado-e-cumprir-quarentena-em-anapolis.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: brasileiros na China devem chegar ao pa\u00eds no s\u00e1bado e cumprir quarentena em An\u00e1polis|date=4 February 2020|publisher=G1|accessdate=4 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205010554/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/04/coronavirus-brasileiros-na-china-devem-chegar-ao-pais-no-sabado-e-cumprir-quarentena-em-anapolis.ghtml|archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* February 5, the Brazilian government sent two planes to evacuate 34 Brazilians from [[Wuhan]]. They and the flight crew were quarantined at a [[Brazilian Air Force]] base in An\u00e1polis,<ref>{{cite news|first1=Pedro Henrique|last1=Gomes|date=5 February 2020 |url= https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/05/coronavirus-avioes-da-fab-decolam-em-viagem-para-buscar-brasileiros-na-china.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: avi\u00f5es da FAB decolam de Bras\u00edlia para buscar brasileiros na China |work=G1|accessdate=5 February 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200205214039/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/02/05/coronavirus-avioes-da-fab-decolam-em-viagem-para-buscar-brasileiros-na-china.ghtml |archive-date=5 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and discharged, along with the doctors and health professionals who had contact with them, on 23 February, four days earlier than predicted, as routine tests repeatedly showed negative results for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{cite news|date=23 February 2020|url= https://www.bbc.com/portuguese/geral-51605693 |title=Coronav\u00edrus: Brasileiros s\u00e3o liberados da quarentena e deixam An\u00e1polis|work= BBC News Brasil |accessdate= 23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n* February 25,  the '''first case of COVID-19 in Brazil''' and in South America, was reported by the Health Department of S\u00e3o Paulo. <ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/02/25/ministerio-da-saude-investiga-possivel-paciente-com-coronavirus-em-sp-caso-foi-para-contraprova.ghtml |title= Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade investiga poss\u00edvel paciente com coronav\u00edrus em SP; caso foi para contraprova| work =G1|date=25 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/equilibrioesaude/2020/02/brasil-confirma-primeiro-caso-do-novo-coronavirus.shtml|title= Brasil confirma primeiro caso do novo coronav\u00edrus|website=Folha de S. Paulo|date=25 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n* February 28, Brazilian scientists from Adolfo Lutz Institute and the [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo]]'s Tropical Medicine Institute\u2014part of the Centre for Arbovirus Discovery, Diagnostics, Genomics & Epidemiology\u2014announced the sequencing of the COVID-19 [[genome]] of the first case reported in Brazil, in a record time of just two days.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409|title= Projecto CADDE \u2013 Primeiro genoma de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil|website= R7|date= 29 February 2020|access-date= 4 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200305042115/http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409|archive-date= 5 March 2020|url-status= live}}</ref> This discovery will assist in improving the diagnosis and control measures to curb the spread of the disease.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/28/cientistas-do-brasil-e-de-oxford-sequenciam-genoma-do-novo-coronavirus-detectado-em-sp.ghtml|title=Cientistas do Brasil e de Oxford sequenciam genoma do novo coronav\u00edrus detectado em SP|website=G1 Bem Estar|date=28 February 2020|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228213521/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/02/28/cientistas-do-brasil-e-de-oxford-sequenciam-genoma-do-novo-coronavirus-detectado-em-sp.ghtml|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* February 29, a second case was confirmed in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://noticias.r7.com/saude/segundo-caso-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-e-confirmado-em-sp-29022020|title= Segundo caso de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil \u00e9 confirmado em SP|website= R7|date= 29 February 2020|access-date= 29 February 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200229203856/https://noticias.r7.com/saude/segundo-caso-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-e-confirmado-em-sp-29022020|archive-date= 29 February 2020|url-status= live}}</ref>\n\n=== March ===\n* March 3, the genome of COVID-19 samples from the second Brazilian case were released on the [[GISAID]] database. The analysis shows two independent introductions of the virus in Brazil from [[Northern Italy]] and have direct implications in understanding the outbreak in Italy.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409 |title= Projeto Cadde \u2013 Segundo genoma de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil |website= Virological |date= 29 February 2020 |access-date= 4 March 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200305042115/http://virological.org/t/first-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-covid-19-in-brazil-south-america-2-genomes-3rd-march-2020/409 |archive-date= 5 March 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref> \n\n[[File:Pronunciamento oficial do Presidente Jair Bolsonaro sobre COVID-19.webm|thumb|right|upright=1.25|right|start=00:00|thumbtime=00:39|President [[Jair Bolsonaro]]'s official announcement about COVID-19 on March 6.]]\n\n* March 6, Brazilian scientists announced the cultivation of COVID-19 in a laboratory, with the purpose of contributing to the diagnosis and vaccines against the disease. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/pesquisadores-brasileiros-produzem-novo-coronavirus-em-laboratorio.ghtml|title=Pesquisadores brasileiros desenvolvem 'novo coronav\u00edrus' em laborat\u00f3rio; material vai ajudar no diagn\u00f3stico da doen\u00e7a|website=Bem Estar|date=6 March 2020|access-date=6 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323140422/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/pesquisadores-brasileiros-produzem-novo-coronavirus-em-laboratorio.ghtml|archive-date=23 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: President [[Jair Bolsonaro]], said during an official announcement on television that \"there is no reason to panic\" and that people \"must strictly follow the experts recommendations as the best protective measure\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/ainda-que-o-problema-possa-se-agravar-nao-ha-motivo-para-panico-diz-bolsonaro-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Bolsonaro diz na TV que n\u00e3o h\u00e1 raz\u00e3o para p\u00e2nico ainda que problema se agrave|website=G1|date=6 March 2020|access-date=7 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307124400/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/06/ainda-que-o-problema-possa-se-agravar-nao-ha-motivo-para-panico-diz-bolsonaro-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=7 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* March 12, F\u00e1bio Wajngarten, Press Secretary to President Bolsonaro, tested positive for COVID-19. As such, the president and his cabinet were being monitored. Wajngarten had also interacted with U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] and Vice President [[Mike Pence]], during Bolsonaro's visit to Miami on March 7, raising concerns that he might have infected them. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://oglobo.globo.com/sociedade/exame-de-fabio-wajngarten-para-coronavirus-da-positivo-24300536|title=Exame de Fabio Wajngarten para coronav\u00edrus d\u00e1 positivo|website=O Globo|date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312220550/https://oglobo.globo.com/sociedade/exame-de-fabio-wajngarten-para-coronavirus-da-positivo-24300536|archive-date=12 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: The Ministry of Health requests the approval of an additional R$10&nbsp;billion (US$2.1&nbsp;billion) in the federal budget to reinforce its fight against the disease in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.infomoney.com.br/economia/guedes-diz-que-governo-negocia-r-10-bi-para-combate-ao-coronavirus-ha-espaco-para-medidas-emergenciais/|title=Guedes diz que governo negocia R$10 bi para combate ao coronav\u00edrus: h\u00e1 espa\u00e7o para medidas emergenciais|website=Infomoney|date=12 March 2020}}</ref> It also estimated that 2,000 intensive care units will be needed to treat patients in the coming weeks.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/12/sus-preve-2-mil-leitos-de-uti-para-tratar-pacientes-com-covid-19.ghtml|title=SUS prev\u00ea 2 mil leitos de UTI para tratar pacientes com Covid-19|website=Infomoney|date=12 March 2020|access-date=12 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322095100/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/12/sus-preve-2-mil-leitos-de-uti-para-tratar-pacientes-com-covid-19.ghtml|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: The cruise ship ''[[Silver Shadow (ship)|Silver Shadow]]'' from [[the Bahamas]] with 318 passengers and 291 crew members, docked in [[Recife]], Pernambuco, with a suspected case of COVID-19. The ship was isolated by health authorities.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/nahorah/cruzeiro-fica-em-quarentena-em-recife-apos-idoso-ser-suspeito-de-contrair-coronavirus|title=Cruzeiro fica em quarentena em Recife ap\u00f3s idoso ser suspeito de contrair coronav\u00edrus|website=Jornal de Bras\u00edlia|date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n* March 13, President Jair Bolsonaro tested negative for COVID-19. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/13/coronavirus-bolsonaro-testa-negativo-diz-perfil-do-presidente-no-facebook.htm|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Bolsonaro testa negativo para covid-19|website=UOL|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314140808/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/13/coronavirus-bolsonaro-testa-negativo-diz-perfil-do-presidente-no-facebook.htm|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://time.com/5802494/jair-bolsonaro-brazil-coronavirus|title=Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro Tests Negative for Coronavirus|website=Time|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313191155/https://time.com/5802494/jair-bolsonaro-brazil-coronavirus/|archive-date=13 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: The Ministry of Health issued a warning recommending Brazilians and foreigners arriving in Brazil to stay in isolation for at least 7 days. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/13/ministerio-da-saude-divulga-orientacoes-para-estados-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade recomenda que viajante internacional fique em casa por 7 dias ao chegar ao Brasil|website=G1|date=13 March 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314134057/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/13/ministerio-da-saude-divulga-orientacoes-para-estados-sobre-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=14 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n: The first patient of COVID-19 in the country finally recovered. <ref>{{cite web|title=Governo anuncia que primeiro paciente com coronav\u00edrus no Brasil est\u00e1 curado|url=https://istoe.com.br/governo-anuncia-que-primeiro-paciente-com-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-curado/|date=13 March 2020|language=pt-BR|accessdate=14 March 2020|publisher=Isto\u00e9|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316063738/https://istoe.com.br/governo-anuncia-que-primeiro-paciente-com-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-curado/|archive-date=16 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> <!-- was he the first confirmed recovery ? -->\n\n* March 15, President Jair Bolsonaro, still being monitored by doctors, was heavily criticized for meeting his supporters in a public parade in Bras\u00edlia without wearing a mask. <ref name=\"auto11\">{{cite web|url=https://www.canalrural.com.br/radar/bolsonaro-tira-selfies-com-manifestantes-em-frente-ao-palacio-do-planalto-2/|title=Bolsonaro tira selfies com manifestantes em frente ao Pal\u00e1cio do Planalto|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322033033/https://www.canalrural.com.br/radar/bolsonaro-tira-selfies-com-manifestantes-em-frente-ao-palacio-do-planalto-2/|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>  <!-- should we move this to another section ? -->\n\n* March 17, the '''first coronavirus-related death was confirmed in the country''' .<ref name=\"first death\">{{cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/sao-paulo-registra-primeira-morte-por-coronavirus.shtml|title=S\u00e3o Paulo registra primeira morte por coronav\u00edrus|website=Folha de S.Paulo|date=17 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318140829/https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/sao-paulo-registra-primeira-morte-por-coronavirus.shtml|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The State of Santa Catarina declares state of emergency and starts preventive measures, including closures of non-essential shops and services (shopping malls, gyms, restaurants, hotels) and suspension of public transit, inter-city and inter-state buses, public meetings, concerts, theatres, sport events and religious services. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sc/santa-catarina/noticia/2020/03/17/governo-de-sc-decreta-situacao-de-emergencia-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml |title=Governo de SC decreta situa\u00e7\u00e3o de emerg\u00eancia por causa do coronav\u00edrus|website=G1 Santa Catarina|date=17 March 2020|access-date=19 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318183649/https://g1.globo.com/sc/santa-catarina/noticia/2020/03/17/governo-de-sc-decreta-situacao-de-emergencia-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that day, the [[Ministry of Health]] reported 291 confirmed cases in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus/|title=Notifica\u00e7\u00e3o de casos de doen\u00e7a pelo coronav\u00edrus 2019 (COVID-19) \u2013 Plataforma Integrada de Vigil\u00e2ncia em Sa\u00fade \u2013 Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|date=18 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318192904/http://plataforma.saude.gov.br/novocoronavirus/|archive-date=18 March 2020|access-date=4 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* March 20, the health departments of the Brazilian states had reported almost a thousand confirmed cases. COVID-19 cases were confirmed in 23 states (of 26) and the Federal District. <ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/casos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-em-20-de-marco.ghtml|title=Casos de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil em 20 de mar\u00e7o|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321010341/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/casos-de-coronavirus-no-brasil-em-20-de-marco.ghtml|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n* March 21, the local government of the State of S\u00e3o Paulo declares a state-wide quarantine starting on March 24. The measure determined the closure of all commerce and non-essential services from that date until April 7.{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n: All Brazilian states reports at least one confirmed case of COVID-19, with the last being Roraima. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gazetadopovo.com.br/republica/breves/governo-de-roraima-confirma-dois-primeiros-casos-e-todos-os-estados-do-brasil-tem-coronavirus/|title=Governo de Roraima confirma dois primeiros casos e todos os estados do Brasil t\u00eam coronav\u00edrus}}</ref>\n\n* March 24, President Jair Bolsonaro makes a third public announcement, criticizing the local governments for issuing quarantines over \"a small flu\", and blaming the media for scaring the population. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/poder/2020/03/em-pronunciamento-bolsonaro-critica-fechamento-de-escolas-ataca-governadores-e-culpa-midia.shtml|title=Em pronunciamento, Bolsonaro critica fechamento de escolas, ataca governadores e culpa m\u00eddia}}</ref>\n\n* March 26, a month after the first confirmed case in February 26, the Ministry of Health reports that Brazil has 2,915 confirmed cases and 77 deaths. <ref>{{cite web | url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/numero-infectados-coronavirus-brasil/ |title = Mortes no Brasil por coronav\u00edrus sobem 19% em um dia e chegam a 92}}</ref>\n\n* March 28, Brazil totals more than 100 confirmed deaths from COVID-19. The Ministry of Health reported on Saturday (28) that Brazil has so far registered 114 deaths and 3,904 confirmed cases of coronavirus. The mortality of COVID-19 in the country is 2.9%, according to the balance released by the folder. The survey also points out that, in the country, men die more from coronavirus than women\u201461.4% for men to 38.6% for women. Approximately 90% of deaths are people over 60 years of age. In 84% of deaths, patients had at least one risk factor. The most common, according to the Ministry, is heart disease, followed by diabetes and [[pneumopathy]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/saude/brasil-tem-114-mortes-e-3904-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-28032020|title=Brasil tem 114 mortes e 3.904 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus|date=28 March 2020|website=R7.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/28/brasil-tem-111-mortes-e-3904-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 114 mortes e 3.904 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|website=G1}}</ref>\n\n=== April ===\n* April 6, clashes between President Jair Bolsonaro and the Minister of Health, [[Luiz Henrique Mandetta]], shake the government and society. The President threatened to fire the Minister<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/blog/gerson-camarotti/post/2020/04/06/ameaca-nao-da-desabafa-mandetta-a-interlocutores.ghtml|title='Amea\u00e7a n\u00e3o d\u00e1', desabafa Mandetta em telefonemas a ministros|date=6 April 2020|website=g1.globo.com}}</ref>, but reverted it after the political opposition. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/04/06/mandetta-diz-que-continua-e-que-governo-se-reposiciona-para-enfrentar-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Mandetta diz que continua e que governo 'se reposiciona' para enfrentar coronav\u00edrus|date=6 April 2020|website=g1.globo.com}}</ref>\n\n* April 9, the federal government rolls out a project that provides financial help to those in need. On this first day, more than 2.5 million people received R$&nbsp;600 ($&nbsp;116) to cover essential needs. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/economia/noticia/2020/04/09/6-milhoes-comecam-a-receber-auxilio-emergencial-de-r-600-nesta-quinta.ghtml|title=2,5 milh\u00f5es receberam aux\u00edlio emergencial de R$ 600 nesta quinta|date=9 April 2020|website=g1.globo.com }}</ref>\n\n* April 10, Brazil confirms '''the thousandth coronavirus-related death''', as the number of confirmed cases nears 20,000. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/04/10/brasil-tem-1057-mortes-e-19638-casos-confirmados-de-novo-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 1.056 mortes e 19.638 casos confirmados de novo coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n: The virus reaches even the most remote locations, as a [[Yanomani]] teen dies in [[Roraima]] from COVID-19. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rr/roraima/noticia/2020/04/10/morre-adolescente-yanomami-infectado-pelo-coronavirus-em-roraima.ghtml|title=\u00cdndio yanomami de 15 anos morre em Roraima ap\u00f3s 6 dias na UTI|date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* April 14, '''more than 14 thousand recoveries''' are reported by the Ministry of Health, with 25,262 confirmed cases and 1,532 confirmed deaths since the beginning of the pandemic. This totals fewer than 10 thousand active cases of COVID-19 in Brazil. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/04/14/brasil-tem-1532-mortes-e-25262-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-diz-ministerio.ghtml|title=Brasil tem 1.532 mortes e 25.262 casos confirmados de coronav\u00edrus, diz minist\u00e9rio|date=14 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* April 15, it was reported that eleven COVID-19 patients taking part in a study died after being given high doses of the anti-malarial drug [[chloroquine]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/12/health/chloroquine-coronavirus-trump.html|title=Small Chloroquine Study Halted Over Risk of Fatal Heart Complications|website= New York Times|language=en|date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n* April 16, President Jair Bolsonaro fires the Minister of Health, [[Luiz Henrique Mandetta]], over disagreements on his social isolation guidelines <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/04/16/mandetta-anuncia-em-rede-social-que-foi-demitido-do-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml|title=Mandetta anuncia em rede social que foi demitido por Bolsonaro do Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade|date=16 April 2020}}</ref>. Shortly afterwards, [[Nelson Teich]] was appointed to replace him. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/04/16/nelson-teich-novo-ministro-da-saude-perfil.ghtml|title=Saiba quem \u00e9 Nelson Teich, novo ministro da Sa\u00fade|date=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Response==\nPolicy responses and prevention announced in the country amid the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\n[[File:Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade - Livreto Plano de Contingencia Covid-19 Coronavirus 2020.pdf|thumb|Contingency plan booklet of the pandemic]]\n\n===Scientific research and forecast===\n\nOn 19 March, scientists predicted up to 2 million deaths in Brazil in the worst-case scenario without measures to contain the virus. They pointed out that a policy of [[social distancing]] is one of the most effective measures given the lack of a [[vaccine]].<ref name=\"auto10\">{{cite web|url=https://www.opovo.com.br/coronavirus/2020/03/19/cientistas-prevem-ate-2-milhoes-de-mortes-no-brasil-no-pior-cenario-sem-medidas-para-conter-o-virus.html|title=Cientistas prevem at\u00e9 2 milh\u00f5es de mortes no Brasil no pior cen\u00e1rio sem medidas para conter o v\u00edrus|first=O.|last=Povo|date=21 March 2020|website=Coronavirus|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320142716/https://www.opovo.com.br/coronavirus/2020/03/19/cientistas-prevem-ate-2-milhoes-de-mortes-no-brasil-no-pior-cenario-sem-medidas-para-conter-o-virus.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, experts from Italy warned that the coronavirus growth curve in Brazil would repeat that of European countries. An observatory with physicists from [[University of S\u00e3o Paulo|USP]], [[Unicamp]], [[Unesp]], [[UnB]], [[UFABC]], [[UC Berkeley]] and the [[University of Oldenburg]] showed that the number of infected people, considering data from March 19, had been doubling every 54 hours, and that the case total would exceed 3,000 on the 24th.<ref name=\"auto13\">{{cite web|url=https://epocanegocios.globo.com/Mundo/noticia/2020/03/curva-de-crescimento-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-repete-de-paises-europeus-alertam-especialistas-da-italia.html|title=Curva de crescimento do coronav\u00edrus no Brasil repete a de pa\u00edses europeus, alertam especialistas da It\u00e1lia|website=\u00c9poca Neg\u00f3cios|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320183307/https://epocanegocios.globo.com/Mundo/noticia/2020/03/curva-de-crescimento-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-repete-de-paises-europeus-alertam-especialistas-da-italia.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/ritmo-de-contagio-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-igual-ao-registrado-na-italia-e-acelerando-aponta-unesp.ghtml|title=Ritmo de cont\u00e1gio do coronav\u00edrus no Brasil est\u00e1 igual ao registrado na It\u00e1lia e acelerando, apontam universidades|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320173906/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/20/ritmo-de-contagio-do-coronavirus-no-brasil-esta-igual-ao-registrado-na-italia-e-acelerando-aponta-unesp.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, researchers were mobilizing to increase test availability in Brazil. The [[Federal University of Rio de Janeiro]] is currently attempting to create a [[serology test]], as opposed to the more common [[PCR test]], to detect infections through a patient's blood drop.<ref name=\"auto6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/pesquisadores-se-mobilizam-para-aumentar-oferta-de-testes-no-brasil,d6a76c837c86a20c120e5d733d51a3ebrddc3q94.html|title=Pesquisadores se mobilizam para aumentar oferta de testes no Brasil|website=Terra|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321163919/https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/pesquisadores-se-mobilizam-para-aumentar-oferta-de-testes-no-brasil,d6a76c837c86a20c120e5d733d51a3ebrddc3q94.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n[[Ministry of Health (Brazil)|Minister of Health]] [[Luiz Henrique Mandetta]] has said the number of cases will increase exponentially until the end of June.<ref name=\"exame\">{{cite web|url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/numero-infectados-coronavirus-brasil/|title=Brasil tem 1546 casos e 25 mortes pelo coronav\u00edrus|website=EXAME|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319232448/https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/numero-infectados-coronavirus-brasil/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 March, a report from [[Funda\u00e7\u00e3o Get\u00falio Vargas|FGV]] economist Emerson Mar\u00e7al predicted a negative 2020 GDP of up to 4.4% with the effect of the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://noticias.r7.com/economia/pesquisa-preve-pib-negativo-de-ate-44-com-efeito-do-coronavirus-23032020 |title=Pesquisa prev\u00ea PIB negativo de at\u00e9 4,4% com efeito do coronav\u00edrus |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324095828/https://noticias.r7.com/economia/pesquisa-preve-pib-negativo-de-ate-44-com-efeito-do-coronavirus-23032020 |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Preventive measures===\n[[File:Corpo de Bombeiros vai atuar na detec\u00e7\u00e3o de casos suspeitos - 49658924053.jpg|thumb|Brazilian firefighters will be helping in the detection of suspected cases]]\n\nOn 17 March, Brazilian authorities partially closed [[Brazil\u2013Venezuela border|their border]] with Venezuela. Health Minister Luiz Henrique Mandetta had urged closure of the border due to Venezuela's collapsing health system.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-venezuela-idUSKBN2143ZS|title=Brazil partially closing Venezuela border, allowing trucks|date=18 March 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318100317/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-venezuela-idUSKBN2143ZS|archive-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, Rio de Janeiro and five other municipalities\u2014[[S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo, Rio de Janeiro|S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo]], [[Guapimirim]], [[Niter\u00f3i]], [[Nova Igua\u00e7u]], and [[Mesquita, Rio de Janeiro|Mesquita]]\u2014in the state of Rio de Janeiro have declared an [[State of emergency|emergency state]] to help contain the coronavirus. declared emergency situations in the area of public health.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/18/prefeitura-do-rio-declara-situacao-de-emergencia.ghtml|title=Rio e outros 5 munic\u00edpios do estado declaram situa\u00e7\u00e3o de emerg\u00eancia para conter o coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319214110/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/18/prefeitura-do-rio-declara-situacao-de-emergencia.ghtml|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe following day, the government of Rio Grande do Sul declared a public calamity situation. Among the measures adopted are the prohibition of interstate travel and the restriction of items purchased in the markets.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rs/rio-grande-do-sul/noticia/2020/03/19/governo-decreta-situacao-de-calamidade-publica-no-rs-devido-ao-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Governo do RS decreta situa\u00e7\u00e3o de calamidade p\u00fablica devido ao coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175803/https://g1.globo.com/rs/rio-grande-do-sul/noticia/2020/03/19/governo-decreta-situacao-de-calamidade-publica-no-rs-devido-ao-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, it was the government of Rio Grande do Norte that declared a public calamity situation.<ref name=\"auto12\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rn/rio-grande-do-norte/noticia/2020/03/20/governo-do-rn-decreta-calamidade-publica-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Governo do RN decreta calamidade p\u00fablica por causa do coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182944/https://g1.globo.com/rn/rio-grande-do-norte/noticia/2020/03/20/governo-do-rn-decreta-calamidade-publica-por-causa-do-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Declara\u00e7\u00f5es \u00e0 Imprensa referentes ao Corona v\u00edrus em 18 de mar\u00e7o de 2020 - Pal\u00e1cio do Planalto 44.jpg|thumb|Government declarations about the disease on the [[Pal\u00e1cio do Planalto]] ]]\n\nGovernment of Rio Grande do Norte decrees public calamity because of the coronavirus. The measure becomes effective on Friday (20), after being published in the Official Gazette of the State.<ref name=\"auto12\"/>\n\nOn 21 March, In SP, cases of coronavirus rise almost 40% in two hours. Deaths also increased in the period. Cities in the Campinas region declared an emergency situation due to the pandemic of the new coronavirus. In addition to the metropolis, Hortol\u00e2ndia, Holambra, Indaiatuba, Itapira, Jaguari\u00fana, Mogi Gua\u00e7u, Mogi Mirim, Paul\u00ednia, Sumar\u00e9 and \u00c1guas de Lindoia issued decrees with special measures to contain the progress of COVID-19 cases. Valinhos and Vinhedo determined a state of public calamity. Americana is in a state of attention.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.diariodolitoral.com.br/saude/em-sp-casos-de-coronavirus-sobem-quase-40-em-duas-horas/133224/|title=Em SP, casos de coronav\u00edrus sobem quase 40% em duas horas|website=diariodolitoral.com.br|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321170926/https://www.diariodolitoral.com.br/saude/em-sp-casos-de-coronavirus-sobem-quase-40-em-duas-horas/133224/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/campinas-regiao/noticia/2020/03/21/coronavirus-veja-lista-de-cidades-em-estado-de-emergencia-ou-calamidade-publica-e-o-que-muda-com-decretos-na-regiao-de-campinas.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: veja lista de cidades em estado de emerg\u00eancia ou calamidade p\u00fablica e o que muda com decretos na regi\u00e3o de Campinas|website=G1|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321163920/https://g1.globo.com/sp/campinas-regiao/noticia/2020/03/21/coronavirus-veja-lista-de-cidades-em-estado-de-emergencia-ou-calamidade-publica-e-o-que-muda-com-decretos-na-regiao-de-campinas.ghtml|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Prefeitura de Petr\u00f3polis - Sirenes m\u00f3veis s\u00e3o usadas para alertar popula\u00e7\u00e3o sobre perigo do Coronav\u00edrus.webm|thumb|Sirens used to warn people about the dangers of the pandemic]]\n\n===Internal policy===\n\nPresident [[Jair Bolsonaro]] has been criticized for his handling of the coronavirus crisis.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/03/coronavirus-bolsonaro-brazil-panelaco.html|title=Could the Coronavirus Topple Jair Bolsonaro?|last=Dias|first=Isabela|date=20 March 2020|website=Slate|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322031616/https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2020/03/coronavirus-bolsonaro-brazil-panelaco.html|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 10 March, he referred to the pandemic as a \"fantasy\" created by the media.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/10/bolsonaro-diz-que-questao-do-coronavirus-e-muito-mais-fantasia.ghtml|title=Bolsonaro diz que 'pequena crise' do coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 'mais fantasia' e n\u00e3o 'isso tudo' que m\u00eddia propaga|website=G1|language=pt-br|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322031617/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/10/bolsonaro-diz-que-questao-do-coronavirus-e-muito-mais-fantasia.ghtml|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, Bolsonaro, who was being monitored by doctors after his Press Secretary tested positive for COVID-19, was heavily criticized for meeting his supporters in a public parade in [[Bras\u00edlia]] without wearing a [[mask]].<ref name=\"auto11\"/> Later, impeachment cases were brought up against the [[President (government title)|President]] for his participation in the parade, which some viewed as anti-democratic, and also for posing a threat to public health.<ref name=\"auto3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/intervozes/coronavirus-desmascara-a-politica-de-morte-de-bolsonaro/|title=Coronav\u00edrus desmascara a pol\u00edtica de morte de Bolsonaro|date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321194634/https://www.cartacapital.com.br/blogs/intervozes/coronavirus-desmascara-a-politica-de-morte-de-bolsonaro/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, Bolsonaro criticized the governor of [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Wilson Witzel]] ([[Social Christian Party (Brazil)|PSC]]), for asking for the suspension of the arrival of [[flights]] from [[state (polity)|state]]s where [[contamination]] by the new coronavirus is [[confirmed]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/bolsonaro-critica-witzel-por-fechar-aeroporto-parece-que-rj-e-outro-pais.htm|title=Bolsonaro critica Witzel por querer impedir voos para o Rio de Janeiro|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320195055/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/bolsonaro-critica-witzel-por-fechar-aeroporto-parece-que-rj-e-outro-pais.htm|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBolsonaro says that closing shopping malls and commerce hurts the economy. In the midst of the COVID-19 pandemic, experts from around the world have suggested measures to restrict the circulation of individuals as one of the most efficient ways to contain the spread of the virus. However, then-president Jair Bolsonaro said on Friday (March 20th) that he was against closing of trade and market places decreed by most state governors as a measure to combat the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bnews.com.br/noticias/economia/coronavirus/262603,bolsonaro-diz-que-fechar-shoppings-e-comercio-prejudica-a-economia.html|title=Bolsonaro diz que fechar shoppings e com\u00e9rcio prejudica a economia|website=BNews|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320195057/https://www.bnews.com.br/noticias/economia/coronavirus/262603,bolsonaro-diz-que-fechar-shoppings-e-comercio-prejudica-a-economia.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe governor of [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]], Jo\u00e3o Doria, countered president Bolsonaro's supposed lack of action, by saying that state's governors are playing the role that should've be his, which is to lead [the people] amidst the pandemic of the new coronavirus. Earlier in [[Bras\u00edlia]], Bolsonaro criticized what he called \"extreme measures\", such as \"closing shopping malls and weekly outdoor markets\". He did not specifically mentioned Doria by name, but the governor of S\u00e3o Paulo defended his policies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/doria-rebate-bolsonaro-estamos-fazendo-o-que-ele-nao-faz-liderar.htm|title=Doria rebate Bolsonaro: 'estamos fazendo o que ele n\u00e3o faz, liderar'|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175802/https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/20/doria-rebate-bolsonaro-estamos-fazendo-o-que-ele-nao-faz-liderar.htm|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBrazil is the second country with most cases of coronavirus at the executive cabinet. Just behind Iran and followed by France, the Brazilian government had at least thirteen prominent politicians contaminated. The confirmation on Thursday 18th that the Minister of Mines and Energy, Bento Albuquerque, and the [[President of the Senate]], [[Davi Alcolumbre]], contracted the new coronavirus made Brazil the second country with more cases of the disease by politicians in leading positions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://veja.abril.com.br/mundo/brasil-e-2o-pais-com-mais-casos-de-coronavirus-na-alta-cupula-do-governo/|title=Brasil \u00e9 2\u00ba pa\u00eds com mais casos de coronav\u00edrus na alta c\u00fapula do governo|website=VEJA|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320132618/https://veja.abril.com.br/mundo/brasil-e-2o-pais-com-mais-casos-de-coronavirus-na-alta-cupula-do-governo/|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, talking about Congress, Bolsonaro said they wanted to impeach him to have a confrontation.{{Clarify|date=April 2020}} The president of the Chamber of Deputies, Rodrigo Maia (DEM-RJ), and of the Senate, Davi Alcolumbre (DEM-AP), as well as the leaders of the main parties in Congress no longer believe in the possibility of productive dialogue with President Jair Bolsonaro.<ref name=\"auto9\"/>\n\nOn 23 March, Rodrigo Maia stated that Brazil might need between $78.1&nbsp;billion to combat coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-budget-idUSKBN21A3GJ|title=Brazil needs up to $78&nbsp;billion to fight coronavirus crisis \u2013 Congress leader|date=23 March 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324095115/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-brazil-budget-idUSKBN21A3GJ|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, president Bolsonaro declared that the routine in the country must return to reality and that the Brazilian press spread the panic around the coronavirus, which he called again \"little flu\". Speaking on radio and television, Bolsonaro also criticized governors for determining quarantine\u2014with trade and border closures\u2014and questioned why schools were closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/politica/ultimas-noticias/2020/03/24/covid-19-bolsonaro-culpa-imprensa-por-panico-e-volta-a-falar-gripezinha.htm|title=Bolsonaro critica imprensa e fechamento de escolas e diz que crise passar\u00e1|website=noticias.uol.com.br|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/regiao-dos-lagos/noticia/2020/03/25/autoridades-no-rj-reagem-a-pronunciamento-de-bolsonaro-que-critica-confinamento-em-massa.ghtml|title=Autoridades no RJ reagem a pronunciamento de Bolsonaro que pede fim do 'confinamento em massa'|website=G1|accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nPoliticians and authorities reacted to President Jair Bolsonaro's pronouncement about the coronavirus pandemic on Tuesday night (24). The president called for \"a return to normalcy\", an end to \"mass confinement\" and said that the media had spread \"dread\". Senate President Davi Alcolumbre (DEM-AP) released a note in which he classified Bolsonaro's speech as \"serious\" and said the country needs \"serious leadership\". The president of the Chamber of Deputies, Rodrigo Maia (DEM-RJ), affirmed that the statement \"was wrong when attacking the press, the governors and specialists in public health\".{{citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nA large number of the Brazilian politicians spoke out against this statement by the President of the Republic.{{efn|They include: [[Davi Alcolumbre]] (DEM-AP) President of the Senate, [[Rodrigo Maia]] (DEM-RJ) President of the Chamber, [[Felipe Santa Cruz]] President of the OAB, [[Gilmar Mendes]] Minister of the STF, [[Wilson Witzel]] (PSC) governor of Rio de Janeiro, [[Helder Barbalho]] (MDB) governor of Par\u00e1, [[Alexandre Frota]] (PSDB-SP) federal deputy, [[Joice Hasselmann]] (PSL-SP) federal deputy, [[Janaina Paschoal]] (PSL-SP) state deputy, [[Rodrigo Pacheco (politician)|Rodrigo Pacheco]] (DEM-MG) senator, [[Kim Kataguiri]] (DEM-SP) federal deputy, [[Jos\u00e9 Serra]] (PSDB) former Minister of Health, Jos\u00e9 Ricardo Roriz vice president of Fiesp, [[Leila Barros|Leila do V\u00f4lei]] (PSB-DF) senator, [[Renato Casagrande]] (PSB) governor of Esp\u00edrito Santo, [[Wellington Dias]] (PT), governor of Piau\u00ed, [[F\u00e1tima Bezerra]] (PT) governor of Rio Grande do Norte, [[Antonio Anastasia]] (PSD-MG) senator, [[Fernando Henrique Cardoso]] former president, [[Jo\u00e3o Amo\u00eado]] ex-president of the New Party, [[Enio Verri]] (PT-PR) federal deputy, [[Eduardo Braga]] (MDB-AM) senator, [[Humberto Costa]] (PT-PE) senator, [[Randolfe Rodrigues]] (Rede-AP) senator, [[Alessandro Molon]] (PSB-RJ) federal deputy, [[Fl\u00e1vio Dino]] (PCdoB) governor of Maranh\u00e3o, [[Jos\u00e9 Nobre Guimar\u00e3es]] (PT-CE) federal deputy, [[Rog\u00e9rio Carvalho Santos|Rog\u00e9rio Carvalho]] (PT-SE) senator, [[Fernanda Melchionna]] (PSOL-RS) federal deputy, [[Weverton Rocha]] (PDT-MA) senator, [[Marcelo Freixo]] (PSOL-RJ) federal deputy, [[Paulo Pimenta (politician)|Paulo Pimenta]] (PT -RS) federal deputy, [[Jean-Paul Prates]] (PT-RN) senator, [[Eliziane Gama]] (Cidadania-MA) senator, [[Marcelo Ramos Rodrigues|Marcelo Ramos]] (PL-AM) federal deputy, [[Arnaldo Jardim]] (Cidadania-SP) federal deputy, [[Reinaldo Azambuja]] (PSDB) governor of Mato Grosso do Sul, [[Wilson Lima]] (PSC) governor of Amazonas.<ref name=\"24globo\"/>}} The [[PSDB]], the Brazilian Press Association (ABI), the Secretaries of Health of the Northeast, the Brazilian Society of Infectology, also spoke against the president's speech. In favor of the president's speech, his two sons [[Eduardo Bolsonaro]] (no party) federal deputy and [[Fl\u00e1vio Bolsonaro]] (no party) senator, along with Vitor Hugo (PSL-GO), federal deputy, spoke.<ref name=24globo>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/24/veja-repercussao-ao-pronunciamento-de-bolsonaro-em-que-ele-pediu-volta-a-normalidade-fim-do-confinamento-e-disse-que-meios-de-comunicacao-espalharam-pavor.ghtml |title=Veja repercuss\u00e3o do pronunciamento de Bolsonaro sobre o coronav\u00edrus em que ele contrariou especialistas e pediu fim do 'confinamento em massa' |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325024638/https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/24/veja-repercussao-ao-pronunciamento-de-bolsonaro-em-que-ele-pediu-volta-a-normalidade-fim-do-confinamento-e-disse-que-meios-de-comunicacao-espalharam-pavor.ghtml |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBrazilian cities register pots against Bolsonaro for the eighth consecutive day. [[S\u00e3o Paulo]], Rio de Janeiro, [[Bras\u00edlia]], [[Belo Horizonte]] and [[Recife]] were some of the cities in which people threw pots during the president's speech last Tuesday (24). Brasilienses protested, against the pronouncement of the President of the Republic, Jair Bolsonaro (without party). \"Pots\" were recorded in \u00c1guas Claras, in the Southwest, in Cruzeiro, in Asa Norte, in Asa Sul and in Taguatinga.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/politica/noticia/2020/03/24/cidades-brasileiras-registram-panelacos-contra-bolsonaro.ghtml |title=Cidades brasileiras registram panela\u0102\u00a7os contra Bolsonaro pelo oitavo dia seguido &#124; Pol\u0102tica &#124; G1 |publisher=G1.globo.com |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metropoles.com/distrito-federal/df-tem-panelaco-contra-bolsonaro-durante-pronunciamento-na-tv|title=DF tem panela\u00e7o contra Bolsonaro durante pronunciamento na TV|date=24 March 2020|website=Metr\u00f3poles}}</ref>\n\n===Foreign policy===\n\nOn 19 March, [[Eduardo Bolsonaro]], son of President Jair Bolsonaro, set off a diplomatic dispute with China, Brazil's largest trading partner, when he retweeted a message blaming the [[Communist Party of China|Chinese Communist Party]] for the virus.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/rio-reports-first-coronavirus-deaths-163812406.html Brazil coronavirus cases top 600, diplomatic spat with China bubbles] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320192215/https://news.yahoo.com/rio-reports-first-coronavirus-deaths-163812406.html |date=20 March 2020 }} By Pedro Fonseca, Reuters, 19 March 2020</ref> Yang Wanming, China's top diplomat in Brazil, later retweeted a message saying \"The Bolsonaro family is the great poison of this country.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Bolsonaro's son enrages Beijing by blaming China for coronavirus crisis |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/coronavirus-bolsonaro-son-china-row |work=The Guardian |date=19 March 2020 |access-date=22 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320190353/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/coronavirus-bolsonaro-son-china-row |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\nBolsonaro made a televised speech about the pandemic, during which both pro and anti-Bolsonaro ''[[Cacerolazo|panela\u00e7os]]'' broke out in the largest cities of Brazil.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51955679|title=Brazil coronavirus protesters urge 'Bolsonaro out'|date=19 March 2020|work=BBC News|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322135850/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-51955679|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nAccording to one poll, 64% of Brazilians reject the way Bolsonaro has been handling the pandemic, while 44.8% support his [[impeachment]], an all-time high.<ref>[https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-19/gestao-de-bolsonaro-do-coronavirus-e-reprovada-por-64-e-45-se-dizem-a-favor-de-impeachment.html \"Gest\u00e3o de Bolsonaro do coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 reprovada por 64%, e 45% se dizem a favor de impeachment\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323021820/https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-19/gestao-de-bolsonaro-do-coronavirus-e-reprovada-por-64-e-45-se-dizem-a-favor-de-impeachment.html |date=23 March 2020 }}. ''El Pa\u00eds''. 19 March 2020.</ref>\nAccording to some sources in the Congress, Bolsonaro is shutting down political dialogue on purpose. They claim he is forcing his impeachment as a way to mobilize his supporters.<ref name=\"auto9\">{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/colunas/tales-faria/2020/03/21/para-o-congresso-bolsonaro-quer-que-tentem-impeachment-para-ter-confronto.htm|title=Para o Congresso, Bolsonaro quer que tentem impeachment para ter confronto|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321172504/https://noticias.uol.com.br/colunas/tales-faria/2020/03/21/para-o-congresso-bolsonaro-quer-que-tentem-impeachment-para-ter-confronto.htm|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Impact==\n===Economy===\nEconomists expect an [[economic stagnation]] for the country in 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://diariodocomercio.com.br/exclusivo/economia-brasileira-sofrera-forte-impacto-com-o-novo-coronavirus/|title=Economia brasileira sofrer\u00e1 forte impacto com o novo coronav\u00edrus|first=Mara|last=Bianchetti|date=21 March 2020|website=Di\u00e1rio do Com\u00e9rcio|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322062357/https://diariodocomercio.com.br/exclusivo/economia-brasileira-sofrera-forte-impacto-com-o-novo-coronavirus/|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> As such, on 16 March, the [[Ministry of Economy (Brazil)|Ministry of Economy]] announced a stimulus package of R$147.3&nbsp;billion (US$29&nbsp;billion) to help the economy against the effects of the pandemic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.poder360.com.br/economia/guedes-anuncia-pacote-de-r-147-bilhoes-para-combater-pandemia-de-covid-19/|title=Guedes anuncia pacote de R$147 bilh\u00f5es para combater pandemia de covid-19|website=Poder 360|date=16 March 2020}}</ref> The Brazilian government is also in negotiations with the [[New Development Bank]] to receive an aid package for its COVID-19 efforts; China received one billion USD from the same institution.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/banco-de-desenvolvimento-do-brics-libera-ajuda-de-r-5-bilhoes-a-china,9bc26d72a411019e55adb6bdd0a3094asut8ttyw.html|title=Banco de Desenvolvimento do BRICS libera ajuda de R$5 bilh\u00f5es \u00e0 China|website=Terra|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321195758/https://www.terra.com.br/vida-e-estilo/saude/banco-de-desenvolvimento-do-brics-libera-ajuda-de-r-5-bilhoes-a-china,9bc26d72a411019e55adb6bdd0a3094asut8ttyw.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 March, Economy Minister [[Paulo Guedes]] announced a series of aid measures to reduce the impact on the economy that will be caused by COVID-19. A scholarship for self-employed professionals, in the amount of R$200, is being prepared, in addition to the payment guarantee for workers who have reduced working hours.<ref name=\"exame\"/>\n\nOn 23 March, government announces package of R$85.8 billion for states and municipalities. Amount involves transfers to the health area, recomposition of transfers of constitutional funds and suspension of the maturity of debts of the states with the Union.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/economia/noticia/2020/03/23/coronavirus-governo-anuncia-pacote-de-r-858-bilhoes-para-estados-e-municipios.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: governo anuncia pacote de R$ 85,8 bilh\u00f5es para estados e munic\u00edpios|website=G1}}</ref>\n\n===Education===\nOn 20 March, The pandemic has [[impact of the 2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic on education|impacted education all over the world]]. In over a hundred countries, there were nationwide school closures. However, President Jair Bolsonaro has issued few country-wide measures to slow the spread of the virus,<ref name=\":17\">{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200316-as-latin-america-takes-steps-to-counter-coronavirus-brazil-s-bolsonaro-snubs-warnings|title=Latin America takes steps to counter coronavirus, Brazil's Bolsonaro snubs warnings|date=16 March 2020|publisher=France 24|access-date=16 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320165406/https://www.france24.com/en/20200316-as-latin-america-takes-steps-to-counter-coronavirus-brazil-s-bolsonaro-snubs-warnings|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-panama-idUSKBN20Y3FA|title=Latin American countries order school closures over coronavirus fears|date=12 March 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=16 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320165410/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-panama-idUSKBN20Y3FA|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and because the federal government decided not to cancel classes in the whole country, lower levels of government have done so on independently. As such, municipal, state, and private schools and universities had different reactions regarding the suspension of classes. Classes were suspended at once, gradually or not at all. Some of them were replaced with [[distance education]] or simply postponed. Because of that, there are only \"localized\" (as opposed to \"national\") school closures, according to [[UNESCO]].<ref name=\"UNESCO\">{{cite web|url=https://en.unesco.org/themes/education-emergencies/coronavirus-school-closures|title=COVID-19 Educational Disruption and Response|publisher=UNESCO|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321000612/https://en.unesco.org/themes/education-emergencies/coronavirus-school-closures|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Favelas===\n\nOn 17 March, Residents of [[favelas]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]] suffer from a lack of water amid the coronavirus pandemic. [[Cariocas]] and fluminenses are much more exposed to the proliferation of coronavirus without having water for cleaning, says a specialist. In parts of the [[Baixada Fluminense]] and the [[North]] Zone of [[Rio de Janeiro]] the water does not reach. Among the affected areas are: Chatuba de [[Mesquita, Rio de Janeiro|Mesquita]], Camarista, [[M\u00e9ier]] and [[Complexo do Alem\u00e3o]] communities. The infectious disease doctor and pediatrician Cristiana Meirelles says that without clean running water, the situation of fighting the epidemic becomes catastrophic.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/17/moradores-de-comunidades-do-rj-sofrem-com-falta-de-agua-em-meio-a-pandemia-de-coronavirus.ghtml|title=Moradores de comunidades do RJ sofrem com falta de \u00e1gua em meio \u00e0 pandemia de coronav\u00edrus|website=G1|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319211134/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/17/moradores-de-comunidades-do-rj-sofrem-com-falta-de-agua-em-meio-a-pandemia-de-coronavirus.ghtml|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nCufa calls for measures to contain coronavirus in favelas. Government actions do not include the economically fragile, a contingent that totals more than 70 million people, says the organization.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/cufa-pede-medidas-para-conter-o-coronavirus-nas-favelas/|title=Cufa pede medidas para conter o coronav\u00edrus nas favelas|website=EXAME|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321203956/https://exame.abril.com.br/brasil/cufa-pede-medidas-para-conter-o-coronavirus-nas-favelas/|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nSome areas of Mar\u00e9 had been without water for two days, and other areas reported have been without water for two weeks.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://s2.glbimg.com/_pbfQW3RR8K11JBZvO2u590X8FM=/0x41:720x861/1600x0/smart/filters:strip_icc()/i.s3.glbimg.com/v1/AUTH_59edd422c0c84a879bd37670ae4f538a/internal_photos/bs/2020/v/O/AA9BvNRQSiodWbwzkd2w/jacarezinho.jfif |title=Archived copy |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324094915/https://s2.glbimg.com/_pbfQW3RR8K11JBZvO2u590X8FM%3D/0x41:720x861/1600x0/smart/filters:strip_icc()/i.s3.glbimg.com/v1/AUTH_59edd422c0c84a879bd37670ae4f538a/internal_photos/bs/2020/v/O/AA9BvNRQSiodWbwzkd2w/jacarezinho.jfif |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-tem-63-casos-suspeitos-do-novo-coronavirus.ghtml |title=Favelas do Rio t\u00eam 61 casos suspeitos do novo coronav\u00edrus, segundo Secretaria de Sa\u00fade |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324154450/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-tem-63-casos-suspeitos-do-novo-coronavirus.ghtml |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brasildefato.com.br/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-sofrem-com-falta-d-agua-e-populacao-fica-mais-vulneravel-a-coronavirus |title=Favelas do Rio sofrem com falta d'\u00e1gua e popula\u00e7\u00e3o fica mais vulner\u00e1vel a coronav\u00edrus |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324094920/https://www.brasildefato.com.br/2020/03/23/favelas-do-rio-sofrem-com-falta-d-agua-e-populacao-fica-mais-vulneravel-a-coronavirus |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Healthcare===\n\n[[File:Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade -01- Boletim Infec\u00e7\u00e3o Humana pelo Novo Coronav\u00edrus 2019-nCoV.pdf|thumb|Ministry of Health -01- Bulletin of Human infection for the Noval Coronavirus 2019-nCoV]]\n\nSince the first cases were reported in the country, there were concerns if its [[Sistema \u00danico de Sa\u00fade|healthcare system]] would be able to deal with the pandemic.\n\nOn 18 March, hospitals in [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]] denounced a lack of health materials, such as masks, gloves and [[hand sanitizer]], caused by an in an increase in prices.<ref name=\"auto8\">{{cite web|url=https://noticias.uol.com.br/saude/ultimas-noticias/redacao/2020/03/19/funcionarios-relatam-falta-de-alcool-gel-e-luvas-em-hospitais-de-sao-paulo.htm|title=Funcion\u00e1rios relatam falta de \u00e1lcool gel e luvas em hospitais de S\u00e3o Paulo|website=noticias.uol.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175759/https://noticias.uol.com.br/saude/ultimas-noticias/redacao/2020/03/19/funcionarios-relatam-falta-de-alcool-gel-e-luvas-em-hospitais-de-sao-paulo.htm|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto7\">{{cite web|url=https://brasil.elpais.com/sociedade/2020-03-20/profissionais-relatam-precariedade-contra-coronavirus-no-sus-paciente-fica-exposto-e-nos-tambem.html|title=Profissionais relatam precariedade contra coronav\u00edrus no SUS: \"Paciente fica exposto, e n\u00f3s tamb\u00e9m\"|first=Joana|last=Oliveira|date=20 March 2020|website=EL PA\u00cdS|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182411/https://brasil.elpais.com/sociedade/2020-03-20/profissionais-relatam-precariedade-contra-coronavirus-no-sus-paciente-fica-exposto-e-nos-tambem.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> According to them, packages of masks went from R$4.50 in January to R$140 on 17 March. The government said it will negotiate with the industry to meet the demand.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/coronavirus-hospitais-de-sp-denunciam-falta-de-materiais-e-aumento-de-ate-30-vezes-nos-precos.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Hospitais de SP denunciam falta de materiais e aumento de at\u00e9 30 vezes nos pre\u00e7os|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175759/https://g1.globo.com/sp/sao-paulo/noticia/2020/03/18/coronavirus-hospitais-de-sp-denunciam-falta-de-materiais-e-aumento-de-ate-30-vezes-nos-precos.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/brasil/coronavirus-caixa-de-mascara-sobe-de-r-450-para-r-140-denunciam-hospitais/|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Caixa de m\u00e1scara sobe de R$ 4,50 para R$ 140, denunciam Hospitais|first=Reda\u00e7\u00e3o Jornal de|last=Bras\u00edlia|date=18 March 2020|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320175758/https://jornaldebrasilia.com.br/brasil/coronavirus-caixa-de-mascara-sobe-de-r-450-para-r-140-denunciam-hospitais/|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Salvador, Bahia|Salvador]], there was an outage of masks and hand sanitizer in the local commerce.<ref name=\"auto4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bahianoticias.com.br/noticia/245528-mascaras-para-profissionais-de-saude-esgotam-em-salvador-e-ambulantes-aproveitam.html|title=M\u00e1scaras para profissionais de sa\u00fade esgotam em Salvador e ambulantes 'aproveitam'|website=bahianoticias.com.br|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182417/https://www.bahianoticias.com.br/noticia/245528-mascaras-para-profissionais-de-saude-esgotam-em-salvador-e-ambulantes-aproveitam.html|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\nRio and five other municipalities in the state declare an emergency to contain the coronavirus. Municipalities of [[S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo, Rio de Janeiro|S\u00e3o Gon\u00e7alo]] and [[Guapimirim]] also declared a state of emergency and [[Niter\u00f3i]], [[Nova Igua\u00e7u]] and Mesquita declared an emergency situation in the area of public health.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nOn 19 March, scientists predicted up to 2&nbsp;million deaths in Brazil in the worst scenario without measures to contain the coronavirus. They point out that maintaining social distance is one of the most effective measures without a vaccine.<ref name=\"auto10\"/> Their conclusion came after analyzing the [[Growth curve (statistics)|growth curve]] of COVID-19 cases in Brazil. The contagion rate is the same as that registered in Italy, as the number of infected people has been doubling every 54 hours. According to estimates, the number of confirmed cases might reach 3,000 by 24 March.<ref name=\"auto13\"/> According to the Ministry of Health, the number of infected patients will grow [[Exponential growth|exponentially]] by the end of June.<ref name=\"exame\"/> The mayor of [[Belo Horizonte]], [[Alexandre Kalil]] (PSD), asked General Altair Jos\u00e9 Polsin, commander of the 4th Army Region, for the temporary assignment of 51 professionals from the army garrison to assist in the demands of fighting the coronavirus. The Brazilian Army has not yet said whether it will meet this demand. Peak cases of COVID-19 in BH will be in the first week of April. In an interview, the health secretary announced the creation of two more Respiratory Disease centers and is studying placing PMs to serve the population.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://noticias.r7.com/minas-gerais/pico-de-casos-de-covid-19-em-bh-sera-na-1-semana-de-abril-19032020|title=Pico de casos de Covid-19 em BH ser\u00e1 na 1\u00aa semana de abril|date=19 March 2020|website=R7.com|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322190809/https://noticias.r7.com/minas-gerais/pico-de-casos-de-covid-19-em-bh-sera-na-1-semana-de-abril-19032020|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto5\">{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/mg/minas-gerais/noticia/2020/03/19/coronavirus-prefeitura-de-bh-pede-reforco-de-medicos-ao-exercito.ghtml|title=Coronav\u00edrus: Prefeitura de BH pede refor\u00e7o do Ex\u00e9rcito para o atendimento da sa\u00fade|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320173852/https://g1.globo.com/mg/minas-gerais/noticia/2020/03/19/coronavirus-prefeitura-de-bh-pede-reforco-de-medicos-ao-exercito.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"auto5\"/>\n\nThe Government of [[Rio Grande do Sul]] decreed a public calamity situation, with measures including the prohibition of interstate travel and the restriction of items purchased in the markets, with the decree in force from 19 March.<ref name=\"auto1\"/>\nEmployees at four public hospitals in the city of S\u00e3o Paulo reported a shortage of materials such as alcohol gel, masks and gloves when caring for patients with suspected coronavirus. Professionals in the [[Sistema \u00danico de Sa\u00fade]] (SUS) reported a shortage of masks and rationing of gel alcohol, though the situation of public service workers is different from{{how|date=April 2020}} that of private hospitals in S\u00e3o Paulo.<ref name=\"auto8\"/><ref name=\"auto7\"/>\nStores specializing in medical supplies no longer had alcohol gels and masks, including [[N95 mask]]s used by health professionals. Street vendors were reported to be taking advantage of the demand for equipment and trying to profit from it.<ref name=\"auto4\"/>\n\n[[File:Capacita\u00e7\u00e3o dos profissionais da Sa\u00fade que atuar\u00e3o nos terminais de \u00f4nibus - 49667698972.jpg|thumb|Health professionals clean up public transport to prevent spread]]\n\nOn 20 March, it was reported by the press that Brazil was contradicting the recommendation of the [[World Health Organization]] by only testing patients in severe condition. Jo\u00e3o Gabbardo, executive secretary at the Ministry of Health, said that the criteria adopted would not change, and people with serious cases will be tested for COVID-19.<ref name=\"auto2\"/> The following day, a group of scientists announced they were developing new COVID-19 tests in Brazil. They expect to elaborate a test which will work with a single drop of blood from the patient. They expect it to be ready for the current outbreak of COVID-19, and hope to engage some of the main Brazilian universities in its development.<ref name=\"auto6\"/>\nWithout protective items, health workers improvise caps like masks in hospitals. In addition to the first cases of coronavirus in Acre, health professionals in the state have to deal with the lack of Personal Protective Equipment (PPE). Some agents are improvising caps like masks.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://istoe.com.br/sem-itens-de-protecao-agentes-de-saude-improvisam-toucas-como-mascaras-em-hospitais/|title=Sem itens de prote\u00e7\u00e3o, agentes de sa\u00fade improvisam toucas como m\u00e1scaras em hospitais|date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nHealth professionals in RJ complain about the lack of conditions to work with patients in COVID-19. Doctor says there are no N95 masks, with more efficient filter, at Hospital Salgado Filho. Unions say there is a shortage of personal protective equipment in hospitals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/20/profissionais-de-saude-do-rj-reclamam-da-falta-de-condicoes-para-trabalhar-com-pacientes-de-covid-19.ghtml|title=Profissionais de sa\u00fade do RJ reclamam da falta de condi\u00e7\u00f5es para trabalhar com pacientes de Covid-19|website=G1|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320182757/https://g1.globo.com/rj/rio-de-janeiro/noticia/2020/03/20/profissionais-de-saude-do-rj-reclamam-da-falta-de-condicoes-para-trabalhar-com-pacientes-de-covid-19.ghtml|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Religious services===\n[[Odilo Scherer|Dom Odilo Scherer]], [[archdiocese of S\u00e3o Paulo|Archbishop of S\u00e3o Paulo]] had initially defended that churches should not be closed, arguing that there should be more daily services to diffuse large gatherings. Later, he determined the suspension of celebrations with the people.<ref name=igrejas/><ref>{{cite web|title=Comunicado sobre a suspens\u00e3o tempor\u00e1ria de Celebra\u00e7\u00f5es Religiosas|url=http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-sobre-a-suspensao-temporaria-de-celebracoes-religiosas|date=21 March 2020|access-date=21 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326200303/http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-sobre-a-suspensao-temporaria-de-celebracoes-religiosas|archive-date=26 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Comunicado n\u00b02 da Arquidiocese de S\u00e3o Paulo sobre Celebra\u00e7\u00f5es e outras A\u00e7\u00f5es Pastorais nas igrejas durante a pandemia do Coronav\u00edrus|url=http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-ndeg2-da-arquidiocese-de-sao-paulo-sobre-celebracoes-e-outras-acoes-pastorais-nas-igrejas-durante-a-pandemia-do-coronavirus|date=26 March 2020|access-date=28 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331203026/http://arquisp.org.br/noticias/comunicado-ndeg2-da-arquidiocese-de-sao-paulo-sobre-celebracoes-e-outras-acoes-pastorais-nas-igrejas-durante-a-pandemia-do-coronavirus|archive-date=31 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Bishop [[Edir Macedo]], founder of the [[Universal Church of the Kingdom of God]] has also defended that services should not be suspended, as well as [[Silas Malafaia]], leader of [[Assembleias de Deus|Assembleia de Deus Vit\u00f3ria em Cristo]].<ref name=igrejas>{{cite web|url=https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-20/igrejas-desafiam-recomendacao-de-suspender-missas-e-cultos-diante-da-pandemia-do-coronavirus.html|title=Igrejas desafiam recomenda\u00e7\u00e3o de suspender missas e cultos diante da pandemia do coronav\u00edrus|first=Breiller|last=Pires|date=20 March 2020|website=EL PA\u00cdS|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321155318/https://brasil.elpais.com/brasil/2020-03-20/igrejas-desafiam-recomendacao-de-suspender-missas-e-cultos-diante-da-pandemia-do-coronavirus.html|archive-date=21 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Malafaia said he would only close his churches if mandated by a court order. Macedo has caused greater controversy after he dismissed coronavirus as a creation of the media.<ref>{{cite web|title=M\u00f4nica Bergamo: V\u00eddeo mostra Edir Macedo dizendo que coronav\u00edrus \u00e9 inofensivo e que Satan\u00e1s e m\u00eddia promovem medo|url=https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/video-mostra-edir-macedo-dizendo-que-coronavirus-e-inofensivo-e-que-satanas-e-midia-promovem-medo.shtml|date=15 March 2020|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064430/https://www1.folha.uol.com.br/colunas/monicabergamo/2020/03/video-mostra-edir-macedo-dizendo-que-coronavirus-e-inofensivo-e-que-satanas-e-midia-promovem-medo.shtml|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Television programming===\nBrazilian networks started airing prevention tips during their programming. [[Rede Globo|Globo]], [[Sistema Brasileiro de Televis\u00e3o|SBT]], [[RecordTV]], [[Rede Bandeirantes|Band]], and [[RedeTV!]] announced they would stop production of all of their ''[[telenovelas]]'', and would record their [[talk shows]] without a live audience, while expanding journalism in their programming.<ref>{{cite web | last=Padiglione | first=Cristina | title=Em razao do coronavirus, Domingao do Faustao vai ao ar sem plateia pela 1 vez em 31 anos | publisher=[[Folha de S.Paulo]] | date=12 March 2020 | url=https://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/em-razao-coronavirus-domingao-faustao-vai-ao-ar-sem-plateia-pela-1a-vez-em-31-anos | accessdate=13 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064434/https://telepadi.folha.uol.com.br/em-razao-coronavirus-domingao-faustao-vai-ao-ar-sem-plateia-pela-1a-vez-em-31-anos | archive-date=22 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Oliveira | first=Fernando | title=Com medo do coronavirus, Raul Gil cancela grava\u00c7ao e se isola em sitio | publisher=[[Universo Online|UOL]] | date=13 March 2020 | url=https://tvefamosos.uol.com.br/colunas/fefito/2020/03/13/com-medo-do-coronavirus-raul-gil-se-isola-em-sitio.html | accessdate=13 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064431/https://tvefamosos.uol.com.br/colunas/fefito/2020/03/13/com-medo-do-coronavirus-raul-gil-se-isola-em-sitio.html | archive-date=22 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=RedeTV! cancela plateia do Encrenca com medo do surto de coronavirus | publisher=[[Universo Online|Noticias da TV \u2013 UOL]] | date=12 March 2020 | url=https://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/televisao/redetv-cancela-plateia-do-encrenca-com-medo-do-surto-de-coronavirus-34432 | accessdate=13 March 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322064431/https://noticiasdatv.uol.com.br/noticia/televisao/redetv-cancela-plateia-do-encrenca-com-medo-do-surto-de-coronavirus-34432 | archive-date=22 March 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n \n\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil/Statistics}}\n{{:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil/Statistics}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.saude.gov.br/saude-de-a-z/coronavirus COVID-19 in Brazil] \u2013 Ministry of Health\n* {{cite web |url=https://coronavirus-global.com/brazil |title=Coronavirus Brazil updates and news |trans-title=Latest news and statistics of coronavirus in Brazil. |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=English, French, Spanish, Portuguese, German, Italian, Swedish, Norwegian, Finnish, Estonian, Russian}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|Brazil|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Brazil]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in South America|Brazil]]\n[[Category:2020 in Brazil|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health disasters in Brazil|Coronavirus]]\n", "name_user": "Coltsfan", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Brazil"}
{"title_page": "Pin Ups", "text_new": "{{other uses|Pin-up (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Pinups\n| type       = Studio album\n| artist     = [[David Bowie]]\n| cover      = PinUps.jpg\n| alt        = yes\n| released   = {{Start date|1973|10|19|df=y}}\n| recorded   = 8 July \u2013 August 1973<ref>{{cite book |title=Hallo Spaceboy: The Rebirth of David Bowie |last=Thompson |first=Dave |year=2006 |publisher=ECW Press |isbn=9781550227338 |page=313}}</ref>\n| venue      =\n| studio     = [[Ch\u00e2teau d'H\u00e9rouville]], [[H\u00e9rouville]], [[Val-d'Oise]] France\n| genre      = {{flatlist|\n* [[Glam rock]]<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/cover-albums-the-best-and-worst-releases-in-the-genre-8764391.html | title=Cover albums: The best and worst releases in the genre | work=[[The Independent]] | date=16 August 2013 | accessdate=6 July 2015 | author=Perrone, Pierre | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714094911/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/cover-albums-the-best-and-worst-releases-in-the-genre-8764391.html | archive-date=14 July 2015 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[proto-punk]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.stereogum.com/1291641/david-bowie-albums-from-worst-to-best/franchises/counting-down/attachment/pinups/ | title=David Bowie Albums From Worst To Best: Pin Ups | work=[[Stereogum]] | accessdate=6 July 2015 | author=Lariviere, Aaron | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627202712/http://www.stereogum.com/1291641/david-bowie-albums-from-worst-to-best/franchises/counting-down/attachment/pinups/ | archive-date=27 June 2015 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n| length     = 33:42\n| label      = [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[Ken Scott]]\n* David Bowie\n}}\n| prev_title = [[Aladdin Sane]]\n| prev_year  = 1973\n| next_title = [[Diamond Dogs]]\n| next_year  = 1974\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Pinups\n | type        = Studio album\n | single1     = [[Sorrow (McCoys song)#David Bowie version|Sorrow]]\n | single1date = 28 September 1973\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Pinups''''' (also referred to as '''''Pin Ups''''' and '''''Pin-Ups''''') is the seventh studio album by English musician [[David Bowie]], released in October 1973 by [[RCA Records]]. It is a [[Cover version|covers album]], featuring covers of songs by bands such as the [[Pretty Things]], [[the Who]], [[the Yardbirds]] and [[Pink Floyd]]. Like his two previous albums, it was produced by Bowie and [[Ken Scott]] and features contributions from two members of Bowie's backing band [[the Spiders from Mars]] \u2013 [[Mick Ronson]] and [[Trevor Bolder]]; [[Mick Woodmansey]] was replaced by [[Aynsley Dunbar]] on drums. It was recorded in July and August 1973 at the [[Ch\u00e2teau d'H\u00e9rouville]] in [[H\u00e9rouville]], France.\n\nPreceded by [[Sorrow (The McCoys song)#David Bowie version|his cover]] of [[the McCoys]]' song \"[[Sorrow (The McCoys song)|Sorrow]]\", ''Pinups'' peaked at No. 1 on the [[UK Albums Chart]], bringing the total number of Bowie albums concurrently on the UK chart to six. However, since release, the album has received generally unfavorable reviews from music critics, many of whom criticised the songs as generally inferior to their original counterparts. It was remastered in 2015 as part of the box set ''[[Five Years (1969\u20131973)]]''.<ref name=\"five years box set\">{{Cite AV media notes|title=Five Years (1969\u20131973)|others=[[David Bowie]]|year=2015|publisher=[[Parlophone]]|location=UK, Europe & US|type=Box set liner notes|id=DBXL 1}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nAccording to co-producer [[Ken Scott]], the LP was originally conceived as \"a complete opposite of [Bowie's] other albums\", consisting of all cover songs except one original composition, and mainly turned towards the US market since \"he wanted to do songs that weren't known as well in the States as they were in England\", yet eventually the plan was dropped.<ref>{{citation |last1=Scott |first1=Ken |title=Abbey Road to Ziggy Stardust: Off-the-record with The Beatles, Bowie, Elton, and so much more. |publisher=Alfred Music Publishing Co. |edition=1st |year=2012}}</ref> ''Pinups'' was the first of two \"1960s nostalgia\" albums that Bowie had planned to release. The second, which was planned to be called \"Bowie-ing Out,\" would have contained Bowie covering his favourite American artists, but was never recorded.<ref>{{citation |last1=Kamp |first1=Thomas |title=David Bowie: The Wild-Eyed Boy 1964\u20131984 |publisher=O'Sullivan, Woodside & Co. |edition=1st |year=1985}}</ref> Bowie also apparently considered making a ''Pinups'' sequel: he had compiled a list of songs he wanted to cover, some of which showed up on his later releases of ''[[Heathen (David Bowie album)|Heathen]]'' (2002) and ''[[Reality (David Bowie album)|Reality]]'' (2003).<ref name=SOS03>{{citation | url=http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/oct03/articles/reality.htm | title=David Bowie & Tony Visconti Recording Reality | date=October 2003 | accessdate=30 July 2013 | first=Richard | last=Buskin | journal=[[Sound on Sound]] | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150606111145/http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/oct03/articles/reality.htm | archive-date=6 June 2015 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn the album booklet, Bowie, writing in his own hand,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soundstation.dk/images/products/large/57/121857-b.jpg |title=Image |date= |accessdate=2016-10-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304082843/http://www.soundstation.dk/images/products/large/57/121857-b.jpg |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> describes ''Pinups'' as:\n\n{{Quote|These songs are among my favourites from the '64\u201367' period of London. / Most of the groups were playing the [[Ricky-Tick]] (was it a 'y' or an 'i'?) -Scene club circuit (Marquee, eel pie island la-la). / Some are still with us. / [[Pretty Things]], [[Them (band)|Them]], [[Yardbirds]], Syd's [[Pink Floyd]], [[Mojos]], [[The Who|Who]], [[Easybeats]], [[Merseys]], [[The Kinks]]. / Love-on ya!}}\n\nThe woman on the cover with Bowie is 1960s supermodel [[Twiggy]] in a photograph taken by her then-manager [[Justin de Villeneuve]].<ref name=\"Phillips\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2012/may/16/photography-justin-villeneuve-best-shot|title=Justin de Villeneuve's best photograph: David Bowie and Twiggy|last=Phillips|first=Sarah|date=16 May 2012|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=8 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215914/http://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2012/may/16/photography-justin-villeneuve-best-shot|archive-date=4 October 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> It was shot in Paris for ''[[Vogue (British magazine)|Vogue]]'' magazine, but at Bowie's request was used for the album instead.<ref name=\"Phillips\" />\n\nA version of [[the Velvet Underground]]'s \"[[White Light/White Heat (song)|White Light/White Heat]]\" was recorded during the sessions. It was never released; Bowie donated the backing track to [[Mick Ronson]] for his 1975 album ''[[Play Don't Worry]]''.\n\nAn insert included with the original LP includes the text \"This album is called Pinups\" and the title is written as one word, without a hyphen, on the LP cover and spine, although the disc label spells the title with a hyphen.\n\n==Release and reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"Eder AllMusic\">{{cite web |last=Eder |first=Bruce |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/pin-ups-mw0000034411 |title=''Pin Ups'' \u2013 David Bowie Album Review |accessdate=20 March 2020 |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905124113/https://www.allmusic.com/album/pin-ups-mw0000034411 |archive-date=5 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Encyclopedia of Popular Music]]''\n| rev2score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite book |title=The Encyclopedia of Popular Music |publisher=[[Omnibus Press]] |edition=5th concise |year=2011 |last=Larkin |first=Colin |authorlink=Colin Larkin (writer) |title-link=Encyclopedia of Popular Music }}</ref>\n| rev3 = [[MusicHound]]\n| rev3score = 3/5<ref>{{cite book|last1=Graff|first1=Gary|last2=Durchholz|first2=Daniel (eds)|title=MusicHound Rock: The Essential Album Guide|publisher=Visible Ink Press|location=Farmington Hills, MI|year=1999|isbn=1-57859-061-2|page=[https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781578590612/page/151 151]|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781578590612/page/151}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev4score = 5.9/10<ref name=\"Wolk Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/21066-five-years-1969-1973/|title=David Bowie: ''Five Years 1969\u20131973''|first=Douglas|last=Wolk|date=1 October 2015|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate=13 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160206231305/http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/21066-five-years-1969-1973/|archive-date=6 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|rev5 = ''[[Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies|Christgau's Record Guide]]''\n|rev5Score = B\u2013<ref name=christgau>{{cite book|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|year=1981|title=Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies|publisher=[[Ticknor & Fields]]|isbn=089919026X|chapter=Consumer Guide '70s: B|chapter-url=https://www.robertchristgau.com/get_chap.php?k=B&bk=70|accessdate=February 22, 2019|via=robertchristgau.com|title-link=Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev6score = (unfavourable)<ref name=\"RS Shaw\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/pin-ups-19731220 |title=Pin Ups |date=19 July 1973 |last=Shaw |first=Greg |accessdate=1 October 2015 |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151004093034/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/pin-ups-19731220 |archive-date=4 October 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[The Rolling Stone Album Guide]]''\n| rev7Score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/artists/david-bowie/albumguide |title=David Bowie: Album Guide |website=[[Rolling Stone]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110530073307/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/artists/david-bowie/albumguide |archivedate=30 May 2011 |accessdate=13 January 2016}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Select (magazine)|Select]]''\n| rev8score = 2/5<ref>{{cite web |url=http://selectmagazinescans.monkeon.co.uk/showpage.php?file=wp-content/uploads/2013/10/reissues2.jpg |title=Stardust Memories |date=August 1990 |accessdate=11 September 2017 |work=[[Select (magazine)|Select]] |page=116 |last=Griffiths |first=Nick |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170912011356/http://selectmagazinescans.monkeon.co.uk/showpage.php?file=wp-content%2Fuploads%2F2013%2F10%2Freissues2.jpg |archive-date=12 September 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Pinups'' was released on 19 October 1973 by [[RCA Records]] under the catalogue number RS 1003 in the UK,<ref>{{Cite AV media notes|title=Pin Ups|others=[[David Bowie]]|year=1973|publisher=[[RCA Records|RCA Victor]]|location=UK|type=liner notes|id=RS 1003}}</ref> only six months after his previous album ''[[Aladdin Sane]]''. ''Pinups'' entered the UK chart on 3 November 1973 (coincidentally the same day as [[Bryan Ferry]]'s covers album ''[[These Foolish Things (album)|These Foolish Things]]'') and stayed there for 21 weeks, eventually peaking at No. 1. It brought the total number of Bowie albums concurrently on the UK chart to six.{{sfn|Sandford|1997|p=115}} It re-entered the chart on 30 April 1983, this time for 15 weeks, peaking at No. 57. In July 1990, it again entered the chart, for one week, at No. 52. The lead single, a cover of [[the McCoys]]' \"[[Sorrow (The McCoys song)|Sorrow]]\", peaked at No. 3 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].\n\nSince release, the album has received generally unfavorable reviews from music critics, many of whom criticised the songs as generally inferior to their original counterparts. In a review for ''Pinups'' on release, Greg Shaw of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' gave the album an unfavorable review, writing, \"Although many of the tracks are excellent, none stands up to the originals.\"<ref name=\"RS Shaw\" /> He further believed that all the tracks were underproduced and believed Bowie's vocal performance to be the album's \"true failure\", believing his \"excessively mannered voice\" was \"a ridiculously weak mismatch for the material\" and that they were mixed too high to give the tracks the \"edge\" or \"punch\" they need to be effective.<ref name=\"RS Shaw\" /> He concludes his review saying, \"while ''Pinups'' may be a failure, it is also a collection of great songs, most of which are given a more than adequate, and always loving, treatment. Maybe the fairest conclusion to draw is that Bowie can\u2019t sing any other way, did the best he could, and the result isn\u2019t all that bad.\"<ref name=\"RS Shaw\" /> When reviewing the album as part of the 2015 box set ''[[Five Years (1969\u20131973)]]'', Douglas Wolk of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' gave the album an unfavorable review, calling it a \"quick-and-sloppy covers album\".<ref name=\"Wolk Pitchfork\" /> Although he believed the album was \"more interesting in theory\", he found that the execution was sloppy, believing that all the original versions were \"vastly\" superior and Bowie added nothing interesting to any of them. He further believed that it didn't help that [[the Spiders from Mars]] were falling apart when recording it.<ref name=\"Wolk Pitchfork\" /> Bruce Eder of [[AllMusic]] similarly found the album to be out of place with Bowie's output up to that point.<ref name=\"Eder AllMusic\" /> He continued, \"''Ziggy Stardust'' and ''Aladdin Sane'' had established Bowie as perhaps the most fiercely original of all England's glam rockers, so an album of covers didn't make any sense and was especially confusing for American fans,\" further criticising the song choices as unknown.<ref name=\"Eder AllMusic\" /> However, Eder went on to praise Bowie's cover of \"Sorrow\", arguing that it's a \"distinct improvement\" over the original. He states that although the album is dismissed by many as just another covers album, Eder views it as an artistic statement and in the context of Bowie's entire career, it represented a \"swan song\" for the Spiders from Mars and an \"interlude\" between the first and second phases of his international career, with his next album ''[[Diamond Dogs]]'' being the end of his glam rock era. He concludes his review writing, \"It's not a bad bridge between the two, and it has endured across the decades.\"<ref name=\"Eder AllMusic\" />\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| headline     = Side one\n| extra_column = Originally by\n| title1       = [[Rosalyn (song)|Rosalyn]]\n| writer1      = [[Jimmy Duncan (songwriter)|Jimmy Duncan]], Bill Farley\n| extra1       = [[Pretty Things]]\n| length1      = 2:27\n| title2       = [[Here Comes the Night]]\n| note2        = *\n| writer2      = [[Bert Berns]]\n| extra2       = [[Them (band)|Them]]\n| length2      = 3:09\n| title3       = [[I Wish You Would (Billy Boy Arnold song)|I Wish You Would]]\n| note3        = *\n| writer3      = [[Billy Boy Arnold]]\n| extra3       = [[The Yardbirds]]\n| length3      = 2:40\n| title4       = [[See Emily Play]]\n| writer4      = [[Syd Barrett]]\n| extra4       = [[Pink Floyd]]\n| length4      = 4:03\n| title5       = [[Everything's Alright (The Mojos song)|Everything's Alright]]\n| writer5      = Nicky Crouch, John Konrad, Simon Stavely, Stuart James, Keith Karlson\n| extra5       = [[The Mojos]]\n| length5      = 2:26\n| title6       = [[I Can't Explain]]\n| writer6      = [[Pete Townshend]]\n| extra6       = [[The Who]]\n| length6      = 2:07\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline     = Side two\n| extra_column = Originally by\n| title1       = [[Friday on My Mind]]\n| writer1      = [[George Young (rock musician)|George Young]], [[Harry Vanda]]\n| extra1       = [[The Easybeats]]\n| length1      = 3:18\n| title2       = [[Sorrow (The McCoys song)|Sorrow]]\n| note2        = *\n| writer2      = Bob Feldman, [[Jerry Goldstein (record producer, musician)|Jerry Goldstein]], [[Richard Gottehrer]]\n| extra2       = [[The McCoys]]\n| length2      = 2:48\n| title3       = [[Don't Bring Me Down (Pretty Things song)|Don't Bring Me Down]]\n| writer3      = [[Fairies (British band)|Johnnie Dee]]\n| extra3       = [[Pretty Things]]\n| length3      = 2:01\n| title4      = [[Shapes of Things]]\n| writer4     = [[Paul Samwell-Smith]], [[Jim McCarty]], [[Keith Relf]]\n| extra4      = [[The Yardbirds]]\n| length4     = 2:47\n| title5      = [[Anyway, Anyhow, Anywhere]]\n| writer5     = [[Roger Daltrey]], Townshend\n| extra5      = The Who\n| length5     = 3:04\n| title6      = [[Where Have All the Good Times Gone]]\n| writer6     = [[Ray Davies]]\n| extra6      = [[The Kinks]]\n| length6     = 2:35\n}}\n\n* Sides one and two were combined as tracks 1\u201312 on CD reissues.\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline     = Bonus Tracks (1990 Rykodisc/EMI)\n| extra_column = Originally by\n| title13      = [[Growin' Up]]\n| note13       = Previously unreleased; from the early ''[[Diamond Dogs]]'' sessions\n| writer13     = [[Bruce Springsteen]]\n| extra13      = Bruce Springsteen\n| length13     = 3:26\n| title14      = [[Amsterdam (Jacques Brel song)|Port of Amsterdam]]\n| note14       = [[A-side and B-side|B-side]] of the \"Sorrow\" single\n| writer14     = [[Jacques Brel]], <abbr title=\"translated by\">trans.</abbr> [[Mort Shuman]]\n| extra14      = Jacques Brel\n| length14     = 3:19\n}}\n\nSongs marked with a <nowiki>*</nowiki> were not recorded for the first time by the acts listed, but were popularized by them.\n\n== Personnel ==\n*[[David Bowie]] \u2013 vocals, guitar, [[tenor saxophone|tenor]] and [[alto saxophone]], [[harmonica]], [[arrangement]]s, backing vocals, [[Moog synthesiser]]<ref name=allmusiccredits>{{cite web |url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r2484|pure_url=yes}} |title=allmusic ((( Pin Ups > Credits ))) |accessdate=15 July 2008 |publisher=allmusic}}</ref>\n*[[Mick Ronson]] \u2013 guitar, piano, vocals, arrangements<ref name=allmusiccredits />\n*[[Trevor Bolder]] \u2013 bass guitar\n*[[Aynsley Dunbar]] \u2013 drums\n\n=== Additional personnel ===\n*[[Mike Garson]] \u2013 piano, [[organ (music)|organ]], [[harpsichord]], [[electric piano]]<ref name=allmusiccredits />\n*Ken Fordham \u2013 [[baritone saxophone]]\n*[[Warren Peace|G.A. MacCormack]] \u2013 backing vocals\n*[[Ronnie Wood]] \u2013 guitar on \"Growin' Up\"\n\n=== Production personnel ===\n*David Bowie \u2013 producer\n*[[Ken Scott]] \u2013 producer\n*Dennis MacKay \u2013 [[recording engineer|engineer]]\n*[[Andy Scott]] \u2013 [[recording engineer|engineer]]\n*Dr. Toby Mountain \u2013 [[audio mastering|mastering engineer]] (1990)\n*Jonathan Wyner \u2013 mastering assistant (1990)\n*[[Peter Mew]] \u2013 mastering engineer (1999)\n*Nigel Reeve \u2013 mastering engineer (1999)\n\n== Charts ==\n'''Album'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Chart\n!Peak position\n|-\n|1973\n|Finnish album Charts\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|1973\n|[[UK Albums Chart]]<ref name=ukt40>{{cite web |url=http://www.everyhit.com |title=UK Top 40 Hit Database |accessdate=15 July 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151106234723/http://www.everyhit.com/ |archive-date=6 November 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|1973\n|[[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' Pop Albums]]<ref name=allmusicalbums>{{cite web |url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r2484|pure_url=yes}} |title=allmusic ((( Pin Ups > Charts & Awards > Billboard Albums ))) |accessdate=15 July 2008 |publisher=allmusic}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|23\n|-\n|1973\n|Norwegian album Charts\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|-\n|1973\n|Australian [[Kent Report]] album Charts\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4\n|}\n\n'''Single'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Single\n!Chart\n!Peak position\n|-\n|1973\n|\"Sorrow\"\n|[[UK Singles Chart]]<ref name=ukt40 />\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n|}\n\n==Certifications and sales==\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|title=Pin Ups|type=album|artist=David Bowie|relyear=1974|region=Australia|award=Gold|salesamount=100,000$|certref=<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Billboard/70s/1974/Billboard%201974-10-26.pdf|title=Australian Gold|date=26 October 1974|website=Billboard|page=78|via=American Radio History|accessdate=20 November 2019}}</ref>}}\n{{certification Table Entry|title=Pin Ups|type=album|artist=David Bowie|relyear=1974|region=France|nocert=true|salesamount=130,300|salesref=<ref>{{cite web|url=http://infodisc.fr/Ventes_Albums_Tout_Temps.php?debut=3400|title=InfoDisc : Les Meilleurs Ventes d'Albums \"Tout Temps\" (33 T. / Cd / T\u00e9l\u00e9chargement)|first=InfoDisc, Daniel Lesueur, Dominic Durand|last=Lesueur|date=|website=infodisc.fr|accessdate=20 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191201150134/http://infodisc.fr/Ventes_Albums_Tout_Temps.php?debut=3400|archive-date=1 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n{{certification Table Entry|title=Pin Ups|type=album|artist=David Bowie|relyear=1974|certyear=1973|region=United Kingdom|award=Gold|salesamount=147,000|salesref= <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Billboard/70s/1973/Billboard%201973-10-20.pdf|title=From the Music Capitals of the World|publisher=Billboard|via=American Radio History|page=61|date=20 October 1973|accessdate=20 November 2019}}</ref>}}\n{{certification Table Bottom}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n;Sources\n* {{cite book|last=Sandford|first=Christopher|title=Bowie: Loving the Alien|publisher=Time Warner|year=1997|origyear=First published 1996|isbn=978-0-306-80854-8|ref=harv|url=https://archive.org/details/bowielovingalien00sand}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.5years.com/pinups.htm ''Pinups'' at The Ziggy Stardust Companion]\n*{{discogs master|22208|Pinups}}\n\n{{David Bowie}}\n\n[[Category:1973 albums]]\n[[Category:David Bowie albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by David Bowie]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Ken Scott]]\n[[Category:Albums with cover art by Mick Rock]]\n[[Category:Covers albums]]\n[[Category:EMI Records albums]]\n[[Category:Glam rock albums by English artists]]\n[[Category:Parlophone albums]]\n[[Category:RCA Records albums]]\n[[Category:Rykodisc albums]]\n[[Category:Virgin Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded in a home studio]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses|Pin-up (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Pinups\n| type       = Studio album\n| artist     = [[David Bowie]]\n| cover      = PinUps.jpg\n| alt        = yes\n| released   = {{Start date|1973|10|19|df=y}}\n| recorded   = 8 July \u2013 August 1973<ref>{{cite book |title=Hallo Spaceboy: The Rebirth of David Bowie |last=Thompson |first=Dave |year=2006 |publisher=ECW Press |isbn=9781550227338 |page=313}}</ref>\n| venue      =\n| studio     = [[Ch\u00e2teau d'H\u00e9rouville]], [[H\u00e9rouville]], [[Val-d'Oise]] France\n| genre      = {{flatlist|\n* [[Glam rock]]<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/cover-albums-the-best-and-worst-releases-in-the-genre-8764391.html | title=Cover albums: The best and worst releases in the genre | work=[[The Independent]] | date=16 August 2013 | accessdate=6 July 2015 | author=Perrone, Pierre | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714094911/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/features/cover-albums-the-best-and-worst-releases-in-the-genre-8764391.html | archive-date=14 July 2015 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[proto-punk]]<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.stereogum.com/1291641/david-bowie-albums-from-worst-to-best/franchises/counting-down/attachment/pinups/ | title=David Bowie Albums From Worst To Best: Pin Ups | work=[[Stereogum]] | accessdate=6 July 2015 | author=Lariviere, Aaron | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627202712/http://www.stereogum.com/1291641/david-bowie-albums-from-worst-to-best/franchises/counting-down/attachment/pinups/ | archive-date=27 June 2015 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n| length     = 33:42\n| label      = [[RCA Records|RCA]]\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[Ken Scott]]\n* David Bowie\n}}\n| prev_title = [[Aladdin Sane]]\n| prev_year  = 1973\n| next_title = [[Diamond Dogs]]\n| next_year  = 1974\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Pinups\n | type        = Studio album\n | single1     = [[Sorrow (McCoys song)#David Bowie version|Sorrow]]\n | single1date = 28 September 1973\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Pinups''''' (also referred to as '''''Pin Ups''''' and '''''Pin-Ups''''') is the seventh studio album by English musician [[David Bowie]], released in October 1973 on [[RCA Records]]. Like his two previous albums, it was produced by Bowie and [[Ken Scott]] and features contributions from two members of Bowie's backing band [[the Spiders from Mars]] \u2013 [[Mick Ronson]] and [[Trevor Bolder]]; [[Mick Woodmansey]] was replaced by [[Aynsley Dunbar]] on drums. It is a [[Cover version|covers album]], featuring covers of songs by bands such as the [[Pretty Things]], [[the Who]], [[the Yardbirds]] and [[Pink Floyd]].\n\nPreceded by [[Sorrow (The McCoys song)#David Bowie version|his cover]] of [[the McCoys]]' song \"[[Sorrow (The McCoys song)|Sorrow]]\", ''Pinups'' peaked at No. 1 on the [[UK Albums Chart]], bringing the total number of Bowie albums concurrently on the UK chart to six. However, since release, the album has received generally unfavorable reviews from music critics, many of whom criticised the songs as generally inferior to their original counterparts. It was remastered in 2015 as part of the box set ''[[Five Years (1969\u20131973)]]''.<ref name=\"five years box set\">{{Cite AV media notes|title=Five Years (1969\u20131973)|others=[[David Bowie]]|year=2015|publisher=[[Parlophone]]|location=UK, Europe & US|type=Box set liner notes|id=DBXL 1}}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nAccording to co-producer [[Ken Scott]], the LP was originally conceived as \"a complete opposite of [Bowie's] other albums\", consisting of all cover songs except one original composition, and mainly turned towards the US market since \"he wanted to do songs that weren't known as well in the States as they were in England\", yet eventually the plan was dropped.<ref>{{citation |last1=Scott |first1=Ken |title=Abbey Road to Ziggy Stardust: Off-the-record with The Beatles, Bowie, Elton, and so much more. |publisher=Alfred Music Publishing Co. |edition=1st |year=2012}}</ref> ''Pinups'' was the first of two \"1960s nostalgia\" albums that Bowie had planned to release. The second, which was planned to be called \"Bowie-ing Out,\" would have contained Bowie covering his favourite American artists, but was never recorded.<ref>{{citation |last1=Kamp |first1=Thomas |title=David Bowie: The Wild-Eyed Boy 1964\u20131984 |publisher=O'Sullivan, Woodside & Co. |edition=1st |year=1985}}</ref> Bowie also apparently considered making a ''Pinups'' sequel: he had compiled a list of songs he wanted to cover, some of which showed up on his later releases of ''[[Heathen (David Bowie album)|Heathen]]'' (2002) and ''[[Reality (David Bowie album)|Reality]]'' (2003).<ref name=SOS03>{{citation | url=http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/oct03/articles/reality.htm | title=David Bowie & Tony Visconti Recording Reality | date=October 2003 | accessdate=30 July 2013 | first=Richard | last=Buskin | journal=[[Sound on Sound]] | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150606111145/http://www.soundonsound.com/sos/oct03/articles/reality.htm | archive-date=6 June 2015 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn the album booklet, Bowie, writing in his own hand,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.soundstation.dk/images/products/large/57/121857-b.jpg |title=Image |date= |accessdate=2016-10-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304082843/http://www.soundstation.dk/images/products/large/57/121857-b.jpg |archive-date=4 March 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> describes ''Pinups'' as:\n\n{{Quote|These songs are among my favourites from the '64\u201367' period of London. / Most of the groups were playing the [[Ricky-Tick]] (was it a 'y' or an 'i'?) -Scene club circuit (Marquee, eel pie island la-la). / Some are still with us. / [[Pretty Things]], [[Them (band)|Them]], [[Yardbirds]], Syd's [[Pink Floyd]], [[Mojos]], [[The Who|Who]], [[Easybeats]], [[Merseys]], [[The Kinks]]. / Love-on ya!}}\n\nThe woman on the cover with Bowie is 1960s supermodel [[Twiggy]] in a photograph taken by her then-manager [[Justin de Villeneuve]].<ref name=\"Phillips\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2012/may/16/photography-justin-villeneuve-best-shot|title=Justin de Villeneuve's best photograph: David Bowie and Twiggy|last=Phillips|first=Sarah|date=16 May 2012|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=8 October 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215914/http://www.theguardian.com/artanddesign/2012/may/16/photography-justin-villeneuve-best-shot|archive-date=4 October 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> It was shot in Paris for ''[[Vogue (British magazine)|Vogue]]'' magazine, but at Bowie's request was used for the album instead.<ref name=\"Phillips\" />\n\nA version of [[the Velvet Underground]]'s \"[[White Light/White Heat (song)|White Light/White Heat]]\" was recorded during the sessions. It was never released; Bowie donated the backing track to [[Mick Ronson]] for his 1975 album ''[[Play Don't Worry]]''.\n\nAn insert included with the original LP includes the text \"This album is called Pinups\" and the title is written as one word, without a hyphen, on the LP cover and spine, although the disc label spells the title with a hyphen.\n\n==Release and reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=\"Eder AllMusic\">{{cite web |last=Eder |first=Bruce |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/pin-ups-mw0000034411 |title=''Pin Ups'' \u2013 David Bowie Album Review |accessdate=20 March 2020 |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905124113/https://www.allmusic.com/album/pin-ups-mw0000034411 |archive-date=5 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Encyclopedia of Popular Music]]''\n| rev2score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite book |title=The Encyclopedia of Popular Music |publisher=[[Omnibus Press]] |edition=5th concise |year=2011 |last=Larkin |first=Colin |authorlink=Colin Larkin (writer) |title-link=Encyclopedia of Popular Music }}</ref>\n| rev3 = [[MusicHound]]\n| rev3score = 3/5<ref>{{cite book|last1=Graff|first1=Gary|last2=Durchholz|first2=Daniel (eds)|title=MusicHound Rock: The Essential Album Guide|publisher=Visible Ink Press|location=Farmington Hills, MI|year=1999|isbn=1-57859-061-2|page=[https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781578590612/page/151 151]|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/isbn_9781578590612/page/151}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev4score = 5.9/10<ref name=\"Wolk Pitchfork\">{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/21066-five-years-1969-1973/|title=David Bowie: ''Five Years 1969\u20131973''|first=Douglas|last=Wolk|date=1 October 2015|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate=13 January 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160206231305/http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/21066-five-years-1969-1973/|archive-date=6 February 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|rev5 = ''[[Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies|Christgau's Record Guide]]''\n|rev5Score = B\u2013<ref name=christgau>{{cite book|last=Christgau|first=Robert|authorlink=Robert Christgau|year=1981|title=Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies|publisher=[[Ticknor & Fields]]|isbn=089919026X|chapter=Consumer Guide '70s: B|chapter-url=https://www.robertchristgau.com/get_chap.php?k=B&bk=70|accessdate=February 22, 2019|via=robertchristgau.com|title-link=Christgau's Record Guide: Rock Albums of the Seventies}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev6score = (unfavourable)<ref name=\"RS Shaw\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/pin-ups-19731220 |title=Pin Ups |date=19 July 1973 |last=Shaw |first=Greg |accessdate=1 October 2015 |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151004093034/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/pin-ups-19731220 |archive-date=4 October 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[The Rolling Stone Album Guide]]''\n| rev7Score = {{Rating|2|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/artists/david-bowie/albumguide |title=David Bowie: Album Guide |website=[[Rolling Stone]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110530073307/http://www.rollingstone.com/music/artists/david-bowie/albumguide |archivedate=30 May 2011 |accessdate=13 January 2016}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Select (magazine)|Select]]''\n| rev8score = 2/5<ref>{{cite web |url=http://selectmagazinescans.monkeon.co.uk/showpage.php?file=wp-content/uploads/2013/10/reissues2.jpg |title=Stardust Memories |date=August 1990 |accessdate=11 September 2017 |work=[[Select (magazine)|Select]] |page=116 |last=Griffiths |first=Nick |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170912011356/http://selectmagazinescans.monkeon.co.uk/showpage.php?file=wp-content%2Fuploads%2F2013%2F10%2Freissues2.jpg |archive-date=12 September 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n\n''Pinups'' was released on 19 October 1973 by [[RCA Records]] under the catalogue number RS 1003 in the UK,<ref>{{Cite AV media notes|title=Pin Ups|others=[[David Bowie]]|year=1973|publisher=[[RCA Records|RCA Victor]]|location=UK|type=liner notes|id=RS 1003}}</ref> only six months after his previous album ''[[Aladdin Sane]]''. ''Pinups'' entered the UK chart on 3 November 1973 (coincidentally the same day as [[Bryan Ferry]]'s covers album ''[[These Foolish Things (album)|These Foolish Things]]'') and stayed there for 21 weeks, eventually peaking at No. 1. It brought the total number of Bowie albums concurrently on the UK chart to six.{{sfn|Sandford|1997|p=115}} It re-entered the chart on 30 April 1983, this time for 15 weeks, peaking at No. 57. In July 1990, it again entered the chart, for one week, at No. 52. The lead single, a cover of [[the McCoys]]' \"[[Sorrow (The McCoys song)|Sorrow]]\", peaked at No. 3 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].\n\nSince release, the album has received generally unfavorable reviews from music critics, many of whom criticised the songs as generally inferior to their original counterparts. In a review for ''Pinups'' on release, Greg Shaw of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' gave the album an unfavorable review, writing, \"Although many of the tracks are excellent, none stands up to the originals.\"<ref name=\"RS Shaw\" /> He further believed that all the tracks were underproduced and believed Bowie's vocal performance to be the album's \"true failure\", believing his \"excessively mannered voice\" was \"a ridiculously weak mismatch for the material\" and that they were mixed too high to give the tracks the \"edge\" or \"punch\" they need to be effective.<ref name=\"RS Shaw\" /> He concludes his review saying, \"while ''Pinups'' may be a failure, it is also a collection of great songs, most of which are given a more than adequate, and always loving, treatment. Maybe the fairest conclusion to draw is that Bowie can\u2019t sing any other way, did the best he could, and the result isn\u2019t all that bad.\"<ref name=\"RS Shaw\" /> When reviewing the album as part of the 2015 box set ''[[Five Years (1969\u20131973)]]'', Douglas Wolk of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' gave the album an unfavorable review, calling it a \"quick-and-sloppy covers album\".<ref name=\"Wolk Pitchfork\" /> Although he believed the album was \"more interesting in theory\", he found that the execution was sloppy, believing that all the original versions were \"vastly\" superior and Bowie added nothing interesting to any of them. He further believed that it didn't help that [[the Spiders from Mars]] were falling apart when recording it.<ref name=\"Wolk Pitchfork\" /> Bruce Eder of [[AllMusic]] similarly found the album to be out of place with Bowie's output up to that point.<ref name=\"Eder AllMusic\" /> He continued, \"''Ziggy Stardust'' and ''Aladdin Sane'' had established Bowie as perhaps the most fiercely original of all England's glam rockers, so an album of covers didn't make any sense and was especially confusing for American fans,\" further criticising the song choices as unknown.<ref name=\"Eder AllMusic\" /> However, Eder went on to praise Bowie's cover of \"Sorrow\", arguing that it's a \"distinct improvement\" over the original. He states that although the album is dismissed by many as just another covers album, Eder views it as an artistic statement and in the context of Bowie's entire career, it represented a \"swan song\" for the Spiders from Mars and an \"interlude\" between the first and second phases of his international career, with his next album ''[[Diamond Dogs]]'' being the end of his glam rock era. He concludes his review writing, \"It's not a bad bridge between the two, and it has endured across the decades.\"<ref name=\"Eder AllMusic\" />\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| headline     = Side one\n| extra_column = Originally by\n| title1       = [[Rosalyn (song)|Rosalyn]]\n| writer1      = [[Jimmy Duncan (songwriter)|Jimmy Duncan]], Bill Farley\n| extra1       = [[Pretty Things]]\n| length1      = 2:27\n| title2       = [[Here Comes the Night]]\n| note2        = *\n| writer2      = [[Bert Berns]]\n| extra2       = [[Them (band)|Them]]\n| length2      = 3:09\n| title3       = [[I Wish You Would (Billy Boy Arnold song)|I Wish You Would]]\n| note3        = *\n| writer3      = [[Billy Boy Arnold]]\n| extra3       = [[The Yardbirds]]\n| length3      = 2:40\n| title4       = [[See Emily Play]]\n| writer4      = [[Syd Barrett]]\n| extra4       = [[Pink Floyd]]\n| length4      = 4:03\n| title5       = [[Everything's Alright (The Mojos song)|Everything's Alright]]\n| writer5      = Nicky Crouch, John Konrad, Simon Stavely, Stuart James, Keith Karlson\n| extra5       = [[The Mojos]]\n| length5      = 2:26\n| title6       = [[I Can't Explain]]\n| writer6      = [[Pete Townshend]]\n| extra6       = [[The Who]]\n| length6      = 2:07\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline     = Side two\n| extra_column = Originally by\n| title1       = [[Friday on My Mind]]\n| writer1      = [[George Young (rock musician)|George Young]], [[Harry Vanda]]\n| extra1       = [[The Easybeats]]\n| length1      = 3:18\n| title2       = [[Sorrow (The McCoys song)|Sorrow]]\n| note2        = *\n| writer2      = Bob Feldman, [[Jerry Goldstein (record producer, musician)|Jerry Goldstein]], [[Richard Gottehrer]]\n| extra2       = [[The McCoys]]\n| length2      = 2:48\n| title3       = [[Don't Bring Me Down (Pretty Things song)|Don't Bring Me Down]]\n| writer3      = [[Fairies (British band)|Johnnie Dee]]\n| extra3       = [[Pretty Things]]\n| length3      = 2:01\n| title4      = [[Shapes of Things]]\n| writer4     = [[Paul Samwell-Smith]], [[Jim McCarty]], [[Keith Relf]]\n| extra4      = [[The Yardbirds]]\n| length4     = 2:47\n| title5      = [[Anyway, Anyhow, Anywhere]]\n| writer5     = [[Roger Daltrey]], Townshend\n| extra5      = The Who\n| length5     = 3:04\n| title6      = [[Where Have All the Good Times Gone]]\n| writer6     = [[Ray Davies]]\n| extra6      = [[The Kinks]]\n| length6     = 2:35\n}}\n\n* Sides one and two were combined as tracks 1\u201312 on CD reissues.\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline     = Bonus Tracks (1990 Rykodisc/EMI)\n| extra_column = Originally by\n| title13      = [[Growin' Up]]\n| note13       = Previously unreleased; from the early ''[[Diamond Dogs]]'' sessions\n| writer13     = [[Bruce Springsteen]]\n| extra13      = Bruce Springsteen\n| length13     = 3:26\n| title14      = [[Amsterdam (Jacques Brel song)|Port of Amsterdam]]\n| note14       = [[A-side and B-side|B-side]] of the \"Sorrow\" single\n| writer14     = [[Jacques Brel]], <abbr title=\"translated by\">trans.</abbr> [[Mort Shuman]]\n| extra14      = Jacques Brel\n| length14     = 3:19\n}}\n\nSongs marked with a <nowiki>*</nowiki> were not recorded for the first time by the acts listed, but were popularized by them.\n\n== Personnel ==\n*[[David Bowie]] \u2013 vocals, guitar, [[tenor saxophone|tenor]] and [[alto saxophone]], [[harmonica]], [[arrangement]]s, backing vocals, [[Moog synthesiser]]<ref name=allmusiccredits>{{cite web |url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r2484|pure_url=yes}} |title=allmusic ((( Pin Ups > Credits ))) |accessdate=15 July 2008 |publisher=allmusic}}</ref>\n*[[Mick Ronson]] \u2013 guitar, piano, vocals, arrangements<ref name=allmusiccredits />\n*[[Trevor Bolder]] \u2013 bass guitar\n*[[Aynsley Dunbar]] \u2013 drums\n\n=== Additional personnel ===\n*[[Mike Garson]] \u2013 piano, [[organ (music)|organ]], [[harpsichord]], [[electric piano]]<ref name=allmusiccredits />\n*Ken Fordham \u2013 [[baritone saxophone]]\n*[[Warren Peace|G.A. MacCormack]] \u2013 backing vocals\n*[[Ronnie Wood]] \u2013 guitar on \"Growin' Up\"\n\n=== Production personnel ===\n*David Bowie \u2013 producer\n*[[Ken Scott]] \u2013 producer\n*Dennis MacKay \u2013 [[recording engineer|engineer]]\n*[[Andy Scott]] \u2013 [[recording engineer|engineer]]\n*Dr. Toby Mountain \u2013 [[audio mastering|mastering engineer]] (1990)\n*Jonathan Wyner \u2013 mastering assistant (1990)\n*[[Peter Mew]] \u2013 mastering engineer (1999)\n*Nigel Reeve \u2013 mastering engineer (1999)\n\n== Charts ==\n'''Album'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Chart\n!Peak position\n|-\n|1973\n|Finnish album Charts\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|1973\n|[[UK Albums Chart]]<ref name=ukt40>{{cite web |url=http://www.everyhit.com |title=UK Top 40 Hit Database |accessdate=15 July 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151106234723/http://www.everyhit.com/ |archive-date=6 November 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|1973\n|[[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' Pop Albums]]<ref name=allmusicalbums>{{cite web |url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r2484|pure_url=yes}} |title=allmusic ((( Pin Ups > Charts & Awards > Billboard Albums ))) |accessdate=15 July 2008 |publisher=allmusic}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|23\n|-\n|1973\n|Norwegian album Charts\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|-\n|1973\n|Australian [[Kent Report]] album Charts\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|4\n|}\n\n'''Single'''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Single\n!Chart\n!Peak position\n|-\n|1973\n|\"Sorrow\"\n|[[UK Singles Chart]]<ref name=ukt40 />\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n|}\n\n==Certifications and sales==\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|title=Pin Ups|type=album|artist=David Bowie|relyear=1974|region=Australia|award=Gold|salesamount=100,000$|certref=<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Billboard/70s/1974/Billboard%201974-10-26.pdf|title=Australian Gold|date=26 October 1974|website=Billboard|page=78|via=American Radio History|accessdate=20 November 2019}}</ref>}}\n{{certification Table Entry|title=Pin Ups|type=album|artist=David Bowie|relyear=1974|region=France|nocert=true|salesamount=130,300|salesref=<ref>{{cite web|url=http://infodisc.fr/Ventes_Albums_Tout_Temps.php?debut=3400|title=InfoDisc : Les Meilleurs Ventes d'Albums \"Tout Temps\" (33 T. / Cd / T\u00e9l\u00e9chargement)|first=InfoDisc, Daniel Lesueur, Dominic Durand|last=Lesueur|date=|website=infodisc.fr|accessdate=20 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191201150134/http://infodisc.fr/Ventes_Albums_Tout_Temps.php?debut=3400|archive-date=1 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n{{certification Table Entry|title=Pin Ups|type=album|artist=David Bowie|relyear=1974|certyear=1973|region=United Kingdom|award=Gold|salesamount=147,000|salesref= <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Billboard/70s/1973/Billboard%201973-10-20.pdf|title=From the Music Capitals of the World|publisher=Billboard|via=American Radio History|page=61|date=20 October 1973|accessdate=20 November 2019}}</ref>}}\n{{certification Table Bottom}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n;Sources\n* {{cite book|last=Sandford|first=Christopher|title=Bowie: Loving the Alien|publisher=Time Warner|year=1997|origyear=First published 1996|isbn=978-0-306-80854-8|ref=harv|url=https://archive.org/details/bowielovingalien00sand}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.5years.com/pinups.htm ''Pinups'' at The Ziggy Stardust Companion]\n*{{discogs master|22208|Pinups}}\n\n{{David Bowie}}\n\n[[Category:1973 albums]]\n[[Category:David Bowie albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by David Bowie]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Ken Scott]]\n[[Category:Albums with cover art by Mick Rock]]\n[[Category:Covers albums]]\n[[Category:EMI Records albums]]\n[[Category:Glam rock albums by English artists]]\n[[Category:Parlophone albums]]\n[[Category:RCA Records albums]]\n[[Category:Rykodisc albums]]\n[[Category:Virgin Records albums]]\n[[Category:Albums recorded in a home studio]]\n", "name_user": "Zmbro", "label": "safe", "comment": "ce lead; small exp", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pin_Ups"}
{"title_page": "2009 World Cup of Pool", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Professional pairs nine-ball tournament, held September 2009}}\n{{Infobox pool tournament\n|tournament_name=\n|dates=\n|startdate=1\n|enddate=6 September 2009\n|venue=[[SM City North EDSA#The Annex (Annex 1)|The Annex]] of [[SM City North EDSA]]\n|city=[[Quezon City]]\n|country=[[Philippines]]\n|organisation=[[Matchroom Sport]]\n|format=[[Single elimination tournament]]\n|Total prize fund=$250,000\n|winners_share=$30,000 per player\n|highest_break=\n|defending_champion=\n|winner={{flag|Philippines}} B ([[Francisco Bustamante]] and [[Efren Reyes]])\n|runner_up={{flag|Germany}} ([[Ralf Souquet]] and [[Thorsten Hohmann]])\n|score=11\u20139\n|previous=[[2008 World Cup of Pool|2008]]\n|next=[[2010 World Cup of Pool|2010]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2009 World Cup of Pool''' (also known as the '''2009 PartyPoker World Cup of Pool''' due to sponsorship) was a professional [[pool (cue sports)|pool]] tournament played in the discipline of [[nine-ball]].  The event was the fourth [[World Cup of Pool]], a [[scotch doubles]] knockout championship representing 32 national teams. The cup was played at [[SM City North EDSA#The Annex (Annex 1)|the Annex]] of [[SM City North EDSA]] in [[Quezon City]], Philippines from 1 to 6 September 2009. The Korean team of [[Ga Young Kim]] and [[Yun Mi Lim]] were the first all-female team to participate at the event. The tournament featured a prize fund of [[$]]250,000 with the winner receiving $60,000. It was sponsored by online poker website [[partypoker]].\n\nThe defending champions were [[Rodney Morris]] and [[Shane Van Boening]] representing the USA, who had won the [[2008 World Cup of Pool|2008 event]] 11\u20137 over the English team of [[Daryl Peach]] and [[Mark Gray]] in the final. The USA team were defeated in the quarter-finals by the Chinese pair [[Fu Jian-bo]] and [[Li He-wen]] 5\u20139. The event was won by the Filipino team of [[Francisco Bustamante]] and [[Efren Reyes]], who defeated the German team of [[Ralf Souquet]] and [[Thorsten Hohmann]] in the 2009 final 11\u20139. The event was organised and later broadcast by [[Matchroom Sport]].\n\n==Tournament format==\n[[File:SM The Annex.jpg|thumb|The Annex of [[SM City North EDSA]], site of the 2009 World Cup of Pool.]]\nThe 2009 World Cup of Pool was a pairs [[nine-ball]] tournament played at the [[SM City North EDSA#The Annex (Annex 1)|the Annex]] of [[SM City North EDSA]] in [[Quezon City]], Philippines. The tournament was played as [[scotch doubles]], with players taking shots alternatively. Matches were played as a {{cuegloss|race}}-to-eight {{cuegloss|racks}} until the quarter-finals, which were race-to-nine along with the semi-finals, and the final was a race-to-11 racks.<ref name=\"B8x00\" /><ref name=\"Hmcwr\" /> The tournament was a [[single elimination]] bracket, consisting of 32 teams.<ref name=\"dqU1D\" /> Of the 32 teams, 16 were [[seed (sports)|seeded]]; whilst 16 were unseeded.<ref name=\"dqU1D\" /><ref name=\"azbi_Gian\" /><ref name=\"pro9_Firs\" />\n\nThe defending champions were the USA team of [[Rodney Morris]] and [[Shane Van Boening]] who defeated [[Dennis Orcollo]] and [[Francisco Bustamante]] in the final of the [[2008 World Cup of Pool|previous year's event]].<ref name=\"bdhvf\" /> The two other previous winners of the event also participated. The event was sponsored by online poker website [[partypoker]],<ref name=\"CEzNY\" /> and organised by [[Matchroom Sport]].<ref name=\"matchroom\">{{Cite web |title=Philippines to host 2009 World Cup of Pool |work=azbilliards.com |access-date=20 April 2020 |url=https://www.azbilliards.com/news/stories/5249-philippines-to-host-2009-world-cup-of-pool/ }}</ref> The tournament was broadcast as 31 one-hour episodes also produced by Matchroom.<ref name=\"matchroom\"/> Locally, the event was broadcast live on [[Solar Sports]] and [[CS9]].<ref name=\"Finland\"/>\n\n===Prize fund===\nPrize money for the event featured $250,000 with $60,000 being awarded to the winning team.<ref name=\"azbi_Part\" /> This was similar to that of the [[2008 World Cup of Pool|previous year's event]].<ref name=\"70ps6\" /> Money earned was shared between the players. A breakdown of prize money is shown below:<ref name=\"dqU1D\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Stage !! Prize Money\n|-\n| Winner || [[United States dollar|$]]60,000\n|-\n| Runner-up || $30,000\n|-\n| Semi-final || $16,000\n|-\n| Quarter-final || $10,000\n|-\n| Second round || $5,000\n|-\n| First round || $3,000\n|-\n| Total || $250,000\n|-\n|}/\n\n===Teams===\nParticipating nations for the event were announced on 31 July 2009, with 31 countries participating, two teams representing the host nation Philippines.<ref name=\"azbi_Worl\" /><ref name=\"pro9_2009\" /> The teams were announced on 14 August with all three prior winners of the competition participating.<ref name=\"azbi_Gian\" /> An all female team, representing Korea, competed at the event for the first time.<ref name=\"azbi_Gian\" /> The teams are listed below:<ref name=\"dqU1D\" /><ref name=\"azbi_Gian\" /><ref name=\"pro9_Firs\" />\n{{col-start}}{{col-break}}\n*Seeded teams:\n*#{{flag|USA}} ([[Rodney Morris]] and [[Shane Van Boening]])\n*#{{flag|Philippines}} A ([[Ronato Alcano]] and [[Dennis Orcollo]])\n*#{{flag|Germany}} ([[Ralf Souquet]] and [[Thorsten Hohmann]])\n*#{{flag|England}} ([[Darren Appleton]] and [[Imran Majid]])\n*#{{flag|Philippines}} B ([[Francisco Bustamante]] and [[Efren Reyes]])\n*#{{flag|Netherlands|name=Holland}} ([[Niels Feijen]] and [[Nick van den Berg]])\n*#{{flag|Chinese Taipei|name=Taiwan}} ([[Lai Chia-Hsiung]] and [[Yang Ching-shun]])\n*#{{flag|Finland}} ([[Mika Immonen]] and [[Markus Juva]])\n*#{{flag|China}} ([[Fu Jian-bo]] and [[Li He-wen]])\n*#{{flag|Poland}} ([[Rados\u0142aw Babica]] and [[Mateusz Sniegocki]])\n*#{{flag|Japan}} ([[Hayato Hijikata]] and [[Satoshi Kawabata]])\n*#{{flag|Italy}} ([[Bruno Muratore]] and [[Fabio Petroni]])\n*#{{flag|Spain}} ([[David Alcaide]] and [[Rafael Guzman]])\n*#{{flag|Canada}} ([[Tyler Edey]] and [[Jason Klatt]])\n*#{{flag|Russia}} ([[Ruslan Chinakhov]] and [[Konstantin Stepanov]])\n*#{{flag|India}} ([[Raj Hundal]] and [[Dharminder Singh Lilly]])\n{{col-break}}\n*Unseeded teams:\n**{{flag|Australia}} (Lou Condo and Greg Jenkins)\n**{{flag|Austria}} (Martin Kempter and [[Jasmin Ouschan]])\n**{{flag|Belgium}} (Pascal Budo and Serge Das)\n**{{flag|Croatia}} (Philipp Stojanovic and Ivica Putnik)\n**{{flag|Denmark}} (Kasper Kristoffersen and Bahram Lotfy)\n**{{flag|France}} (Stephan Cohen and Vincent Facquet)\n**{{flag|Hong Kong}} (Kenny Kwok and Lee Chenman)\n**{{flag|Indonesia}} (Muhammad Bewi Simanjuntak and Muhammad Zulfikri)\n**{{flag|South Korea|name=Korea}} ([[Ga-Young Kim]] and Yun-Mi Lim)\n**{{flag|Malaysia}} (Ibrahim Bin Amir and Lee Poh Soon)\n**{{flag|Malta}} ([[Alex Borg]] and [[Tony Drago]])\n**{{flag|Qatar}} (Bashar Hussain and Mohammed Ali Bin Ali)\n**{{flag|Singapore}} (Chan Keng Kwang and Toh Lian Han)\n**{{flag|Sweden}} ([[Marcus Chamat]] and [[Tom Storm (pool player)|Tom Storm]])\n**{{flag|Thailand}} (Nitiwat Kanjanasri and Surethep Phoochalam)\n**{{flag|Vietnam}} ([[Luong Chi Dung]] and [[Nguyen Thanh Nam]])\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Tournament Summary==\n===Early rounds===\n[[File:Efren Reyes in the World 9-Ball Pool Championship.jpg|thumb|[[Efren Reyes]] (pictured) and [[Francisco Bustamante]] won the tournament with a 11\u20139 victory in the final.]]\nThe tournament began on 1 September 2009, with the first round played until 3 September.<ref name=\"xk7Yn\" /> The opening match of the tournament featured the French team of [[Stephan Cohen]] and [[Vincent Facquet]] win 8\u20131 over the Canadian team.<ref name=France/> The first two rounds were played as a race-to-8-racks. The defending champion USA team of [[Rodney Morris]] and [[Shane Van Boening]] met the Maltese team of [[Alex Borg]] and [[Tony Drago]] in the opening match.<ref name=\"azbi_USAO\" /> The match was tied at 7\u20137, but a {{cuegloss|dry break}} by Drago allowed USA to win 8\u20137.<ref name=\"azbi_Defe\" /> The unseeded Indonesian team won their opening round match over the Indian team 8\u20133 to draw the USA in the second round.<ref name=\"azbi_Spai\">{{Cite web |title=Spain and Indonesia March On at World Cup of Pool |work=azbilliards.com |access-date=20 April 2020 |url=https://www.azbilliards.com/news/stories/5935-spain-and-indonesia-march-on-at-world-cup-of-pool/ }}</ref>\n\nAn all-female team competed for the first time at the event, with the Korean team of [[Ga Young Kim]] and [[Yun Mi Lim]]. The pair lead 3\u20130 before being defeated 5\u20138 by the ninth seed and [[2007 World Cup of Pool|2007 championship]] winning team of [[Li He-wen]] and [[Fu Jian-bo]] from China, who won six racks in-a-row.<ref name=\"CBN\" /><ref name=France>{{Cite web |title=China and France score round one World Cup wins |work=azbilliards.com |access-date=20 April 2020 |url=https://www.azbilliards.com/news/stories/5934-china-and-france-score-round-one-world-cup-wins/ }}</ref> The Filipino A side of [[Ronnie Alcano]] and [[Dennis Orcollo]] won their match against the Thai team 8\u20135, despite trailing 4\u20135.<ref name=\"CBN\" />\n\nJapan were trailing at 3\u20136 behind in their match against Croatia, before winning six straight racks to win 8\u20136.<ref name=\"azbi_Japa\">{{Cite web |title=Japan Comeback KOs Croats \u2013 Germans White Wash Hong Kong |work=azbilliards.com |access-date=20 April 2020 |url=https://www.azbilliards.com/news/stories/5939-japan-comeback-kos-croats-germans-white-wash-hong-kong/ }}</ref> German [[Thorsten Hohmann]] commented that he would want to play with his partner [[Ralf Souquet]] above any other player after his first round match. The team defeated the Hong Kong team of Kenny Kwok and Lee Chenman in a [[whitewash (sport)|whitewash]] 8\u20130.<ref name=\"azbi_Japa\"/> The [[2007 World Cup of Pool|2007]] runners-up Finland played Sweden in the first round. The finish team won 8\u20133 over [[Tom Storm]] and [[Marcus Chamat]].<ref name=\"Finland\">{{Cite web |title=World Cup of Pool: Finland Ease Home in Scandinavian Clash \u2013 Italy Make Round Two |work=azbilliards.com |access-date=20 April 2020 |url=https://www.azbilliards.com/news/stories/5941-world-cup-of-pool-finland-ease-home-in-scandinavian-clash-italy-make-round-two/ }}</ref>\n\nThe second round was played from 4 to the 5 September.<ref name=\"sportsman\" /> Thirteenth seed Spain played the fourth seed English side of [[Darren Appleton]] and [[Imran Majid]].<ref name=\"sportsman\" /> In the 13th rack, with the match tied at 6\u20136, [[David Alcaide]] called a foul on himself that neither the referee or the English side had seen. The English side won this, and the next rack to win 8\u20136 and eliminate the Spanish team.<ref name=\"1wWrH\" /> Following the match England's [[Darren Appleton]] called Alcaide a \"great sportsman\".<ref name=\"sportsman\" /> \n\nThe Philippine B side played the Italian team in the second round. The Italian team were trailing at 4\u20136, when referee Cielo Lopez deemed [[Bruno Muratore]]'s arm had struck the cue-ball.<ref name=\"784hs\" /> Later television replays were inconclusive.<ref name=\"azbi_USAP\" /> The Italian team won only one more rack and were defeated 5\u20138. The Philippine A side of Orcollo and Alcano won eight straight racks after trailing 0\u20133 to the Russian side to win 8\u20133. Russia's [[Ruslan Chinachov]] was only 17-years-old; but missed some \"crucial shots\" during the match.<ref name=\"sportsman\" />\n\nThe quarter-finals were played on the 5 September and as a race-to-9 racks.<ref name=\"quarter1\" /><ref name=\"quarter2\" /> Both home Philippines teams reached the quarter-finals. Alcano and Orcollo defeated the Polish team of [[Rados\u0142aw Babica]] and [[Mateusz Sniegocki]] 9\u20135. The Philippines trailed 0\u20132 and 4\u20132 before eventually winning 9\u20135.<ref name=\"quarter2\" /> The English side won only one rack, when trailing by three racks, and eventually lost 1\u20139.<ref name=\"quarter1\" /> The defending champions were defeated by the Chinese team. China were 1\u20133 behind, but won seven racks in a row, and eventually won 9\u20135.<ref name=\"quarter1\" /> The final quarter-final featured the German team of [[Ralf Souquet]] and [[Thorsten Hohmann]] defeating the Netherlands 9\u20137.<ref name=\"quarter2\" />\n\n===Later rounds (semi-final\u2014final)===\nThe semi-finals were played on 6 September, as race-to-9 racks matches.<ref name=\"azbi_Worl_QR8l0\" /> The first semi-final, the Chinese and Filipino teams were equal at 8\u20138.<ref name=\"finalazb\" /> In the deciding rack, the Chinese team had the break, but Fu missed a two-ball {{cuegloss|combination}} on the second shot.<ref name=\"Final day\" /> The Filipino team of Reyes and Bustamante ran the rest of the rack to win 9\u20138.<ref name=\"finalazb\" /> The second semi-final featured the other Philippine team face the Germans. The German team prevented an all home-nation final, winning 9\u20136.<ref name=\"Final day\" /><ref name=\"pro9_Pro9\" />\n\nThe final was also played on 6 September as a race-to-11 racks match.<ref name=\"finalazb\" /> Germany won the {{cuegloss|lag}} and broke first, but failed to win any of the first three racks.<ref name=\"De5pl\" /> The German team won five straight racks to lead 5\u20133, before the Philippines tied the match 6\u20136.<ref name=\"SptuY\" /> Rack 14 was a long rack, with a prlongued bout of safety play with Reyes and Bustamante both missing long pots.<ref name=\"azbi_Phil\" /> Souquet himself converted a long shot at the {{cuegloss|9-ball}} to put the Germans up 8\u20136.<ref name=\"ORYCO\" /> The Philipino team won four of the next five racks to get to the {{cuegloss|hill}} at 10\u20139 ahead.<ref name=\"pro9_Pro9\" /><ref name=\"NNU7b\" /> The Philipino team won the next rack to win the tournament winning 11\u20139.<ref name=\"Final day\" />\n\n==Results==\nBelow is the results from the event. Teams in bold denote match winners. Numbers to the left of teams represents the team's seedings.\n{{32TeamBracket \n| RD1=Round 1<br />Race to 8\n| RD2=Round 2<br />Race to 8\n| RD3=Quarter-finals<br />Race to 9 \n| RD4=Semi-finals<br />Race to 9 \n| RD5=Final<br />Race to 11\n| team-width=130px\n\n| RD1-seed01=1\n| RD1-team01='''{{flag|USA}}'''\n| RD1-score01='''8'''\n| RD1-seed02=\n| RD1-team02={{flag|Malta}}\n| RD1-score02=7\n\n| RD1-seed03=16\n| RD1-team03={{flag|India}}\n| RD1-score03=3\n| RD1-seed04=\n| RD1-team04='''{{flag|Indonesia}}'''\n| RD1-score04='''8'''\n\n| RD1-seed05=9\n| RD1-team05='''{{flag|China}}'''\n| RD1-score05='''8'''\n| RD1-seed06=\n| RD1-team06={{flag|South Korea|name=Korea}}\n| RD1-score06=5\n\n| RD1-seed07=8\n| RD1-team07='''{{flag|Finland}}'''\n| RD1-score07='''8'''\n| RD1-seed08=\n| RD1-team08={{flag|Sweden}}\n| RD1-score08=3\n\n| RD1-seed09=5\n| RD1-team09='''{{flag|Philippines}} B\n| RD1-score09='''8'''\n| RD1-seed10=\n| RD1-team10={{flag|Qatar}}\n| RD1-score10=3\n\n| RD1-seed11=12\n| RD1-team11='''{{flag|Italy}}'''\n| RD1-score11='''8'''\n| RD1-seed12=\n| RD1-team12={{flag|Austria}}\n| RD1-score12=5\n\n| RD1-seed13=13\n| RD1-team13='''{{flag|Spain}}'''\n| RD1-score13='''8'''\n| RD1-seed14=\n| RD1-team14={{flag|Australia}}\n| RD1-score14=3\n\n| RD1-seed15=4\n| RD1-team15='''{{flag|England}}'''\n| RD1-score15='''8'''\n| RD1-seed16=\n| RD1-team16={{flag|Malaysia}}\n| RD1-score16=4\n\n| RD1-seed17=3\n| RD1-team17='''{{flag|Germany}}'''\n| RD1-score17='''8'''\n| RD1-seed18=\n| RD1-team18={{flag|Hong Kong}}\n| RD1-score18=0\n\n| RD1-seed19=14\n| RD1-team19={{flag|Canada}}\n| RD1-score19=1\n| RD1-seed20=\n| RD1-team20='''{{flag|France}}'''\n| RD1-score20='''8'''\n\n| RD1-seed21=11\n| RD1-team21='''{{flag|Japan}}'''\n| RD1-score21='''8'''\n| RD1-seed22=\n| RD1-team22={{flag|Croatia}}\n| RD1-score22=6\n\n| RD1-seed23=9\n| RD1-t